broken_generic_manor_375a5026	broken	It is a decent-sized house.	game/scripts/broken/broken_generic_choices.rpy	228	broken "[what]"
broken_generic_manor_85772fd9	broken	Probably originally for a wealthy local landowner.	game/scripts/broken/broken_generic_choices.rpy	228	broken "[what]"
broken_generic_manor_2426b9d3	broken	Though it is not large enough for an important aristocrat like a Duke or an Earl.	game/scripts/broken/broken_generic_choices.rpy	228	broken "[what]"
broken_generic_manor_a62357ab	broken	I do not know much about this Lady Claythorn, but her family are probably squires or baronets.	game/scripts/broken/broken_generic_choices.rpy	228	broken "[what]"
broken_generic_manor_1e492207	broken	Unless they are just wealthy industrialists and they added the "Lady" to lend some prestige to their name.	game/scripts/broken/broken_generic_choices.rpy	228	broken "[what]"
broken_generic_manor_d42f60f2	broken	That would be quite outrageous if that were the case.	game/scripts/broken/broken_generic_choices.rpy	228	broken "[what]"
broken_generic_manor_a974b189	doctor	Really? I would not have thought of that.	game/scripts/broken/broken_generic_choices.rpy	242	doctor "[what]"
broken_generic_manor_39e122f8	doctor	Where did you learn all of this?	game/scripts/broken/broken_generic_choices.rpy	242	doctor "[what]"
broken_generic_manor_e011688b	broken	Because I was raised in a house a bit like this one.	game/scripts/broken/broken_generic_choices.rpy	248	broken "[what]"
broken_generic_manor_77c50972	broken	I started as a bootboy when I was a wee lad, but quickly rose in rank to become a footman.	game/scripts/broken/broken_generic_choices.rpy	248	broken "[what]"
broken_generic_manor_0ec85ab5	broken	Then the war happened and everything changed.	game/scripts/broken/broken_generic_choices.rpy	248	broken "[what]"
broken_generic_manor_offended_afceae43	doctor	I understand that you did not want to keep doing this after the war.	game/scripts/broken/broken_generic_choices.rpy	269	doctor "[what]"
broken_generic_manor_offended_51771da3	doctor	It must have seemed too trivial to keep being a servant after such a horrific experience.	game/scripts/broken/broken_generic_choices.rpy	269	doctor "[what]"
broken_generic_manor_offended_993fb50e	broken	Not really.	game/scripts/broken/broken_generic_choices.rpy	275	broken "[what]"
broken_generic_manor_offended_a14f7985	broken	I do not think there is anything wrong with being a servant.	game/scripts/broken/broken_generic_choices.rpy	275	broken "[what]"
broken_generic_manor_offended_6660fc1b	broken	I would have loved to keep doing this job.	game/scripts/broken/broken_generic_choices.rpy	275	broken "[what]"
broken_generic_manor_offended_666eb89c	broken	I even hoped to be a butler someday.	game/scripts/broken/broken_generic_choices.rpy	275	broken "[what]"
broken_generic_manor_offended_e5f2632e	broken	But it turns out a footman has to fit certain characteristics.	game/scripts/broken/broken_generic_choices.rpy	275	broken "[what]"
broken_generic_manor_offended_290a17a7	broken	For instance, they have to be tall.	game/scripts/broken/broken_generic_choices.rpy	275	broken "[what]"
broken_generic_manor_offended_ef87fe1c	broken	I am not sure why, but it is a matter of pride for them to have the tallest servants possible.	game/scripts/broken/broken_generic_choices.rpy	275	broken "[what]"
broken_generic_manor_offended_70e7697c	broken	It is all part of us being seen as part of the "image" of their property.	game/scripts/broken/broken_generic_choices.rpy	275	broken "[what]"
broken_generic_manor_offended_29fab326	broken	As you can guess, when I returned from the war, I was not considered "footman" material and was relegated to grunt work.	game/scripts/broken/broken_generic_choices.rpy	275	broken "[what]"
