broken_introduction_fc8132ee		He won't have to wear it anymore.	game/scripts/broken/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	20	"[what]"
broken_introduction_e525f88b		That's not so bad, he couldn't bare the look of the people around him.	game/scripts/broken/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	20	"[what]"
broken_introduction_fdbc0f5d		After dedicated his youth to the army he ends up alone in his apartment.	game/scripts/broken/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	20	"[what]"
broken_introduction_9f25cc4a		To scared to go out most of the time.	game/scripts/broken/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	20	"[what]"
broken_introduction_8b5e55de		The loneliness might have been the cause of death as much the failings of his aching body.	game/scripts/broken/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	20	"[what]"
broken_introduction_902a5e3c		I search about his place and found nothing that was not a necessity.	game/scripts/broken/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	20	"[what]"
broken_introduction_b03781a0		On his desk is a picture of us when we were teens, the caption reads: Thomas and Archie spring 1892).	game/scripts/broken/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	20	"[what]"
