captain_generic_weather_friday_8018a0d2	captain	I can see that a storm is coming.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	18	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_weather_friday_bf773979	captain	And it looks like a big one.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	18	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_weather_saturday_ee9e5c34	captain	The little storm we had yesterday seems to have worn off.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	28	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_weather_saturday_55b5f900	captain	The weather should improve from now on.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	28	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_weather_sunday_7d95538e	captain	(Placeholder for Sunday weather dialogue)	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	39	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_room_322bdc11	captain	The 'George I' Bedroom.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	47	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_room_e61476ab	captain	The most remarkable thing about 'George I' is that ...	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	53	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_room_13bd856c	psychic	He was a foreigner, yes.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	57	psychic "[what]"
captain_generic_room_f1b551de	psychic	As the first King of the house of Hanover, he was born in Germany and had a very limited grasp of English.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	57	psychic "[what]"
captain_generic_room_5be340dc	captain	Well, I was going to say his reign marked the beginning of the gradual transformation of the British monarchy into a more constitutional one,	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	63	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_room_ac5f35ed	captain	with real political power shifting towards Parliament and ministers.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	63	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_room_5484fc80	captain	But I guess you're right too.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	63	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_origin_psychic_1_a2259021	captain	I come directly from London.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	78	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_origin_psychic_1_618f0390	captain	I have been living there for the last two decades.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	78	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_origin_psychic_1_e98109b0	psychic	London.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	86	psychic "[what]"
captain_generic_origin_psychic_1_2647918a	psychic	Right.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	86	psychic "[what]"
captain_generic_origin_psychic_1_8960b560	psychic	But that's not what I meant.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	86	psychic "[what]"
captain_generic_origin_psychic_1_a6673bc7	captain	I am sorry, what did you mean?	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	94	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_origin_psychic_2_ec03c888	captain	Oh ... I was raised in Calcutta.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	105	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_origin_psychic_2_fa6bd432	captain	But I've been living in England for so long that I don't even think about it anymore.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	105	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_origin_psychic_2_36834ad8	psychic	Alright. Calcutta is in the far east, right?	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	111	psychic "[what]"
captain_generic_origin_psychic_2_8a38ef20	captain	Yes, it's in North India.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	115	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_origin_psychic_2_f76468e2	captain	I was born there.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	119	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_origin_psychic_2_cbbf22a0	captain	My noble lineage ensured I received an excellent education, far superior to most in the region.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	119	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_origin_psychic_2_bfbb7792	captain	Growing up, I was always fascinated by the stories of the Raj army and their brave officers.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	119	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_origin_psychic_2_f304eefc	captain	I knew from a young age that I wanted to join the army and serve my country.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	119	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_origin_psychic_2_e3069fd2	captain	As I grew older, I began to prepare myself for the rigorous training that would be required to become an officer in the Raj army.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	119	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_origin_psychic_2_bcaba3c1	captain	I studied hard and practiced my shooting and horseback riding skills.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	119	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_origin_psychic_2_ea9447ad	captain	I also learned about the history of India and the British Raj, so that I could understand the context of the conflicts that the army was involved in.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	119	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_origin_psychic_2_54e5ba8a	captain	Finally, in 1890, I was accepted into the Raj army as a cadet.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	119	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_origin_psychic_2_6d6ddda4	captain	The training was grueling, but I was determined to succeed.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	119	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_origin_psychic_2_7bcd310c	captain	I was taught how to march, how to shoot, and how to lead my men in battle.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	119	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_origin_psychic_2_4993ca85	captain	I also learned about strategy and tactics, so that I could make quick decisions in the heat of battle.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	119	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_origin_psychic_2_0b836221	captain	After two years of training, I was finally commissioned as an officer.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	119	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_origin_psychic_2_df1d399c	captain	I was assigned to a regiment and sent to the frontier, where I would be fighting against the tribes that were trying to rebel against the British Raj.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	119	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_origin_psychic_2_e2fd4c17	captain	It was a difficult and dangerous assignment, but I was determined to do my best.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	119	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_origin_psychic_2_7482a564	captain	I led my men into battle and fought bravely, always thinking of the safety and well-being of my men.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	119	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_origin_psychic_2_a5b103bb	captain	I was able to successfully quell the rebellion, and my men and I returned home as heroes.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	119	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_origin_psychic_2_58d70a4a	captain	I continued to serve in the Raj army for many years, rising through the ranks and taking on more responsibility.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	119	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_origin_psychic_2_e7a16a77	captain	As the years went by, I was increasingly exposed to the ways of the British army and began to adopt their techniques and strategies.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	119	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_origin_psychic_2_85ec09e8	captain	I was eventually sent to London to train new officers, ...	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	119	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_origin_psychic_2_47640804		My god, he is going to tell me his whole life story.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	161	"[what]"
captain_generic_origin_psychic_2_1b9587c9		How rude.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	161	"[what]"
captain_generic_origin_psychic_2_54726f0c		And there is no way to avoid him here.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	161	"[what]"
captain_generic_origin_psychic_2_82dc35ec		So I nod in assent and barely listen to what he is saying.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	161	"[what]"
captain_generic_background_psychic_47774692		Wait, why am I encouraging him?	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	181	"[what]"
captain_generic_background_psychic_564538ac	captain	Oh, I thought I already said plenty in the car.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	185	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_background_psychic_f2dca49e	captain	But, if you insist of course.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	185	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_background_psychic_cdf1d292	captain	Where did we stop last time?	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	185	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_background_psychic_1aae2919	captain	Ah yes, I was telling you about the time I was sent to London.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	185	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_background_psychic_d05af1e4	captain	My mission there was to train new officers, a duty I regarded as both an honour and a burden.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	185	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_background_psychic_6a29c791	captain	The young men were eager, full of fire, but they had little understanding of what it truly meant to lead others into danger.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	185	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_background_psychic_4a92c273	captain	It was my task to temper their enthusiasm with discipline, to teach them not merely how to fight, but how to think, how to endure, and how to carry the weight of command.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	185	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_background_psychic_36e54733	captain	In those years I saw the very best and the very worst of human nature.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	185	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_background_psychic_9c3816be	captain	Some rose splendidly to the challenge, others faltered and fell away.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	185	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_background_psychic_287c3248	captain	But I gave them all that I could, for I knew that the fate of many would one day rest upon their shoulders, just as it had once rested upon mine.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	185	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_background_psychic_0a60fac0	captain	When at last my service came to its end, I retired with a measure of pride, though also with a heavy heart.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	185	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_background_psychic_67bdebeb	captain	For the army had been my life, my purpose, and leaving it behind was no easy thing.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	185	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_background_psychic_015884d8	captain	Still, I hold no regrets. I served faithfully, and I did my duty, as any officer ought.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	185	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_background_psychic_3b687249		All right, I think I have heard his whole life story now.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	213	"[what]"
captain_generic_heroic_act_psychic_bedb8fce	captain	It is most likely because of my actions during the Great War.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	224	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_heroic_act_psychic_49c1e846	captain	In particular, those in 1917, during the Mesopotamian campaign.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	224	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_heroic_act_psychic_fac9ff57	captain	Our regiment was tasked with taking control of a heavily fortified Turkish position.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	224	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_heroic_act_psychic_dc98ad02	captain	The battle was intense and brutal, with heavy gunfire and explosions all around us.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	224	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_heroic_act_psychic_991cd961	captain	I led my men through the chaos, urging them forward and providing cover fire.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	224	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_heroic_act_psychic_c62c8adf	captain	Despite the danger, we were able to push through the enemy lines and take control of the position.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	224	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_heroic_act_psychic_7b228db4	captain	I was severely injured in the battle, but I refused to be taken off the field until the objective was secured.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	224	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_heroic_act_psychic_a812b963	captain	My actions, bravery and leadership inspired my men and led to the success of our mission.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	224	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_heroic_act_psychic_41ba9263	captain	For my actions, I was awarded the Military Cross, one of the highest honors that can be given to an officer of the British army.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	224	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_heroic_act_psychic_783115db	captain	I was proud to have served my country and to have played a role in the ultimate victory of the Great War.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	224	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_heroic_act_psychic_36358427		Well, he certainly likes to tell a story in full.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	246	"[what]"
captain_generic_heroic_act_psychic_9a24ff7d		That's my fault for asking.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	246	"[what]"
captain_generic_manor_psychic_b951793e	captain	It's a splendid house.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	259	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_manor_psychic_d2d27182	captain	A bit old, and it could use some renovations.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	259	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_manor_psychic_c82deed5	captain	But I know it is no easy task.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	259	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_manor_psychic_183d66ce	captain	I have seen my fair share of grand buildings and stately homes, and I can confidently say that renovating an old Victorian mansion is no easy feat.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	268	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_manor_psychic_9ac8668d	captain	The challenge lies in balancing the preservation of the building's historical integrity with the necessary updates and modernizations for contemporary living.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	268	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_manor_psychic_90277ade	captain	One issue that often arises is the cost of renovations.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	268	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_manor_psychic_4d1cc68e	captain	Victorian mansions were built with materials and techniques that are not always easily replicated today, making repairs and replacements quite expensive.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	268	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_manor_psychic_6fd333ac	captain	Additionally, many of these homes have unique architectural features that require specialized skills and knowledge to maintain.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	268	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_manor_psychic_9578fc1f	captain	Another obstacle to overcome is the potential for structural issues.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	268	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_manor_psychic_3e5e67d8	captain	Victorian mansions are often quite old, and over time, they can suffer from wear and tear.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	268	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_manor_psychic_20cbe9f8	captain	This means that any renovation work will need to be done with an eye towards ensuring the building's stability and safety.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	268	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_manor_psychic_55e84e4a	captain	Personally, I believe that renovating an old Victorian mansion is a noble endeavor.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	268	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_manor_psychic_2e84e1e8	captain	These buildings are a testament to a bygone era and preserving them for future generations is important.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	268	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_manor_psychic_75fd6f3f	captain	However, it is crucial to approach the task with a realistic understanding of the challenges and costs involved.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	268	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_manor_psychic_cbe826d2	captain	A balance must be struck between maintaining the historical integrity of the building and ensuring that it is functional and comfortable for modern living.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	268	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_manor_psychic_d32dcf19	captain	Ultimately, renovating an old Victorian mansion is not for the faint of heart, but for those who are willing to put in the time, effort, and resources, the end result can be truly spectacular.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	268	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_manor_psychic_78b3bc04		Another long story.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	296	"[what]"
captain_generic_manor_psychic_b1fe256d		But how does he know such things?	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	296	"[what]"
captain_generic_manor_psychic_97e8b738		Is he one of those bookish people who read about everything and anything?	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	296	"[what]"
captain_generic_room_friday_3f75c1f8	captain	I am not sure actually.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	310	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_room_friday_8f26ad82	captain	I guess I'll see after dinner.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	310	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_age_psychic_456ddce0	captain	Why?	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	320	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_age_psychic_7d0c958d	captain	Are you having trouble guessing my age because I'm Indian?	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	320	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_age_psychic_7f093056	captain	Many people do.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	320	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_age_psychic_4bb78e26	psychic	Gosh no, I'm merely asking out of curiosity.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	328	psychic "[what]"
captain_generic_age_psychic_ad86d0bf	psychic	I didn't intend any offense.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	328	psychic "[what]"
captain_generic_age_psychic_2c61369c	captain	Hmph.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	334	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_age_psychic_a001c80a	captain	Very well.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	334	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_age_psychic_5b07e0a4	captain	I am 56 years old.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_choices.rpy	334	captain "[what]"
captain_library_default_159e3f8e		The library is as I left it.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	10	"[what]"
captain_library_default_454f8f41		I have already read what I needed from the genealogy book.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	16	"[what]"
captain_library_default_f6c02ecf		There is nothing more here for me.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	16	"[what]"
captain_library_default_b548ae0c		The genealogy book still lies open on the table, waiting.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	26	"[what]"
captain_library_default_6bb99aa2		A well-stocked library. The kind one would expect in a house like this.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	34	"[what]"
captain_library_default_f22c98ac		A book lies open on a table.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	34	"[what]"
captain_library_default_b8f97dc4		'A Genealogical and Heraldic Dictionary of the Landed Gentry of Great Britain.'	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	34	"[what]"
captain_library_default_15ec495b		The eighth edition, printed in 1894.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	34	"[what]"
captain_library_default_9882e308		I remember dreaming of seeing my name in such a book.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	34	"[what]"
captain_library_default_fe53ec87		I know now that it will never happen.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	34	"[what]"
captain_library_read_e8f50066		I glance through a few pages.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	60	"[what]"
captain_library_read_3ece375a		Let us see if the Claythorns are mentioned.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	60	"[what]"
captain_library_read_3b743e3f		I search through the index. Clarendon, Claridge, Clark...	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	60	"[what]"
captain_library_read_4009268c		Claythorn.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	60	"[what]"
captain_library_read_661c4207		There are several entries. I find the one concerning this manor.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	60	"[what]"
captain_library_read_2e358eaa		I read the entry twice.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	74	"[what]"
captain_library_read_b2311a24		There it is. The family name is Claythorn, but their title is not.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	74	"[what]"
captain_library_read_fb5f7bb6		They hold a peerage — the Earldom of Kilbraith. Their seat is this manor, but the title is quite separate.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	74	"[what]"
captain_library_read_82165c4a		A peer is addressed by his title, not by his surname. The Earl of Kilbraith is styled 'Lord Kilbraith', and his countess, 'Lady Kilbraith'.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	74	"[what]"
captain_library_read_4c122d17		Never 'Lord Claythorn', nor 'Lady Claythorn'.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	74	"[what]"
captain_library_read_a81b49f3		Still, I should not leap to conclusions.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	74	"[what]"
captain_library_read_ef38312d		It is not unheard of for a family to set the formal title aside in daily use.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	74	"[what]"
captain_library_read_8f12e1c3		Since the war, I have heard of peers who have grown weary of ceremony.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	74	"[what]"
captain_library_read_e9916f53		Or perhaps it is a local habit. The villagers call her 'Lady Claythorn' after the name of the house, and in time she has simply let it stick.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	74	"[what]"
captain_library_read_e50f7fd7		And yet, it is something strange enough that I should not dismiss it entirely.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	74	"[what]"
captain_library_read_0835a892		I close the book and place it back on the table.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	74	"[what]"
captain_host_suspicion_a14b95e4		That is the third intriguing thing I notice about Lady "Claythorn".	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	108	"[what]"
captain_host_suspicion_00ab546f		A lapse in manner at dinner.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	108	"[what]"
captain_host_suspicion_220ff81d		No visible portrait of her in her house.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	108	"[what]"
captain_host_suspicion_b036fd1b		And a rather unconventional use of her name.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	108	"[what]"
captain_host_suspicion_9871ee9e		What could this mean?	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	108	"[what]"
captain_host_suspicion_1ee2d95a		I am starting to fear that something is amiss here.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	108	"[what]"
captain_portrait_gallery_default_e1eb8dd6		The Claythorn forebears still gaze down from their frames, silent and stern.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	131	"[what]"
captain_portrait_gallery_default_faafe096		The absence of our host's portrait remains as striking as before.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	131	"[what]"
captain_portrait_gallery_default_ae94ed59		There is nothing more the gallery can tell me.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	131	"[what]"
captain_portrait_gallery_default_2e119cf3		A gallery of family portraits lines the walls.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	141	"[what]"
captain_portrait_gallery_default_9e0ee7c8		The Claythorn lineage, rendered in oil and gilt frames.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	141	"[what]"
captain_portrait_gallery_default_96415526		I study the faces. Old money, passed down through blood.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	141	"[what]"
captain_portrait_gallery_default_6de85618		There are perhaps a dozen portraits here, spanning several generations.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	141	"[what]"
captain_portrait_gallery_default_40c5c702		Stern-looking gentlemen in powdered wigs. Ladies in elaborate gowns.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	141	"[what]"
captain_portrait_gallery_default_1bc98436		But then something strikes me.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	141	"[what]"
captain_portrait_gallery_default_3f7d794e		None of them resemble our host.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	141	"[what]"
captain_portrait_gallery_default_c24ac71b		Where is Lady Claythorn?	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	141	"[what]"
captain_portrait_gallery_default_e6fb83e9		If she is the current mistress of this house, her portrait ought to hang here alongside her forebears.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	141	"[what]"
captain_portrait_gallery_default_1eb0c4df		And yet there is nothing.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	141	"[what]"
captain_portrait_gallery_default_8b52c618		And I do not recall seeing it anywhere else in the house.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	141	"[what]"
captain_portrait_gallery_default_505c07e2		In itself, that does not mean much.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	141	"[what]"
captain_portrait_gallery_default_ff1ef590		Perhaps she had difficulty persuading a decent artist to come all the way out here.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	141	"[what]"
captain_portrait_gallery_default_3736ddc0		Or, it could simply be a personal preference.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	141	"[what]"
captain_portrait_gallery_default_05a06fe6		But I will keep that in mind nonetheless.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_locations.rpy	141	"[what]"
captain_generic_other_guests_friday_2980903f	captain	Well, I don't know.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	10	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_other_guests_friday_a482b8c5	captain	I don't have a strong opinion about anyone at this point.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	10	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_other_guests_friday_0493b2f1	captain	Do you have someone in particular in mind?	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	10	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_other_guests_saturday_morning_282eb051	captain	I guess we can talk a bit about the other guests.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	25	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_other_guests_saturday_morning_3556fd65	captain	Who in particular?	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	25	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_other_guests_saturday_evening_4ba26398	captain	You are right, after all that happened we should discuss the others.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	38	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_other_guests_saturday_evening_eb0503f9	captain	Who do you have in mind?	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	38	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_drunk_friday_psychic_2fb3c156	captain	Ah yes, our intoxicated friend.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	51	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_drunk_friday_psychic_cfe183da	captain	There's not much to say that you haven't already noticed yourself.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	51	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_drunk_friday_psychic_ec4fb286		I guess he's right about that.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	57	"[what]"
captain_generic_drunk_saturday_psychic_f615cf7e	captain	I can't believe we gave him a gun.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	66	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_drunk_saturday_psychic_980a5286	captain	Anyone could have seen he was drunk more often than not.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	66	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_drunk_saturday_psychic_7ba2814e	captain	In hindsight, this tragedy ought to have been avoided.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	66	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_drunk_saturday_psychic_1931f669	psychic	What do you think will happen to him?	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	74	psychic "[what]"
captain_generic_drunk_saturday_psychic_917c7f5f	captain	I can't say for certain.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	78	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_drunk_saturday_psychic_b63da7ce	captain	He could be charged with manslaughter by negligence and face prison time.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	78	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_drunk_saturday_psychic_21c97111	captain	Or he might be acquitted, if the death is ruled an accident.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	78	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_drunk_saturday_psychic_b837e618	psychic	Really? He could just walk free after all this?	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	86	psychic "[what]"
captain_generic_drunk_saturday_psychic_5440ed1d	captain	That depends on how the situation is presented to the police—	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	90	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_drunk_saturday_psychic_0e1e4335	captain	and more importantly, on his connections.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	90	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_drunk_saturday_psychic_518c3bfa	captain	If he were a prominent aristocrat, I've no doubt he could sweep it all under the rug.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	90	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_drunk_saturday_psychic_0d0acb13	captain	But I don't believe that'll be the case for our friend.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	90	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_host_friday_psychic_07ac98be	captain	A charming lady, for sure.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	105	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_host_friday_psychic_61f2c9ce	captain	However, there's something about her that intrigues me.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	105	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_host_friday_psychic_b00bf9f0	psychic	Really?	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	111	psychic "[what]"
captain_generic_host_friday_psychic_ce3eff43	psychic	What exactly do you mean?	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	111	psychic "[what]"
captain_generic_host_friday_psychic_f5aed041		He seems unsure.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	117	"[what]"
captain_generic_host_friday_psychic_329b9b85		A bit embarrassed, even.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	117	"[what]"
captain_generic_host_friday_psychic_26ae3844	captain	I'm sorry, I meant nothing specific.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	123	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_host_friday_psychic_01b8232e	captain	I shouldn't be talking about our gracious host in any case.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	123	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_host_friday_psychic_e418ad92	psychic	Of course.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	129	psychic "[what]"
captain_generic_host_friday_psychic_ef6a3218		He knows more than he's willing to say.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	133	"[what]"
captain_generic_host_friday_psychic_b3b232f6		But he won't disclose it with other people around.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	133	"[what]"
captain_generic_nurse_friday_da85f8f6	captain	A discreet woman.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	144	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_nurse_friday_b9079b16	captain	She's stylishly dressed, but in a humble way.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	144	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_nurse_friday_0882252c	captain	You can immediately tell she's at ease in these kinds of gatherings.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	144	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_broken_friday_645bb014	captain	I'd say he's one of our war heroes.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	159	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_broken_friday_bd153272	captain	As a veteran of many battles, I have seen my fair share of horrors on the battlefield.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	163	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_broken_friday_e4dc038a	captain	One of the most devastating and haunting realities of war is the damage it can inflict on a person's face.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	163	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_broken_friday_043cc5cc	captain	The broken faces of Great War soldiers, disfigured and scarred by shrapnel, bullets, and gas, are a constant reminder of the terrible cost of conflict.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	163	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_broken_friday_b7dcab56	captain	Many of these soldiers are forced to wear masks to conceal their injuries, both physical and emotional.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	163	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_broken_friday_c5361d31	captain	These masks are not only a means of hiding their disfigurement but also a way of protecting themselves from the judgmental and curious gaze of others.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	163	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_broken_friday_8d4dfa0f	captain	I have met many of these brave men, and I have seen the pain and sadness in their eyes.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	163	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_broken_friday_9779a60e	captain	They have been through something unimaginable, and it is not something anyone should have to face.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	163	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_broken_friday_06ea0401	captain	Their sacrifice for their country is something truly admirable.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	163	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_broken_friday_d3dd9e61	captain	War is not just about the physical injuries, but also the emotional and psychological scars it leaves behind.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	163	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_broken_friday_27daf997	captain	The broken faces of these soldiers are a reminder of the human cost of war.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	163	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_broken_friday_52433f4f	captain	They are a reminder that behind every mask, there is a person with a story and a life that has been forever changed.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	163	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_broken_friday_7964d49a	captain	I hope that we can learn from the sacrifices of these soldiers and work towards a world where conflicts can be resolved without violence, and where the broken faces of war are a thing of the past.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	163	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_broken_friday_039449a0		Well, that was another tedious speech.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	193	"[what]"
captain_generic_broken_friday_5c979969		That's my fault for asking I suppose.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	193	"[what]"
captain_generic_broken_saturday_09d4edc2	captain	What can I say, other than the obvious?	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	204	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_broken_saturday_66587c39	captain	It's a shame he died like that.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	204	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_broken_saturday_122d937d	captain	Then again, perhaps he was in a great deal of pain from his injuries.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	204	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_broken_saturday_b974ee3f	captain	If so, he might have welcomed death as a release.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	204	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_broken_saturday_380f706b	psychic	You don't think there was anything odd about his death?	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	216	psychic "[what]"
captain_generic_broken_saturday_8e64a1bf	captain	Not really, no. If there had been, Doctor Baldwin would've said something.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	220	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_broken_saturday_22fcfb9c	captain	I believe Thomas Moody died a natural death.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	220	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_broken_saturday_dac19870	psychic	I suppose you're right.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	226	psychic "[what]"
captain_generic_lad_friday_psychic_af803cd8	captain	Mr Harring seems like a fine young fellow.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	235	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_lad_friday_psychic_007bc0cc	captain	But you've talked to him more than I have.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	235	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_lad_friday_psychic_2a112503	captain	You must have a more accurate opinion of him.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	235	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_lad_friday_psychic_26561d6f	psychic	That's true. Nevertheless, have you noticed anything specific about him?	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	243	psychic "[what]"
captain_generic_lad_friday_psychic_347b147f	captain	Well, I did notice that his clothes are a bit dated and worn.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	247	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_lad_friday_psychic_30363674	captain	Either he doesn't care about his appearance, or he can't afford more recent clothing.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	247	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_lad_friday_psychic_f92cf583	captain	I'll leave it to you to make your own judgment about that.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	247	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_doctor_friday_bdfbfb55	captain	At first glance, he seems like a decent gentleman.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	262	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_doctor_friday_47db1355	captain	However, he looked a bit nervous to me.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	262	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_doctor_friday_7ba935f9	captain	I noticed him fidgeting earlier, as if he were anxious about something.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	262	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_doctor_saturday_498d41b8	captain	I didn't know him very well but he seemed like a decent person.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	275	captain "[what]"
captain_generic_doctor_saturday_46ac34e1	captain	Such a pity he died like that.	game/scripts/captain/captain_generic_other_guests.rpy	275	captain "[what]"
captain_introduction_652079a7		The governess is speaking, but I cannot hear her words.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	26	"[what]"
captain_introduction_9394eff2		I am watching the garden below from the upstairs window.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	26	"[what]"
captain_introduction_478ba8b7		A group of white children are playing cricket outside, their laughter carrying up through the warm Calcutta air.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	26	"[what]"
captain_introduction_52ea3a13		I want to join them, but I know better than to ask.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	26	"[what]"
captain_introduction_24b3b112		Mother's hand rests on my shoulder.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	26	"[what]"
captain_introduction_e89cea85		"You are the son of a zamindar," she says softly. "Our family has held land in Bengal for generations."	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	26	"[what]"
captain_introduction_813d6a7c		"You will learn their manners. You will master every rule of their world."	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	26	"[what]"
captain_introduction_59401ac1		"And one day, they will have no choice but to respect you."	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	26	"[what]"
captain_introduction_0ed9686b		I nod, though I do not fully understand.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	26	"[what]"
captain_introduction_7d7eb761		I am seven years old.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	26	"[what]"
captain_introduction_064e3d9f		The governess resumes her lesson. Posture. The correct way to hold a teacup. How to address a gentleman. How to enter a room.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	26	"[what]"
captain_introduction_ec2c4e9e		I practise until my back aches and my mind grows heavy with rules I do not yet understand.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	26	"[what]"
captain_introduction_0c69073f		Outside, the cricket game ends. The boys run off laughing.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	26	"[what]"
captain_introduction_04baf0df		They don't sit through tedious lessons like I do.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	26	"[what]"
captain_introduction_67647282		And yet, one day, they will rule the world all the same.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	26	"[what]"
captain_introduction_8f649764		The governess clears her throat. I turn back to face her and continue with my lesson.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	26	"[what]"
captain_introduction_0f418841		Mother watches me, and I can see in her eyes that she believes every word she has told me.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	26	"[what]"
captain_introduction_033a1923		That if I am polished enough, refined enough, the doors of the Empire will open for me too.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	26	"[what]"
captain_introduction_f740a88e		"Again," she says.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	26	"[what]"
captain_introduction_d50aa27c		So I sit up straight, and I begin again.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	26	"[what]"
captain_introduction_a20cefa7		...	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	80	"[what]"
captain_introduction_ada950db		The train jolts, and the memory dissolves.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	80	"[what]"
captain_introduction_2cc7b95a		I blink.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	80	"[what]"
captain_introduction_f9b16235		My neck is stiff from sleeping against the window, and the English countryside rushes past in a grey-green blur.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	80	"[what]"
captain_introduction_9eb6d802		I straighten my collar and catch my reflection in the darkened glass.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	80	"[what]"
captain_introduction_38edff10		Distinguished enough, I suppose. But it was never going to make my mother's dream come true.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	80	"[what]"
captain_introduction_e9a4d633		The doors she promised me? They remain firmly shut.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	80	"[what]"
captain_introduction_f1013323		Twenty years in London, and I am still the Indian officer whom people greet with polite surprise, as though my perfect English were some sort of parlour trick.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	80	"[what]"
captain_introduction_c2d571ab		Invited to some receptions, yet never to the clubs that matter. Tolerated at dinners, yet never truly welcomed.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	80	"[what]"
captain_introduction_a616ebc5		I have done everything she asked of me. I mastered their language, learned their manners.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	80	"[what]"
captain_introduction_f1a52cc9		I served their Empire faithfully all my life.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	80	"[what]"
captain_introduction_b669ec26		And yet, I am still just an outsider looking through the window.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	80	"[what]"
captain_introduction_80f11db4		Good manners were not enough.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	80	"[what]"
captain_introduction_55c6c336		If I want a proper place in society, I will also need money.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	80	"[what]"
captain_introduction_751f32e9		That is the reason I am here.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	80	"[what]"
captain_introduction_4b0557ab		I reach into my breast pocket and unfold the letter once more.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	80	"[what]"
captain_introduction_730180d5	letter	"... as a thank you for all the lives you saved during the war, I would ..."	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	114	letter "[what]"
captain_introduction_4ba3c147		I don't know where Lady Claythorn got the idea of this "heroic action" of mine.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	118	"[what]"
captain_introduction_2bb95357		She most certainly mistook me for another Indian soldier.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	118	"[what]"
captain_introduction_0de7d2f6		God knows it wouldn't be the first time.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	118	"[what]"
captain_introduction_3b91bfdb		Yet, the invitation is vague enough that it could still apply to me.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	118	"[what]"
captain_introduction_b9ae30a3		I mean, I am sure I saved lives... technically.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	118	"[what]"
captain_introduction_f3e85256		Many soldiers died because they didn't receive their rations on time. Or because they lacked proper clothing.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	118	"[what]"
captain_introduction_6b6fc0dc		I made certain that didn't happen on my watch.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	118	"[what]"
captain_introduction_eba643b7		But I know that can't be what she meant.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	118	"[what]"
captain_introduction_97fed028		The honest thing would have been to write back and correct her mistake.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	118	"[what]"
captain_introduction_067c5709		But when has honesty ever helped me?	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	118	"[what]"
captain_introduction_f3a9b50d		The money promised by Lady Claythorn would go a long way. Enough to host a few proper dinners, join the right club, and be seen in the right company.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	118	"[what]"
captain_introduction_72f2eb97		That could finally be my way in.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	118	"[what]"
captain_introduction_b3a102f3		So yes, I am committing fraud. There is no other way to put it.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	118	"[what]"
captain_introduction_00f35b2b		But I have spent my whole life earning a place that was promised to me and never delivered.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	118	"[what]"
captain_introduction_53d31208		If they won't give it to me, I shall simply have to take it.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	118	"[what]"
captain_introduction_ea24f964		I fold the letter away and sit up straighter.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	118	"[what]"
captain_introduction_19e0e873		I will play the part of a battle-hardened officer.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	118	"[what]"
captain_introduction_48f14b42		How hard could that be?	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	118	"[what]"
captain_introduction_9af920dc		As soon as the train stops, I am on the platform.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	162	"[what]"
captain_introduction_08f6d42b		I scan the few people waiting and quickly notice there is only one servant.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	162	"[what]"
captain_introduction_eee87106		If Lady Claythorn is well-organised, he must be here for me.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	162	"[what]"
captain_introduction_23d70ac1		I reach him before he sees me.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	162	"[what]"
captain_introduction_c3d256c2	captain	Excuse me, young man.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	172	captain "[what]"
captain_introduction_0ec9d409	captain	Are you working for Lady Claythorn?	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	172	captain "[what]"
captain_introduction_baf3b4d7	footman	Indeed, I am. You must be ...	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	178	footman "[what]"
captain_introduction_1369c7c3	captain	Sushil Sinha. Retired captain.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	182	captain "[what]"
captain_introduction_590f21b1	footman	Of course, I've been expecting you, captain.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	186	footman "[what]"
captain_introduction_1ed61c37	footman	There are a few more people on this train who are also guests of Lady Claythorn...	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	186	footman "[what]"
captain_introduction_2c9ee748	captain	Of course, I'll wait for them.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	192	captain "[what]"
captain_introduction_06fd9111		After a while, an older lady named Amelia Baxter joins us.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	196	"[what]"
captain_introduction_9881e948		Then, an inebriated gentleman erupts from the train at the last minute.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	196	"[what]"
captain_introduction_9a5bd801		I am surprised that he is also a guest.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	196	"[what]"
captain_introduction_7416920e		When we reach the car, I quickly sit with Miss Baxter.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	196	"[what]"
captain_introduction_7c08660a		The drunk quickly falls asleep.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	208	"[what]"
captain_introduction_307b8c64		So, I have only the older lady to make conversation with.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	208	"[what]"
captain_introduction_dbb2afaa		She asks me a few questions. Some of them have a tinge of racism to them.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	208	"[what]"
captain_introduction_0f2c2157		Sadly, it's something I am too familiar with, so I say nothing.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	208	"[what]"
captain_introduction_13d2f10b		No matter how I feel, I have learned it's better to stay polite.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	208	"[what]"
captain_introduction_06cbab29		But to avoid another inappropriate question, I decide to monopolise the conversation while we stay in the car.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	208	"[what]"
captain_introduction_f885f821		Let's see how she likes being forced to listen to something she doesn't want to.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	208	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_downstairs_default_7f913766		Downstairs is reserved for the staff, so I should not go.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	63	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_downstairs_default_7c5a699d		If I were seen poking around there, it would invite exactly the sort of suspicion I am trying to avoid.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	63	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_tea_room_52d3086d		The tea room is deserted now. Nothing of interest here.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	79	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_dining_room_ab3a7ffa		The staff are clearing away the last of the dinner service.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	90	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_dining_room_3ccd503c		No reason to linger.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	90	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_garden_f5708c5f		I look through the window. The rain is coming down hard now.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	103	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_garden_2ba4df01		A storm is gathering. I can hear the wind picking up against the glass.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	103	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_garden_54edc329		Most people would turn back at this point.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	103	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_garden_9c7a161c		But I have marched through monsoons. A bit of rain is hardly cause for concern.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	103	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_garden_35f618c2		I step outside.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	115	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_garden_175b794a		The air is cold and the rain is heavier than it looked from indoors.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	115	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_garden_02d10168		Within moments, my jacket is soaked through.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	115	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_garden_7582b76b		I walk a short distance around the house.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	115	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_garden_ef78412d		Nothing remarkable in the dark.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	115	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_garden_e52c5983		A garden, a gravel path, and what appears to be an outbuilding further on.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	115	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_garden_7f7b1592		I am soaking wet and the cold is beginning to bite.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	134	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_garden_3e1ca425		In these conditions, there is no point in staying any longer.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	134	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_garden_aed633a4		I return inside and head straight to my room to change.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	142	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_garden_228d1239		A foolish exercise, perhaps, but at least I have a better understanding of the estate.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	142	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_shed_4e247da6		I press on through the rain, boots sinking into the sodden gravel.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	153	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_shed_95611c8a		The outbuilding proves to be a squat timber shed, half hidden behind an overgrown hedge.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	153	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_shed_f2642351		I try the handle.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	153	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_shed_69d6d78c		It does not give. The door is locked, and firmly so.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	153	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_shed_e319fb80		That is odd.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	153	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_shed_968fd686		A garden shed, out here in the middle of nowhere, bolted shut against what exactly?	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	153	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_shed_6f882129		Whoever fitted that lock had a reason, and it was not the threat of common thieves.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	153	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_entrance_hall_64a3651a		The entrance hall is quiet at this hour.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	178	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_entrance_hall_f7ae7422		It is a fine space. The kind of hall that speaks of generations.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	178	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_entrance_hall_e3c7ba41		I take a moment to study the architecture, then move on.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	178	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_attic_default_dc435c50		The servants' quarters are upstairs.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	199	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_attic_default_eec032e0		I have no business going there.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	199	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_attic_default_012167ff		A guest does not wander into the staff's private rooms. It would be a serious breach of propriety.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	199	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_attic_default_5703abda		Whatever is up there is none of my concern.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	199	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_bedroom_avoid_78b6aece		I pause outside the door.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	223	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_bedroom_avoid_b97f8f31		No. It would be improper to enter someone's room uninvited.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	223	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_bedroom_avoid_33b1d5a2		That is not how a gentleman conducts himself.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	223	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_bedroom_avoid_57aa5119		I consider it for a moment, then think better of it.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	233	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_bedroom_avoid_2022fa72		A man does not go rummaging through another person's private quarters.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	233	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_bedroom_avoid_61e1843c		I should keep the bedrooms out of my mind entirely.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	233	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_82e3eed5		We arrive at the manor.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	32	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_e2e630c1		It is an imposing house. Not the grandest I have seen, but respectable.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	32	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_ba12dd4f		The kind of place I should have been invited to years ago.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	32	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_9528a4ea		I straighten my jacket and step inside.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	32	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_ef7795eb		Manning is already demanding a drink. The man has no shame.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	44	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_508b82f8		But at least he draws attention away from me.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	44	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_21b39578		Miss Baxter excuses herself to freshen up in her room.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	52	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_98af6622		Good. I have had quite enough of her questions for now.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	52	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_82e52a7a		The tea room it is.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	52	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_25a004c6		As soon as we enter, Samuel Manning rushes to the tray of drinks.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	64	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_a224bbb0		There is a woman there already. And Samuel Manning seems to be trying to engage in conversation with her.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	64	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_af6eb781		I could go and rescue her, but I do not really feel like dealing with that right now.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	64	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_46cd353e		I also spot two men in quiet conversation.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	64	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_c92666c8		That seems like a better alternative.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	64	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_c792052a		Time to introduce myself.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	64	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_cfda4738		That part, at least, is true.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	80	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_d61d6439		I carry on from there. A story about a drunkard officer in Calcutta.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	80	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_f664cca5		Then another about the supply lines in Burma.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	80	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_ced8bc7e		And another.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	80	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_f7955aab		I can tell the doctor has stopped listening after a while, but Mr Moody seems genuinely interested.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	80	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_f213be85		Then, the woman approaches our group.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	80	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_cce5e35b		That particular scar is from falling off a chair in my office in Calcutta.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	96	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_f63b5b5c		But they do not need to know that.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	96	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_04da7633		I carry on. Miss Marsh listens attentively.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	104	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_33040248		The doctor, on the other hand, has drifted off entirely. He nods, but his mind is elsewhere.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	104	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_2621bc9b		Two more guests slip into the room. The butler announces the young man.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	104	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_2ce34aae	butler	Mr Ted Harring!	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	112	butler "[what]"
captain_day1_evening_ef161dfa		He looks out of place. Young, nervous, dressed in clothes that have seen better days.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	116	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_29c78f82		I pay him little mind and continue my story.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	116	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_d93f1254		I am in the middle of a rather good tale when the gong interrupts me.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	124	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_01c0ffb1		A pity. I was just getting to the best part.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	130	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_b3a39ff6		We file into the dining room. Each place is marked with a name card.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	142	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_fdec073a		I find mine near the head of the table. A good position.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	142	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_1c50015c		Miss Baxter is on my right. Mr Moody sits across from me, but far too distant for conversation.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	142	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_ddae126e		Then, our host makes her entrance.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	142	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_cdd6e74e		She is rather young, elegantly dressed, with the quiet confidence of old money.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	142	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_3fef2423		She takes her seat at the head of the table.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	142	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_99762544		After the speech, I cannot help but notice a tightness in my stomach.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	158	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_92143309		It reminds me that I am an impostor here, not worthy of any award.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	158	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_02f92cbb		If I am discovered, not only will I lose the money, but there will certainly be talk about what I have done.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	158	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_1da58c68		That could hurt my reputation.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	158	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_6683685d		So I should watch what I am saying carefully.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	158	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_f4bb1017		As we begin to eat, I notice Miss Baxter turning to her right.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	158	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_76aac738		She has struck up a conversation with Mr Harring.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	158	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_502a5ee3		That is unusual. In a formal setting, one addresses the person on one's left first.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	158	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_390f89e9		So she ought to have spoken to me.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	158	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_13e6ec8a		Either she is unaware of the convention, or she is deliberately avoiding me.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	158	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_c7253aef		It could be the latter. But as I examine the other guests, small lapses begin to reveal themselves.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	158	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_e18262af		Mr Manning holds his wine glass by the bowl, not the stem.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	158	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_c837d887		Mr Harring hesitates over his cutlery, glancing at his neighbour before choosing a fork.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	158	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_4a321bef		Dr Baldwin has not touched his napkin at all. It lies folded beside his plate, forgotten.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	158	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_9a13ab3c		Small things. The sort a man like me has trained himself to notice in others.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	158	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_f7ef2c2f		None of them are accustomed to proper company. That much is plain enough.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	158	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_0f40e94e		Then my gaze drifts to the head of the table, and I pause.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	158	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_b29c1859		Lady Claythorn reaches for her bread roll and picks up the butter knife.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	158	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_a143e4f7		She cuts the roll in half and butters it whole.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	158	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_9de0e9b7		A small thing. Invisible to most at this table.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	158	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_9dc3ccba		But one does not butter an entire roll. One breaks off a single piece and attends to that alone.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	158	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_f398c6cb		I have been told that so many times I cannot fail to notice it.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	158	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_50916b0c		Of all the people at this table, I did not expect that from her.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	158	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_cf9ceac2		Then again, this alone probably means nothing.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	158	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_4e8af069		With a manor this remote, perhaps she has simply not had occasion for proper company in some time, so she has forfeited some of the usual habits.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	158	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_42c6ddeb		After a while Miss Baxter seems to have exhausted her conversation with the young man.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	212	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_92bc3f20		I can talk to her now if I please.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	212	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_588d2deb		The dinner reaches its conclusion.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	228	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_fc1ccf31		Lady Claythorn mentions that drinks will be available in the billiard room for those who wish to continue the evening.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	228	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_cd838605		First, I should like to see my room. I have not yet had the chance to settle in.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	228	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_bfceec02		I ask the footman to show me the way.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	228	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_44268753	footman	Here you are, Captain.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	240	footman "[what]"
captain_day1_evening_e3a0f09d	footman	You've been assigned the 'George I' room.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	240	footman "[what]"
captain_day1_evening_91e16256		The room is adequate. Not extravagant, but respectable.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	250	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_76a5861c		Still, it is more comfortable than my lodgings in London.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	250	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_1a2121bd		I unpack quickly and consider my options.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	250	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_8397163c		The hour is late and the house has grown quiet.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	270	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_b33f8aba		I return to my room.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	270	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_1f02c78d		I change and prepare for bed while I review the evening in my head.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	278	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_05845251		I have done well. Nobody suspects a thing.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	278	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_7aa47e68		My stories have held their attention, and I have avoided any question that might have caught me out.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	278	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_0b7f1cf6		If I can keep doing this, I might be able to get out of here with the reward without anyone the wiser.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	278	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_ab96c1da		I turn back the covers and find a folded sheet of paper resting on the pillow.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	278	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_5c225116		Plain. Unmarked.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	278	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_2a398dc6		I pick it up and unfold it.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	278	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_488a50d9	letter	You are a fraud.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	296	letter "[what]"
captain_day1_evening_96126837		My hand stills.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	300	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_bbb9c76a		For a moment, I am frozen, unable to react.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	300	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_95a4a831		I gather all my strength not to panic.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	300	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_cd4227a2		I breathe. I think.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	300	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_80486163		I set the paper down.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	300	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_d171c94e		Someone in this house knows. Someone has been in this very room tonight and placed this where I could not miss it.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	300	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_3440caa5		But why?	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	300	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_c52b719a		Is it a threat? A warning?	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	300	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_652c099c		And from whom?	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	300	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_40bef757		From the Mistress of this place? Then this whole weekend could be designed just to torture me?	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	300	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_cad12705		But I cannot see a reason why — I have no enemies, not real ones at least.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	300	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_53f30487		It could also come from a guest.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	300	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_bab4066e		Someone who knows me, and realised I do not belong here.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	300	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_d2efbd20		But then, why not say it in front of everybody?	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	300	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_a2608fed		To torture me?	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	300	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_03b62571		I sit on the edge of the bed. I go through every face at dinner, trying to remember someone.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	300	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_4be4c4d1		I find nothing.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	300	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_4e1222e2		Unless, of course, the culprit is the person behind the mask.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	300	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_b700238d		The other military man in the house.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	300	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_c1c16de8		Thomas Moody is the most likely to have recognised me, realised I am not who I claim to be, and decided to make me pay for it.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	300	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_d15ee768		Still, he did not show it at all tonight.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	300	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_96088c22		I stay still for a while, trying to make sense of this, but cannot.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	300	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_49ba6d0f		And the letter is not the only thing weighing on my mind.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	348	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_d236f1bf		Lady Claythorn, from what I have learnt tonight, could be an impostor too.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	348	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_ab1aa397		No more the mistress of this manor than I am a decorated war hero.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	348	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_fb079b09		Perhaps we all are.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	348	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_66f6df90		Perhaps this whole weekend is some elaborate piece of theatre, and each of us has been handed a part to play.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	348	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_ef8a509c		The question now is what to do.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	362	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_c46270de		I could flee. Leave this place and everyone behind.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	362	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_7ba8ba32		But then I would give up the money.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	362	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_79290f13		The letter's goal could be to make me do just that.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	362	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_3f7f0118		But I cannot. I will not.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	362	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_e18be522		I have come too far, put too much hope in this journey to give up now.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	362	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_5eef86e5		Whatever is at play here, I will stay at least until tomorrow, and decide accordingly.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	362	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_b5aaa251		I lie back, but sleep does not come easily.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	362	"[what]"
captain_day1_dinner_no_talk_600b9627		I decide that the best way not to be discovered is to simply keep to myself.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	390	"[what]"
captain_day1_dinner_no_talk_05a73447		So I do not engage with Miss Baxter.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	390	"[what]"
captain_day1_dinner_no_talk_f9ae5819		She does not seem to mind.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	390	"[what]"
captain_day1_dinner_no_talk_8e41f1c8		We eat in silence until the end of dinner.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	390	"[what]"
captain_day1_dinner_psychic_131a147b	captain	Miss Baxter.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	405	captain "[what]"
captain_day1_dinner_psychic_87833a53		She gives me an annoyed look. I do not think she was expecting to be put back in her place by someone like me.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	411	"[what]"
captain_day1_dinner_psychic_50560466		That gives me a small feeling of satisfaction.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	411	"[what]"
captain_day1_dinner_psychic_265cb0c1		She then proceeds to ask me questions about myself, and I make sure each answer is filled with inconsequential details.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	411	"[what]"
captain_day1_dinner_psychic_2ec61ee0		Hopefully, if I drown her in information, she might not notice any inconsistencies.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	411	"[what]"
captain_day1_dinner_psychic_ba72f57a		When the dinner reaches its conclusion, I realise I have not even asked her anything about herself.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	411	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_16ff7575		The billiard room is warm and well lit.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	10	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_7db8918c		Most of the guests have gathered here.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	10	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_473c90d3		Lady Claythorn is in conversation with Miss Marsh and Thomas Moody.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	10	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_98bb5aa9		Ted Harring hovers near them, looking as uncomfortable as ever.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	10	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_d8bfbc2c		Daniel Baldwin sits alone in a chair, nursing a glass.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	10	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_cea240ae		And Manning is at the bar. Naturally.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	10	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_16f859fd		As I enter, a few heads turn my way.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	10	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_9a725cae		I recognise that look. They are bored and waiting for any kind of distraction.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	10	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_619510f0		I am back in the billiard room.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	39	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_story_bf32738f		I make my way towards Lady Claythorn and the others.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	50	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_story_070b23f5	host	Captain Sinha. Do come and join us.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	54	host "[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_story_ba8936f8	captain	Thank you, Lady Claythorn.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	58	captain "[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_story_6ccf8f7a	nurse	Captain, you must tell us one of your stories.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	62	nurse "[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_story_6fc463f8	nurse	Mr Moody was just saying what a fine storyteller you are.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	62	nurse "[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_story_71785185		My old standby rises to the tip of my tongue. The Boxer Rebellion.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	68	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_story_9051b37c		I have told that tale a hundred times. It almost feels like a memory of my own.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	68	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_story_a15ea4e0		Yet, a single misplaced detail in front of the wrong listener could unravel the whole pretence.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	68	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_story_935d36b4		On the other hand, refusing outright might invite suspicion.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	68	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_story_tell_3e3d08aa	captain	How kind of him.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	88	captain "[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_story_tell_748f69b3	captain	Well, if you insist.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	88	captain "[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_story_tell_24a962c3		I take a position near the fireplace and begin.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	94	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_story_tell_07067132		This is my best story.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	94	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_story_tell_ac4ad648		I have told it so many times that it almost feels true.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	94	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_story_tell_356e2d72		I speak of the Boxer Rebellion. The Eight-Nation Alliance. The march on Beijing.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	94	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_story_tell_82892b9b		I give them the full account.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	94	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_story_tell_a294cb4f		Everyone is listening. Even the doctor has looked up from his glass.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	94	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_story_tell_c5fa6fdf		Good.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	94	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_story_tell_79abe8a0		The truth is, during the Boxer Rebellion, I was a supply officer stationed behind the lines.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	94	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_story_tell_cc666f34		I never saw a single Boxer. I never fired a single shot.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	94	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_story_tell_0a0f0aac		But I have read enough accounts of the expedition to describe it as though I were there.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	94	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_story_tell_6ca8e1b1		And over the years, the story has become so polished that even I sometimes forget the reality.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	94	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_story_tell_0389a5ad		I finish the story and pause, letting the silence settle.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	94	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_story_tell_d8a78671		Miss Marsh is studying me. There is something in her expression that I do not quite like.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	94	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_story_tell_d8ddf8ad		But the rest of the room seems satisfied.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	94	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_story_tell_92274aac		Mr Moody nods approvingly. Lady Claythorn offers a polite smile.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	94	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_story_tell_ae261ae1		It is a good story. That is what matters.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	94	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_story_refuse_cb2ad7f1	captain	You are most kind, Miss Marsh. But I fear I must disappoint you this evening.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	135	captain "[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_story_refuse_cd50d7e7	captain	The journey has left me no strength for a performance.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	135	captain "[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_story_refuse_4e6bcd3d	captain	Perhaps another time.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	135	captain "[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_story_refuse_979a23de		The silence that follows is a fraction too long.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	143	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_story_refuse_50160db1		Lady Claythorn's smile thins. Mr Moody's face slips into open disappointment.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	143	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_story_refuse_46c2d525		My refusal has made everyone uneasy.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	143	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_story_refuse_0c692ec9		A man invited for his military exploits who refuses to tell a war story is a man with something to conceal.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	143	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_story_refuse_5ec17e99		Maybe I made a mistake.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	143	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_story_refuse_f6f6a984		I should take myself out of sight before I make it any worse.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	143	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_story_refuse_c484bcc5	captain	Forgive me. I believe I shall retire to my room now.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	157	captain "[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_story_refuse_bc72a4f2		I incline my head politely and withdraw from the group, conscious that everyone in the room is following me to the door.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	161	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_bar_cac844ce		I make my way to the bar.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	173	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_bar_fd76a342		Manning is there, slumped against the counter.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	173	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_bar_97e72697		I pour myself a small measure of port and stand apart from him.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	173	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_bar_b0cdeb11		There is nothing to be gained from associating with a drunkard.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	173	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_baldwin_a6b680a9		I approach Baldwin.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	188	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_baldwin_c391d0db		He looks up. His eyes are flat.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	188	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_baldwin_4da50fcd	doctor	Captain Sinha, how are you?	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	194	doctor "[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_baldwin_7a335cfa	captain	I am fine, Doctor.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	198	captain "[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_baldwin_2530b518	captain	What about you?	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	198	captain "[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_baldwin_6679cccb	doctor	A little tired if I am being honest.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	204	doctor "[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_baldwin_c7ecd8b5	doctor	The journey has exhausted me.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	204	doctor "[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_baldwin_4809f655		Yes, the journey was long. But I can tell that is not entirely what is causing Dr Baldwin's tiredness.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	210	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_baldwin_7f51fd50		But no need to say anything.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	210	"[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_baldwin_cfde2ba3	captain	Very well, I'll leave you alone then.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	216	captain "[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_baldwin_448a9ff8	captain	Have a good night.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	216	captain "[what]"
captain_day1_evening_billiard_room_baldwin_0333874b	doctor	You too.	game/scripts/captain/Day 1/2_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	222	doctor "[what]"
captain_day2_morning_c23646a6		I wake before the sun has fully cleared the horizon.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	31	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_acc024c6		The room is silent, its heavy curtains muffling the morning bird-song.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	31	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_a7272f2c		I lie still for a moment, listening to the house.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	31	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_6983c569		Day two.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	31	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_7f0d3f4d		The letter still lies on the bedside table where I left it last night.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	31	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_8b2d827f		Four words, unsigned.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	31	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_923124f0		I turned them over a hundred times before sleep finally found me, and I am no nearer an answer this morning than I was then.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	31	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_bb02169d		Someone beneath this roof knows I am not the hero I claim to be.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	31	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_3fa11666		And the letter is not the only matter that weighs upon me.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	51	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_2a160ea0		Nor is our gracious hostess quite who she pretends to be.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	51	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_1dced8de		That adds a layer of risk to everything.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	51	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_d50d0af9		Whatever is at play here, I must be extremely careful.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	59	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_ea7c95b8		I rise and begin my preparations.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	59	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_479c76c8		Washing is a brief, cold affair. Dressing is done with practised efficiency.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	59	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_5f875178		Every button fastened. Every crease straightened.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	59	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_8130409a		The mirror shows a man who belongs here. That is all that matters.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	59	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_b3401b63		Now, it is time for breakfast.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	59	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_b975a713		I enter the dining room.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	77	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_b092756c		The table is set, and the smell of coffee and fried bread fills the air.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	77	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_b0c4f951		I am the first guest to arrive. That suits me.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	77	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_ef12fe41		I help myself to a modest plate at the buffet and take the same seat I occupied last night.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	77	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_a475cd96		A few minutes alone, before the others descend, are always welcome.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	77	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_6e9108a3		Doctor Baldwin is the first to join me.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	91	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_60747219		He offers a silent nod from across the room, which I return in kind.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	91	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_cb988dd1		He helps himself to a plate and eats without a word.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	91	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_aa6abd1c		A sensible man. He has already understood that the morning is not for chatter.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	91	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_0f3a423b		My mind, however, is not entirely on my breakfast.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	91	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_d0745d42		What I uncovered last night still sits uncomfortably at the back of my thoughts.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	91	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_c05c3740		I shall have to be extremely careful today, especially around Thomas Moody.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	91	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_a484be9e		Miss Baxter is next to appear.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	109	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_2713de7e		She drifts in and helps herself to a small serving.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	109	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_7db3f916		She takes her seat next to mine and, to my quiet relief, seems in no more hurry to speak than I am.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	109	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_75956373		Miss Marsh follows a moment later. A nod, a word of greeting, and she settles at the far side of the table with her tea.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	109	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_7abf1d98		Lastly, Mr Harring slips in with an air of not quite belonging, and seats himself near Miss Baxter.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	109	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_8cf85651		I have no interest in following their exchange, so I keep eating in silence.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	109	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_96befd4f		While I am eating, Samuel Manning makes his entrance.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	109	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_6250922a		Or rather, he stumbles through it.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	109	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_c1c2902e		His complexion is ashen, his cravat askew, and his hands shake so badly that he drops a spoon twice before finally securing a cup of black coffee.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	109	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_d44d1546		He has clearly not recovered from yesterday.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	109	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_55ca3681		He drops into the nearest seat without a word to anyone.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	109	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_01813448		Miss Baxter's expression hardens at the sight of him, though she says nothing.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	109	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_647484e9		So I readily accept the invitation to join in this afternoon exercise.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	143	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_79aba749		All the other men accept as well, but the ladies will remain behind.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	143	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_death_2be5c0b1		While I am observing Mr Manning, the butler slips into the room and bends to Lady Claythorn's ear.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	158	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_death_4573b88e		Whatever he tells her, it takes all of her breeding to receive it without crying out.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	158	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_death_e0eff390		She rises at once, crosses the room, and stops beside Doctor Baldwin.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	158	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_death_f67481e8		The three of them leave together.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	168	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_death_72d0e172		To my surprise, Mr Harring also stands and follows them out, with no apparent reason.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	168	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_death_e1129315		The room settles into silence.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	168	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_death_253c12c8		Nobody speaks, though every face bears the same unspoken question.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	168	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_death_0ba10a72		After a moment, Miss Baxter realises she can't ignore me forever.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	168	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_death_eee7755c		She then proceeds to ask me various questions.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	182	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_death_be1e1b39		I try to fill the time with the most detailed stories I can. I do not reciprocate her questions.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	182	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_death_1a28a03b		Mr Moody. Dead in his bed.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	194	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_death_7050bb53		The doctor speaks of old war wounds and natural failure, and it is plausible enough.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	194	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_death_1a1ccade		Yet something in me refuses to accept it quite so readily.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	194	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_death_e850ccd9		The letter comes back to me at once.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	194	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_death_ef4b56d2		Someone under this roof sent it. And now, barely twelve hours later, a man is dead.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	194	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_death_e8818820		That is not a coincidence I am prepared to dismiss.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	194	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_death_ab29ee52		The hostess is not what she presents herself to be, either.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	210	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_death_d15b5ae2		A letter, a false identity, a dead man. Three things beneath the same roof.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	210	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_death_fb767968		Doubt creeps into my mind. Maybe I should not have stayed.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	210	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_death_8459a42d		But I feel I am in too deep to turn back now.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	210	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_death_36eca08d		Our hostess is remarkably composed.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	224	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_death_ce9bd157		A death beneath one's roof is no small matter, and yet she carries on as though nothing more serious had occurred than a postponed tea.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	224	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_death_f8204509		That, in itself, is worth noting.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	224	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_death_084acc7a		For my part, I am in no position to refuse her.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	224	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_death_0f871821		A man invited for his military record would look strange indeed if he shrank from a morning's shooting.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	224	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_alive_1929557d		Mr Moody appears a moment later.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	245	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_alive_f222a84c		He pauses at the threshold and surveys the room before heading to the buffet.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	252	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_alive_c23c2dd8		There, he helps himself to a light plate.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	252	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_alive_bea38004		He then takes the seat in front of me and starts engaging with our hostess.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	252	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_alive_245359c2		I look at him for a few seconds.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	252	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_alive_bb1af29c		His presence makes me uneasy.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	252	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_alive_2e2064a4		Even if I have no proof, I still suspect he is responsible for the letter.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	252	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_alive_d67cbe8a		Before he can notice my staring, I turn my head to the side.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	252	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_alive_e718011a		Miss Baxter is still talking with Ted Harring, which leaves me with no one to talk to.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	252	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_alive_e1445468		That suits me well enough.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	252	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_alive_2c95c618		As the plates are gradually cleared, Lady Claythorn rises and addresses the table.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	276	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_alive_2a983198	host	Well, if everyone has finished, I should like to remind you that activities were planned for today.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	282	host "[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_alive_d1755c77	host	This morning, those who wish to are to join a hunt.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	282	host "[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_alive_1467018b	host	Our staff will lend you everything you need, clothes, guns, and their assistance throughout the event.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	282	host "[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_alive_cbd9f236	host	Of course, if you would rather remain indoors by the fire, that is perfectly welcome too.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	282	host "[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_alive_d70a5fe5		A hunt. Yes, I remember it being mentioned.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	292	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_alive_07262b79		I can scarcely refuse without drawing attention to myself.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	292	"[what]"
captain_day2_morning_breakfast_alive_f441a33e		And a morning in the open air will do me good.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	292	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_1d0a0b89		I retire briefly to my room to change.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	33	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_533f73c2		The household has laid out a tweed jacket of about my size.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	33	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_fcd0d637		I have brought my own but don't want to offend our hostess, so I put this one on.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	33	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_9510004f		Properly turned out, I make my way down to the gun room.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	33	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_b3ce4e84		The butler is already there, attending to the rifles with unhurried care.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	45	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_3c7b987b		He hands me a piece, well-kept and finely balanced.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	45	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_f6d41d98		I weigh it briefly, then sight along the barrel and find it true.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	45	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_de65e719		It has been some years since I last shouldered such a weapon, yet the hands do not forget.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	45	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_91862a46		I have a passable hand at shooting. Not, perhaps, what my hosts expect of a decorated officer, but sufficient to avoid embarrassment.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	45	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_748138f2		I step out into the garden, where the others are already gathering.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	59	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_45f37f75		Doctor Baldwin is checking the action of his rifle quietly.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	59	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_be79ab30		Samuel Manning stands a little apart, a flask in one hand and a gun in the other. A poor pairing.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	59	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_53974db8		Mr Harring hovers at the edge of the group, plainly ill at ease. A footman attends him closely, as well he should.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	59	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_e7a85262		Lady Claythorn is the last to emerge, dressed all in tweed.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	59	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_b6a594c0		At least, her outfit is perfect. But we will see if she can act the part.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	73	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_b8b85f7d		Next to her, stands Thomas Moody.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	79	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_269cbc48		He catches my eye and offers a small nod.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	79	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_c17851ef		I return it. Steady. No hesitation.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	79	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_850415b8		Whatever he knows, or believes he knows, I will not give him the satisfaction of a flinch.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	79	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_7f384e4e		But I feel uneasy nevertheless.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	79	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_ba67861c	captain	If I may, my lady. I should consider it a privilege to accompany you.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	93	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_a503eeb0	host	How gallant of you, Captain. The privilege, I assure you, is mine.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	97	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_3c409755	drunk	Doctor, I would be honoured to partner with you.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	101	drunk "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_43b993aa	drunk	You don't mind, do you?	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	101	drunk "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_f6dbf6b9		Doctor Baldwin's mouth opens, then closes again. It is plain he does mind, but cannot find the words to refuse.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	107	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_49ca4043	doctor	Well... no, of course not.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	111	doctor "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_a82b1491		Mr Harring hovers at the edge of the gathering, plainly uncertain where he belongs.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	115	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_ad8c4cfc		He settles, in the end, with Mr Manning and Baldwin.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	115	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_5e9e2a6c		The butler, who has been listening with the unobtrusive attention of his trade, steps forward.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	15	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_55d3cde2	butler	If I may, my lady.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	19	butler "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_5fd41011	butler	Doctor Baldwin and Mr Manning to the western grove, with Mr Harring.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	19	butler "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_02ce991e	butler	The footman will go along with them.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	19	butler "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_6ea37a67	butler	My lady and Captain Sinha to the north field, and I shall attend.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	19	butler "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_06ab7b50		Good, a morning in our hostess's company is definitely the better outcome for me.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	29	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_5a22f3da		Whatever she conceals, a few hours alone may loosen her tongue.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	35	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_6762a944		We walk for some time through the undergrowth before coming across anything worth a shot.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	43	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_b5e649b3		Lady Claythorn carries her piece as though it were a parasol that had grown unaccountably heavy.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	43	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_5f27a66a		Twice the barrel has dipped toward the earth. Once she has shifted her grip in plain sight, as if she could not recall where her hands belonged.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	43	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_9fce5739		A pheasant breaks cover. She brings the rifle up late, the stock set too high against her shoulder.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	52	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_bd1acdfb		The shot goes wide by a great margin. The recoil jolts her visibly, and she winces before she thinks to hide it.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	61	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_c4d1262a		She laughs it off with a small, embarrassed shake of the head.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	61	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_d62a558f	host	The light is most unhelpful today.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	67	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_9965f883		The light is perfectly fine.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	71	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_af48fb5f		She has scarcely handled a rifle in her life. That much is plain.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	71	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_6c2b5984		A gentlewoman who has organised a hunting weekend on her own grounds ought to know one end of her gun from the other.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	71	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_9ec0add9		A rabbit bolts from the fern.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	82	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_3c1b9590		I raise, aim, and fire.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	82	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_acdf1a89		A clean miss, though not by much.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	92	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_73e5b6c5		I lower the rifle and allow myself a small, private smile.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	92	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_1f8906d4	host	Captain, that was a nice attempt.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	98	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_eedf6c05	host	I am sure you will have better luck next time.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	98	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_c5d55d9b	captain	You are too kind, my lady.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	104	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_87a7eae6	captain	I suppose you were right about the light.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	104	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_db08faa2		Well, if I must keep my cover, I might as well go along with her lies.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	110	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_d98fe4dd		Nothing else comes our way, and soon it is time to stop for luncheon.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	116	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_42b92033		The butler lays out a modest spread on a linen cloth, pours tea, then steps back with a brief bow.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	122	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_c3bb61a8	butler	If you don't mind, my lady. I should like to look in upon the other party, that they might not want for anything.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	126	butler "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_b578d1f3	butler	I shall be back soon.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	126	butler "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_7893e35f	host	Very well. Thank you.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	132	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_fa44a3ff		Finally, we are alone.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	138	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_35700a95		The moment I was hoping for.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	138	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_bebbaec8		A rifle across my knees. The butler away.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	138	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_4ef7b6b6		It may not come again.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	138	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_5382c02a		I feel like I have seen enough to know "Lady Claythorn" is not who she appears to be.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	138	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_90a6eead		And yet, I will have to suppress everything in my education if I want to tell her that.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	138	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_3c2d043c		It does not help that she has a loaded weapon beside her.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	138	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_dd54f275		Confronting her now might not be the wisest course of action.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	138	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_4f83d998		A moment alone with her.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	166	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_02aec988		I could use it to press her on the unusual things I noticed.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	166	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_be3b2147		But everything in me prevents me from doing so.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	166	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_872ac510		My suspicions are clearly not strong enough to make me risk angering our hostess.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	166	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_c2c14328		It would be improper, but that is not the only reason.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	166	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_0cf71531		I may not like it, but I am also afraid of losing the money that was promised to me.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	166	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_dead_688e4f2c		No, I need more evidence if I want to risk it all by confronting her.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	166	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_silent_luncheon_dfc55fed		I hold my peace.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	193	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_silent_luncheon_6fad2c41		We finish the luncheon with the sort of polite small talk that reveals nothing and obliges nothing.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	193	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_silent_luncheon_e7bab6ef		In due course the butler returns, composed as ever, and we resume the hunt.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	201	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_silent_luncheon_69120d57		Two shots, close together, from the direction of the western grove.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	211	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_silent_luncheon_c7095fc0		Lady Claythorn lifts her head.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	211	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_silent_luncheon_5ed2f5b7	host	It seems the others have seen something.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	217	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_silent_luncheon_26a6ad65		Then, a moment later, a different sound.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	221	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_silent_luncheon_a60a112e		A cry. Thin and urgent, carried between the trees.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	221	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_silent_luncheon_c1c30f60	host	Captain. With me, please.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	229	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_silent_luncheon_90f87e91		When we reach the others, Doctor Baldwin lies on his back in the fern.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	235	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_silent_luncheon_4fab64b0		His shirt has been torn open and pressed dark with blood. His bag is open at his side, a pair of emptied vials loose in the moss.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	235	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_silent_luncheon_19c7e6cc		Mr Harring kneels beside him, white as paper, a useless hand resting on the ruined shirt.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	235	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_silent_luncheon_84081072		Samuel Manning stands a few paces off, his rifle at his feet, his whole frame trembling.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	235	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_silent_luncheon_55f25e36		The footman hovers uncertainly, having clearly not known where to place himself.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	235	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_silent_luncheon_8294ddd5	drunk	A rabbit. It was a rabbit.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	247	drunk "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_silent_luncheon_7190e819	drunk	I never saw him. I swear it on my life, I never saw him.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	247	drunk "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_silent_luncheon_ecaae2fe	footman	Mr Manning fired at something in the undergrowth, my lady.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	253	footman "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_silent_luncheon_6dbb9fad	footman	The doctor was ahead of him, and the bracken was thick between them.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	253	footman "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_silent_luncheon_b378d621	footman	The bullet took him in the side.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	253	footman "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_silent_luncheon_ca9be3f9		The doctor's face has already settled into the stillness of the dead.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	261	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_silent_luncheon_8f6c391c		A liver shot, from the placement of the blood. Quick enough, though not quickly enough for comfort.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	261	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_silent_luncheon_32b2217b	butler	A dreadful business, my lady.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	267	butler "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_silent_luncheon_381a1682	butler	If you will permit me, we ought to return to the house and send for the proper authorities.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	267	butler "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_silent_luncheon_c6453230	host	Yes. Yes, of course.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	273	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_silent_luncheon_5bf60520	host	Poor Doctor Baldwin. What a terrible, terrible accident.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	273	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_silent_luncheon_993884b6		Two men dead in the same day.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	281	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_silent_luncheon_6275754f		And our hostess receives the second with the same well-rehearsed composure as the first.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	281	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_silent_luncheon_72cbda12		I shall have a great deal to think about tonight.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	281	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_e3bd13f4		I set down my cup with deliberate care and allow the rifle to rest within easier reach.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	304	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_81e7f840	captain	Lady Claythorn. Forgive the indelicacy.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	308	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_efe50204	captain	There is a matter I should like to put to you plainly.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	308	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_8143d107	host	Goodness, Captain, how grave you sound.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	314	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_b9c96639	host	Whatever can be the matter?	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	314	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_4bdae6c8	captain	I noticed a lot of things that do not make sense this weekend:	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	320	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_e308858f	captain	Your portrait is nowhere in the gallery.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	320	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_88e56a06	captain	You either do not know, or do not follow, proper dining etiquette.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	320	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_d9e86931	captain	The hunt you yourself arranged appears to be quite beyond your skill.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	320	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_e987ae82	captain	And, worst of all, the surname you are using is not your title, as it should be.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	320	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_78d517e5	captain	I do not believe you are Lady Claythorn.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	320	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_ec9dada7	captain	In fact, I do not think there is a "Lady Claythorn."	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	320	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_27c15962		Her smile holds.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	336	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_498e6543		Firmly, as a practised hostess will hold a smile through a guest's poor taste.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	336	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_ab61b1b1	host	Captain, I confess myself astonished.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	342	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_c534aebd	host	The morning sun has plainly done your head a mischief.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	342	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_05101cbd	host	You are clearly confusing yourself with some detective from a poorly written novel.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	342	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_1a218008	host	There is a perfectly good explanation for everything you have mentioned.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	342	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_fbf9a198	captain	Well, in that case, please enlighten me.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	352	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_844d3be7	host	Shall we take them in turn, Captain?	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	356	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_a71b17bd	host	As for my portrait, I have never cared to sit for one.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	356	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_af387d8e	host	Its absence in the gallery is my own doing, nothing more sinister than vanity in reverse.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	356	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_499c4c76	host	For my manners at table, I live here for the most part alone.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	356	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_80e49a64	host	When one dines without company for months on end, the old conventions grow dusty.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	356	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_81589660	host	And for the hunt, I arranged it for the pleasure of my guests, not my own.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	356	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_fd913c81	host	I take up a rifle perhaps once a year.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	356	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_e582f6c9	host	The light was unkind to me this morning, but I confess that even in fair weather I should be no credit to my name.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	356	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_073e7485	host	Now, for the name itself, my late husband had grown weary of ceremony, as so many did after the war.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	356	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_82ed6f75	host	He preferred that we be addressed by the house rather than the peerage.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	356	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_7147d1da	host	A small indulgence, perhaps. Hardly a conspiracy.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	356	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_29e5a3b3		Each answer, taken on its own, is perfectly plausible.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	380	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_aea00780		Worse than that. Each echoes the very explanations I myself had turned over in my mind when I first noticed these things.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	380	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_2af87235		But the answers come too readily, as if rehearsed.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	380	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_1a734db1		An honest woman would stumble. Take offence. Demand to know what on earth I meant by it all.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	380	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_6df6d62b		Instead, she has submitted to my interrogation as if she were prepared for it.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	380	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_9c449ccc		But let's see how well she is really prepared.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	380	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_4df8d729	captain	That is a very logical explanation for everything.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	394	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_33037dc4	captain	But in that case, what is your title?	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	394	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_9ce18a0b	captain	If you are right, you cannot have forgotten it.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	394	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_02e2ba2c		There, she hesitates.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	402	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_1e4b2c0f	host	My memory, I am afraid, is not what it once was.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	406	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_515f1b66	captain	Surely, my Lady would know her title.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	410	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_e5bfc51c	captain	There is no doubt your father has repeated it constantly as you were growing up.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	410	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_9e1dfb75	captain	You should have heard it said by friends, by visitors, in letters addressed to you.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	410	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_feaff13b	captain	You must have heard it when you were presented at court.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	410	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_5c9b3627		She prepares to answer, but cannot find the words.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	420	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_bdc55770		Finally, her smile fades by degrees, and something tired and older takes its place beneath it.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	420	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_cd06df41	host	Very well, Captain.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	426	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_9aac604a	host	You are right.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	426	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_26aeac9b	host	I am not Lady Claythorn.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	426	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_9d864fdd	host	I am just playing the part.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	426	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_a4f93d7c	captain	But why? What is the purpose of this?	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	436	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_36899d42	host	That, I do not know.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	440	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_02ddbe14	host	I was hired for a role, an unconventional one I admit.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	440	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_4bf43c1d	host	But all I was told was what to do, not the reason behind it.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	440	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_6f6aa389	captain	Hired? By whom?	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	448	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_5e8adbdd	host	The arrangement was made through a firm of solicitors in London.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	452	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_e8667b14	host	I never met the person behind this enterprise.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	452	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_d7928501	host	The pay was generous, so I didn't ask many questions.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	452	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_4314250c		It takes me a while to take everything in.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	460	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_2ab45f72		That story goes way beyond what I had imagined.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	460	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_bef40c74		It leads to even more questions.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	460	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_10654848	captain	And the letter left in my room last night?	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	468	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_17a9e9af	host	What letter?	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	472	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_e5c155a9	host	I know nothing of any letter, Captain.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	472	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_754c67c3	captain	And Thomas Moody?	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	478	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_1f240c19	captain	A man is found dead in his bed, and you carry on as though a guest had spilt his wine.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	478	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_7b00a1e5	host	I have no idea what happened to him.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	484	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_5ec8ce0f	host	That was never planned!	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	484	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_ace42ec3		She shifts as she speaks, her weight settling then settling again, as though the ground beneath her would not hold still.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	490	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_fbe67c2b	captain	I am sorry to say, madam, but I do not believe you.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	494	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_21ca06b3		I lift the rifle and level it at her.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	498	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_5a9f7623		Not aiming, precisely. Simply making it plain that I am the one asking the questions.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	498	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_06295863		Her eyes widen. She sets her cup down with a slow, careful hand.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	498	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_42b027c1	host	Captain. Please.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	506	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_01044c9f	captain	Now, you will explain clearly the terms of the arrangement.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	510	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_f2906698	captain	I want to know everything.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	510	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_9707cecb		She opens her mouth to answer.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	519	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_a1c2cbad		A twig snaps behind me.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	525	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_8b564547		I begin to turn, far too slowly.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	531	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_fd8aeca1		Something draws tight around my throat.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	531	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_2f29c1de		The rifle is struck cleanly from my hands before I can bring it round.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	531	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_2735a880		A broad forearm crosses my shoulders.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	531	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_e689ed27		A thin leather strap crushes against my windpipe.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	531	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_d8f621d2		I drive an elbow backwards and find nothing but heavy tweed.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	531	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_108e6868		The butler's breath is steady against my ear.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	531	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_de5ab3df	host	Wait.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	547	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_8e7221b3	host	There is no need to hurt him.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	547	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_ac45074d	butler	I am afraid there is.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	553	butler "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_d33d2dd9	butler	I've heard what he said to you.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	553	butler "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_f4b88dee	butler	He knows too much.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	553	butler "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_bc4a9892		My vision blurs at the edges.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	561	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_317f9c8a		I grope for the knife at my belt.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	561	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_f3154abb		My fingers will not close upon it.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	561	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_confront_host_ccfe668e		A moment more, and the forest folds inward and goes dark.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_moody_dead.rpy	561	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_5e0763db	broken	Doctor Baldwin's party is already three guns strong.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	15	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_090cb21f	broken	I shall round out your own, if my lady will have me.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	15	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_bef9c179	host	Why, Mr Moody, of course.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	21	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_2c1fd9b6	host	The more the merrier.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	21	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_a86b8bb8		A chill passes through me.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	27	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_50c6bd62		I would rather have avoided him this afternoon.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	27	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_a63a2024		But, I cannot object without drawing attention to myself.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	27	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_9ebed843	captain	A pleasure, Mr Moody.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	35	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_78f19824	broken	The pleasure is entirely mine, Captain.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	39	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_f87f0a27		The butler steps forward.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	43	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_2d93a0fd	butler	Very good. Doctor Baldwin and Mr Manning to the western grove, with Mr Harring.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	47	butler "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_02ce991e	butler	The footman will go along with them.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	47	butler "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_5d7fda2b	butler	My lady, Captain Sinha and Mr Moody to the north field, and I shall attend.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	47	butler "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_a8524472		We walk some distance before the first quarry presents itself.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	59	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_9981aa90		A pheasant, breaking cover not ten yards from our line.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	59	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_bdfcb227		Mr Moody's rifle cracks before mine is even at my shoulder.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	67	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_af7eecd7		The bird drops cleanly.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	67	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_8f51bde3	host	Bravo, Mr Moody. A splendid shot.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	73	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_e1b8901b	broken	You flatter me, my lady.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	77	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_1812f097	broken	One does one's best.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	77	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_bb9f2858		I do not care for the ease of it.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	83	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_a7e7ed87		Mr Moody must be a remarkable marksman. His modesty is a performance.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	83	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_1aa9f2b8		My own turn comes a few minutes later, at a rabbit in the grass.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	83	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_dd59cf9f		My hands are not as steady as I should like.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	93	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_fec5a8af		The shot goes a full yard wide.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	93	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_fb3ec8f3	broken	Hard luck, Captain. Hard luck indeed.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	99	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_28b1eb60	captain	I misjudged the lead.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	103	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_b74618de	broken	Quite. The lead.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	107	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_62a46c1f		He is saying this playfully, but I cannot help but feel slighted.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	111	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_b7a7be35		The morning wears on in this fashion.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	117	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_1f538a60		More birds burst from the bushes, and Mr Moody takes them without appearing to aim.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	117	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_fa1f0fcf		Lady Claythorn's shots go wide.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	117	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_3623d702		My own shots find nothing but empty air.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	117	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_a03e78a0		By the time the butler calls us in, only Mr Moody has game to show.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	117	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_06d596d7	host	Three birds and a pair of rabbits, Mr Moody. You are most impressive.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	131	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_ea852905	host	I confess I had no notion we should be so splendidly provided for.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	131	host "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_eba73547	broken	Your ladyship is too generous.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	137	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_fe1445c5	broken	I was just very lucky today, that is all.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	137	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_4db88438	broken	Otherwise, I am certain a decorated veteran like Captain Sinha would have put me quite to shame.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	137	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_d553fccb		He says it politely enough, but I feel the mockery in his tone.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	145	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_a3c645de		I force a thin smile and say no more.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	145	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_c1748cda		We settle for luncheon in a clearing bordered by birches.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	145	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_9324219b		The butler lays out a spread upon a linen cloth and serves the tea with his customary care.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	145	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_49c45661		Mr Moody installs himself at Lady Claythorn's side and keeps up a steady flow of agreeable conversation.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	145	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_d143f75f		I eat very little and say less.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	145	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_df8b4282	broken	Captain, a word, if I may.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	161	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_2ee3cc07	broken	My rifle has been pulling to the left all morning.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	161	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_da2198ef	broken	I should value a second eye upon it.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	161	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_1f9e922f	broken	A few paces up the track will do.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	161	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_f71f56b5		I do not like the idea of following him alone into the trees.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	171	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_23d7cd2a		It is hard to believe there is anything wrong with his weapon.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	171	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_d2986124		But I cannot find a polite reason to refuse.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	171	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_79e76191		My manners overrule my better judgement.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	171	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_a001c80a	captain	Very well.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	181	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_1fb044c7	captain	Lead on, Mr Moody.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	181	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_29905261	captain	I shall be right behind you.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	181	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_f1e63314		I follow him up the track.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	191	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_912418e0		He walks easily, his rifle slung over his shoulder.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	191	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_acf419f8		Thirty yards from the clearing, the cover thickens.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	191	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_1c801090		The voices from the luncheon fall away.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	191	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_1404de51		He stops, turns, and lifts the rifle from his shoulder.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	191	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_5784bee0		Not to show me.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	191	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_c342417f		To hold.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	191	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_20e0215a	broken	That is quite far enough, I think, Captain.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	207	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_c709f8cf		His gun is now pointing directly at my chest.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	211	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_6908f552		My own rifle hangs uselessly at my side.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	211	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_efd86df6		There is a yard too many between us for me to raise it in time.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	211	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_b21c4528	captain	Mr Moody.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	219	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_64ea55f7	captain	What is the meaning of this?	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	219	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_c02ea99a	broken	You see, Captain, I found a piece of paper upon my bed yesterday.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	225	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_81ed9ebd	broken	An old order from the War, written in the autumn of 1917.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	225	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_58d7876f	broken	The order was to send men to take a vaguely strategic position in Flanders.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	225	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_c8fd453f	broken	At first, I did not understand what it was doing here.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	225	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_0fee3000	broken	There must have been thousands of such orders issued during the war.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	225	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_8854d175	broken	Then I recognised the name of the company that received the order: B Company, 2nd Battalion, Lancashire Fusiliers.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	225	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_35e4522b	broken	And then I checked the date of the order.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	225	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_6940705b	broken	It was a date that will remain engraved in my memory for ever.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	225	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_e46a4d4c	broken	And at the end of the order, the name of the man who signed the fatal order.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	225	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_3ce41a8f	broken	Captain S. Sinha, Staff Officer, General Headquarters.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	225	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_b96baced	broken	Hundreds of men were sent by your hand, to take a small village of no importance.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	225	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_4b27ab75	broken	Most of them, dead by now.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	225	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_09b0725a	broken	And the few survivors of that horrific day were not much luckier.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	225	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_a8147361	broken	They were forced to go through life as living monsters, hiding behind a mask such as this.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	225	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_1d1e2f20		He taps the porcelain of his mask with two gloved fingers.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	255	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_6a42c5cb		My mouth is dry.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	259	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_b53f572d		I have signed a great many papers in my time.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	259	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_22a30b12		Transfers, requisitions, routine dispatches.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	259	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_7c3e5423		Most of them I could not recall if my life depended upon it.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	259	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_f27a1307		Yet I never ordered men to battle, that was never my job.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	259	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_40d992d1	captain	You are mistaken, Mr Moody.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	271	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_eec250e1	captain	That is a slander.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	271	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_cd5841ca	captain	I have never sent men to their deaths.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	271	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_d5dd50d7	captain	My work relied only on securing rations, arranging transport, and endorsing requisitions.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	271	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_3d356d30	captain	Someone is trying to pit you against me.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	271	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_c0b32f38	broken	Ah! How convenient for you, Captain.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	283	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_54e6a537	broken	But I have no reason to believe you.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	283	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_e0f5b539	broken	Especially since I am now sure that you are not the war hero you claim.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	283	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_cb1b306c	broken	I know that a staff officer never sees battle.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	283	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_96446eea	broken	It was obvious today, when you could not even shoot a bird right under your nose.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	283	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_c23e8a5c	broken	Yet yesterday you were entertaining everyone with tales of Burma and the Boxers, as though you had fought in them yourself.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	283	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_44e541b5	broken	You are a fraud, that is plain.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	283	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_1e590caa	broken	And maybe somebody is using me to hurt you.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	283	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_2fc7411e	broken	But I am very happy to oblige.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	283	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_03ad60cc		He does not lower the rifle.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	303	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_21bff9ce		His gaze is resolute, heavy with hatred.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	303	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_1804485e	captain	Please, Mr Moody, consider what is at stake here.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	309	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_18af1d8b	captain	Someone here is manufacturing all of this.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	309	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_5ebd5bb2	captain	They were likely hoping for precisely this to happen.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	309	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_0932afc0	captain	You are being used to their end.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	309	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_58e4b84d	captain	And you are no safer than I am.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	309	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_721a118e	broken	How very considerate of you, Captain.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	321	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_657ff964	broken	But I can quite look after myself, I assure you.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	321	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_83645ccf		He levels the rifle at my head.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	327	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_2c5fc823		I raise my hands to protect myself.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	327	"[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_b4cfe94c	broken	Ah! It is rather plain you never saw battle, Captain.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	333	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_ac5cdb5c	broken	Well.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	333	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_hunt_moody_alive_6d69ee27	broken	This is as close as it gets.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/2_Hunt/3_moody_alive.rpy	333	broken "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_5e16f8fd		The walk back from the western grove felt twice as long as it ought to have.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	36	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_db67ca05		Doctor Baldwin was a heavier man than he appeared, and the makeshift stretcher was poor work.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	36	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_bf356205		But that is the sort of thought one keeps firmly to oneself.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	36	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_663b458a		As we carry him through the entrance hall, I hear footsteps on the stair.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	36	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_fc108342		Miss Baxter and Miss Marsh come to a halt at the bottom, and both their faces change at once.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	36	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_8383ec3c		Mr Harring and I carry the doctor up the stair and lay him upon his bed.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	52	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_158bb9b5		I draw a blanket over him to the shoulders, as one would for a man asleep.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	52	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_e639297a		The boy stays beside me, drained of colour.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	52	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_374eea0a		He has seen enough today to last him a long time.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	52	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_49bb6d41		I leave him to his change of clothes and start back down the stair.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	64	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_06db1f7c		A household cannot be permitted to drift. Someone must hold it steady, and the task, by default, falls to me.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	64	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_daa7e230		The plan is laid. Manning to his room.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	78	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_82fc06b0		Then, I have no doubt, our hostess will urge the rest of us to scatter to our own, and we shall meet again at dinner as though nothing of consequence had occurred.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	78	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_73dd5755		That will not do. Not with what I know.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	78	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_428638fe		A name that is no title. A portrait that is not upon the wall. A hostess who cannot shoulder her own rifle.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	78	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_a021c3f7		And now, a second death.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	78	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_143a6846		One death, beneath a capable mistress, may pass as ill fortune.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	78	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_b59e6fca		Two deaths, beneath a mistress who is not its mistress, does not.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	78	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_1db39d83		If I am to press her on any of this, I must do it now, before witnesses who are still shaken enough to listen.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	78	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_a01b6029		But I must also have the field to myself.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	78	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_bb694045		The butler is her prop. Her steadiness. His keys, his discretion, his composure at her elbow.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	78	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_85de9baf		If I am to challenge her, I should like him well out of the room. Upstairs, seeing to Mr Manning, would do nicely.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	78	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_35cabff7		Or I may simply take Manning up myself, as the house has invited me to, and let this moment pass.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	78	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_b7fb6ca6		A public accusation, if it does not land, will finish me just as surely as a rifle in a wood.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	78	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_e16ed68f		I sit upon the edge of the bed with my hands pressed together.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	124	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_0e334bb9		A good officer reviews the field after the action, not during it.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	124	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_2a7ac317		So I let the afternoon settle in my mind, piece by piece.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	124	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_13c35241		Doctor Baldwin, shot under circumstances that can be explained, but that hang uneasily all the same.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	124	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_9bf061c4		Mr Moody, dead in his bed only this morning.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	124	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_2d9add1d		A butler with a ready set of keys. A hostess with an unruffled composure.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	124	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_29741d2f		And a letter left upon my pillow last night that I have still not accounted for.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	124	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_809e5519		The gong.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	146	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_265d23a4		As though we were the same party that sat down last night.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	146	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_af37e315		Three chairs sit empty.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	156	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_3f2a0924		Doctor Baldwin. Mr Moody. Mr Manning.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	156	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_612a1a82		I take my usual place. Miss Baxter settles on my right, quieter than I have yet seen her.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	156	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_6e3f747b		Miss Marsh has been moved nearer to the head of the table, at our hostess's invitation.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	156	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_60bfdb1d		Mr Harring slips in a moment later, hair damp, a fresh shirt at his collar.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	156	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_4a34e572		Lady Claythorn rises to speak.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	156	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_ce97e587		Not a glance, not a flicker, to acknowledge the exchange of an hour past.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	174	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_329d5029		She might as well have taken tea with me between whiles.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	174	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_c73de93d		I watch her carefully and learn nothing I did not already know.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	174	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_eb45253c		That, in itself, is worth noting. A woman truly disturbed by a guest's accusation would not be this still.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	174	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_17732b73		A measured address. If she is troubled by what has happened beneath her roof today, nothing of it shows.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	186	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_d44d56f6		A man less suspicious than I am would take her at her word and think no further of it.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	186	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_7c9a5a29		As it is, I take note of her composure, and say nothing of it aloud.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	186	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_normal_escort_bac9e75d		Manning walks ahead of me without speaking.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	207	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_normal_escort_3d86005f		The drink is still on him, though quieter now. He moves like a man in a dream he does not care to interrupt.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	207	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_normal_escort_727840bd		I see him into his room and draw the door closed behind him.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	207	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_normal_escort_b7d59823		The key turns in the lock with a heavy, deliberate click.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	207	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_normal_escort_45a5eb13		For good measure, I try the handle twice. It holds.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	221	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_normal_escort_5e737dc8		He will trouble no one for the remainder of the evening.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	221	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_normal_escort_5a400875		I weigh the key in my palm.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	221	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_normal_escort_8c08f956		It would be the natural thing to return it to the butler at once.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	221	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_normal_escort_1fcf5991		And yet... I should prefer it stayed where it is.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	221	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_normal_escort_10618b1d		Tonight, under this roof, a key is not a small thing.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	221	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_normal_escort_bae9bc55		I slip it quietly into my waistcoat pocket.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	221	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_normal_escort_fa418489		When I come back down, the others have remained much as I left them.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	241	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_normal_escort_d6165930		Lady Claythorn looks towards me with the faintly anxious composure of a hostess whose weekend has slipped beyond repair.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	241	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_butler_escorts_manning_32233290	captain	Mr Harring needed to change, he'll join us shortly.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	266	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_butler_escorts_manning_32203767	host	Ah, Captain! It's good you're here.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	270	host "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_butler_escorts_manning_8a7cb8f6	host	We've been deliberating over what action to take concerning Samuel Manning.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	270	host "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_butler_escorts_manning_499543b1	captain	I see.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	276	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_butler_escorts_manning_61a7be99	captain	And what is your plan?	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	276	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_butler_escorts_manning_654d0412	host	We've decided to confine him to his chamber.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	282	host "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_butler_escorts_manning_69d7ceae	host	At least until the authorities can take over.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	282	host "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_butler_escorts_manning_39e0bc9a	captain	A prudent measure, my lady.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	288	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_butler_escorts_manning_f264eba4	captain	Though I hope you will forgive me if I stop short of playing gaoler in a house not my own.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	288	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_butler_escorts_manning_045f77f0	captain	The task ought to fall to a member of your household.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	288	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_butler_escorts_manning_1d9abc99		A brief silence.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	296	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_butler_escorts_manning_fdb6efcc		The hostess hesitates, then turns to the butler.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	296	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_butler_escorts_manning_98c6a5b8	host	Of course, Captain. How thoughtless of me to have supposed otherwise.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	302	host "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_butler_escorts_manning_532864da	butler	I shall see to it, my lady.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	306	butler "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_butler_escorts_manning_34ee9aef		The butler produces his keys with practised ease and moves to Samuel Manning's side.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	310	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_butler_escorts_manning_34db2d0e	butler	If you will come with me, sir. This way.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	314	butler "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_butler_escorts_manning_5a2d9cd9	drunk	Yes... yes, of course.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	318	drunk "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_butler_escorts_manning_a50960ee		Manning rises without protest and follows the butler towards the stair.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	322	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_butler_escorts_manning_d86cdd48		The two men disappear up the steps, and the hall quiets in their wake.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	322	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_butler_escorts_manning_d90cca8a		That is precisely the ground I wanted.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	322	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_butler_escorts_manning_3b3a3ee1		With the butler out of the room, our hostess has lost her closest prop.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	322	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_d57fc959		Miss Baxter and Miss Marsh linger uncertainly near the foot of the stair.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	339	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_5bcf4846		Lady Claythorn draws breath to speak, no doubt to send us all to our rooms until the gong.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	339	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_c08b6c37		I move before she can.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	339	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_ef95c19c	captain	Forgive me, Lady Claythorn. I am afraid I cannot, in good conscience, retire to my room as though this were merely a weekend grown tiresome.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	347	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_31aac8ec	host	Captain?	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	351	host "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_0cfb11b5	captain	Two men dead within the space of a day, beneath the same roof.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	355	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_c7f8ca21	captain	Mr Moody in the small hours. Doctor Baldwin in the woods this afternoon.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	355	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_b01a5cfa	captain	And now you mean to send us upstairs, to wait upon our dinner in quiet reflection.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	355	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_10bbad02	captain	That, my lady, is not the conduct of a house in mourning. That is the conduct of a house carrying on a performance.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	355	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_31315295	host	Captain, I ask only that we preserve what order we may.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	365	host "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_3a4ee763	host	The police cannot reach us before morning. Running about in alarm will not bring back either man.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	365	host "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_8e707be6	captain	Order has its place, my lady. And grief has another.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	371	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_652f6928	captain	You have shown us no sign of the second.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	371	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_9d5c16b5		The hall stills.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	377	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_50cca624		Miss Marsh has turned her head. Miss Baxter watches me with an expression I cannot read at all.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	377	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_19be5867	psychic	Captain... surely you cannot mean to suggest our hostess is in some way answerable for what has happened?	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	383	psychic surprised "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_12cf85a5	captain	I mean, Miss Baxter, that we ought not accept this evening at its face value.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	387	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_0ea2cb7f	captain	For there is a great deal about our hostess that does not sit well with me.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	387	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_ab12520b		Her smile holds, as a hostess's smile will hold through a guest's poor taste.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	393	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_9644d794		But the set of her shoulders has shifted.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	393	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_1e463d03	captain	Your portrait, my lady, is nowhere in the gallery upstairs.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	399	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_bb99480d	captain	In a house as old as this, where every Claythorn since Cromwell hangs upon the wall, the present mistress is absent.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	399	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_d50cf671	captain	And on the hunt this afternoon, you could scarcely shoulder a rifle. A gentlewoman who arranges a shooting weekend on her own grounds ought to know her piece.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	399	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_3049e97b	captain	And most particular of all, your surname is not a title, as it ought to be. There is no such style as 'Lady Claythorn.'	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	399	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_156fcd75	captain	Any one of these, taken alone, would perhaps pass for nothing.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	399	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_ce54e987	captain	Taken together, they paint a picture I cannot unsee.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	399	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_80feff27	host	Captain, you overreach yourself.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	413	host "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_36f1ae4e	host	Each of those trifles has a perfectly ordinary explanation.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	413	host "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_7e15479b	host	You will forgive me if, after the day we have had, I am not minded to deliver them in detail.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	413	host "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_a7065820	captain	Then deliver me this one, my lady, and I shall press you no further tonight.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	421	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_2d6e695d	captain	What is your title?	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	421	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_8280f3ca		A silence.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	427	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_8c3d0c3c		It is the silence of a woman who was not expecting the question put quite so plainly.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	427	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_eac9a5f3		Her eye flicks towards the stair, as though to measure how long the butler has been gone.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	427	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_9cda06bb	host	Captain, I find your tone intolerable.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	435	host "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_b029dd8a	host	I shall not be interrogated in my own hall.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	435	host "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_b4291813	nurse	Captain Sinha... perhaps this is not the hour for such a discussion.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	441	nurse "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_f298be9e	nurse	We are all of us shaken.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	441	nurse "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_1a43800b		Miss Marsh speaks gently, but there is something close to a warning in her eye.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	447	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_24429d22		I realise at once that I have spent my ammunition.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	447	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_35c6b9db		To press further now, before witnesses too tired and too frightened to weigh the matter, would serve only to make me appear unhinged.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	447	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_ff0df5a5		I let a beat pass, and incline my head.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	447	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_72a7bda7	captain	Of course, Miss Marsh. Forgive me.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	457	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_2316c2b6	captain	I have said what I felt I must.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	457	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_9c838995	captain	I shall say no more of it tonight.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	457	captain "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_60e8a43b		But I have said it, and before two witnesses. That cannot be taken back.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	465	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_59714144		Lady Claythorn recovers her smile.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	465	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_482a436f	host	No harm done, Captain. These are trying hours for us all.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	471	host "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_f3d201db	host	I trust we shall meet at dinner on better terms.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	471	host "[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_6f12b86b		A gracious answer, and perfectly delivered.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	477	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_13de6ed9		At that moment, I hear the butler's tread upon the stair.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	477	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_b558394e		He returns to the hall in the manner of a man who has heard what he was not meant to hear.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	477	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_121c4513		Her eye meets his for the briefest of moments.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	477	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_6806239c		A look passes between them. Brief. Unambiguous.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	477	"[what]"
captain_day2_evening_confront_host_81532425		Whatever I have planted in this hall tonight, I have been marked for it.	game/scripts/captain/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	477	"[what]"
breakpoint_0d30a068		DEBUG	game/scripts/custom_functions.rpy	94	"[what]"
work_in_progress_db4afd84		You've reached to end of the story written so far.	game/scripts/custom_functions.rpy	436	"[what]"
work_in_progress_d2fbcd7b		But don't worry, the rest of this game will be ready soon ! (or at some point in the future).	game/scripts/custom_functions.rpy	436	"[what]"
doctor_introduction_bb8cad4a		Anxiety hits me harder than usualy.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	27	"[what]"
doctor_introduction_78eb136c		I haven't been away this long in years. It feels off, but there's no turning back.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	27	"[what]"
doctor_introduction_55f63765		Not with so much money at stake.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	27	"[what]"
doctor_introduction_b8f159d0		I'll manage. I always do.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	27	"[what]"
doctor_introduction_a1adb73e		My gaze lands on the bag. I pause. The thought crosses my mind—it could help. It always does.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	27	"[what]"
doctor_introduction_faa21329		But it's a mistake, and I know it.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	27	"[what]"
doctor_introduction_d19ac6c3		I don't want to start wrong. Not this time. Something tells me I'll need my wits about me all weekend.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	27	"[what]"
doctor_introduction_dde2ae4b		I think it through, weigh it all, and still reach for the bag.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	27	"[what]"
doctor_introduction_0c750674		As I head to the bathroom, the train begins to slow.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	47	"[what]"
doctor_introduction_8b19326e		Too late now.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	47	"[what]"
doctor_introduction_e485fd96		I gather my things and leave the train.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	57	"[what]"
doctor_introduction_be2a3f51		Stepping off, I look for my driver.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	63	"[what]"
doctor_introduction_126413c4		The train is empty enough that I quickly spot the only person fitting the bill at the station.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	63	"[what]"
doctor_introduction_2546a253	doctor	Hello. Could you help me? I'm supposed to go to Claythorn Manor.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	69	doctor "[what]"
doctor_introduction_15962149	footman	Of course, sir. Lady Claythorn sent me to pick up her guests.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	73	footman "[what]"
doctor_introduction_244a30fe	doctor	Good. Do you know how many were on this train?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	77	doctor "[what]"
doctor_introduction_864ff013	footman	I can't say for certain. We'll wait a few minutes to see if anyone else shows up.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	81	footman "[what]"
doctor_introduction_24990bbb	doctor	Fine.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	85	doctor "[what]"
doctor_introduction_e6d3686e		It isn't long before a woman approaches us.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	89	"[what]"
doctor_introduction_f76b3e7c		I am seated at the front of the car.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	97	"[what]"
doctor_introduction_ac4b2d9e		I tried to keep the conversation going for a while, but it fizzled out rather quickly.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	97	"[what]"
doctor_introduction_1e1debaf		Rosalind Marsh seems to be more of the quiet type, and besides, she still seems uneasy about being seated with the former soldier.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	97	"[what]"
doctor_introduction_6888aeb0		She keeps looking out of the window, avoiding his gaze as much as possible.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	97	"[what]"
doctor_introduction_a8815acb		Thomas Moody doesn't seem to mind. He must be accustomed to this kind of treatment.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	97	"[what]"
doctor_introduction_e78e08f6		In any case, he remains silent. I don't know if it's out of compassion for Miss Marsh or if that's just his nature.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	97	"[what]"
doctor_introduction_1d202687		So after a while, we all retreated into a silent contemplation of the landscape.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	97	"[what]"
doctor_introduction_c092da5b		I glance behind me every now and then to check on the others, when I notice the driver looking at me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	97	"[what]"
doctor_introduction_da2763b2		When he realises I can see him, he quickly turns back to stare at the road.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	97	"[what]"
doctor_introduction_edcd00dd		Am I imagining things, or is he blushing?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	97	"[what]"
doctor_introduction_931dc5da		It looks like we've reached our destination right on time to avoid a storm.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	123	"[what]"
doctor_introduction_4690ce0f		The sky is getting dark but it's not raining yet.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	123	"[what]"
doctor_introduction_454d209b		Claythorn Manor is impressive enough.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	123	"[what]"
doctor_introduction_c884aca4		I better try to relax now.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	123	"[what]"
doctor_downstairs_day1_9342f037		I ought to have a look downstairs. Might be something of interest there.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	73	"[what]"
doctor_downstairs_day1_bc9313d9	footman	Good evening, sir. I'm afraid guests aren't permitted beyond this point.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	77	footman "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_day1_3f285e1e		I offer him my warmest smile.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	81	"[what]"
doctor_downstairs_day1_6827d1c2	doctor	I do apologise. I'm only having a quick look. Could you make an exception?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	85	doctor "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_day1_74fe5b9f	doctor	I promise I won't be long.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	85	doctor "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_day1_5c30c593	footman	If it were up to me, I'd gladly say yes.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	91	footman "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_day1_c0780646	footman	But Lady Claythorn was quite clear with her instructions.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	91	footman "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_day1_ba6d9818	footman	I'm sure you understand.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	91	footman "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_day1_c4e84946	footman	Please don't take it personally.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	91	footman "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_day1_d5eef9fb		He says it with a warm smile of his own.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	101	"[what]"
doctor_downstairs_day1_db4e644a		His eyes say sorry, but there's something else there, too.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	101	"[what]"
doctor_downstairs_day1_3ab0530b		I wonder if...	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	101	"[what]"
doctor_downstairs_flirt_5e35b606	doctor	That's a shame, but I quite understand. Orders are orders.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	121	doctor "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_flirt_56e84a32	doctor	Still, I had rather hoped you might show me around.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	121	doctor "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_flirt_aeaa4858	doctor	There are a few things I'd not mind discussing with you.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	121	doctor "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_flirt_833422b7	footman	I'm a bit tied up at the moment, sir.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	129	footman "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_flirt_cfaa7feb	footman	But I could make time later, if you'd still care to talk.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	129	footman "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_flirt_7a5a9d1c	doctor	I'd like that very much.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	135	doctor "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_flirt_99e530b3	doctor	Where shall we meet?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	135	doctor "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_flirt_9300500a	footman	Hard to say when I'll be free.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	141	footman "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_flirt_26f11820	footman	But I could stop by your room once I've a moment—if you don't mind, that is.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	141	footman "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_flirt_7fb5cd4d		Well, that is rather forward.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	147	"[what]"
doctor_downstairs_flirt_59428c37		I glance about to be sure we're alone.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	147	"[what]"
doctor_downstairs_flirt_6ac1d039		We are.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	147	"[what]"
doctor_downstairs_flirt_bccc96d8		I let my gaze linger a moment longer than necessary.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	147	"[what]"
doctor_downstairs_flirt_df8e6040	doctor	Are you certain you can't come now?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	157	doctor "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_flirt_0d79ff0a	footman	No, truly I can't.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	161	footman "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_flirt_e87c2236	footman	But I'll be done soon enough.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	161	footman "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_flirt_9d93e7cd	footman	I'll see you later then, Doctor Baldwin.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	161	footman "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_flirt_051b9d15	doctor	Please—call me Daniel.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	169	doctor "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_flirt_bc888356	footman	Very well, Daniel. I'm Andrew.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	173	footman "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_flirt_d24a10cc	doctor	I'll see you later, Andrew.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	177	doctor "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_apologize_eddf6947	doctor	Quite right.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	188	doctor "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_apologize_860f2cee	doctor	I'll be off, then.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	188	doctor "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_apologize_776ba773	doctor	Good evening.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	188	doctor "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_apologize_3050204c	footman	Good evening, sir.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	196	footman "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_library_ed71b42e		That is a well-furnished library.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	208	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_library_56485fb4		It's been a while since I've seen that many books.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	208	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_library_fdd0f525		There is one already opened on a desk.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	208	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_library_bd3589c1		"A Genealogical and Heraldic Dictionary of the Landed Gentry of Great Britain."	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	208	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_library_9aeff08f		That sounds tedious.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	208	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_library_fe27ecea		But maybe I can borrow something else to read later in my room?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	208	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_library_1846ca73		I'm sure our host won't mind.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	208	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_library_6aac250f		I looked around for a book that might be of interest, and found a couple of options.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	226	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_book_mystery_ea91edaf		That appears to be the most recent book they have.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	252	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_book_mystery_c4efed3c		A mystery novel.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	252	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_book_mystery_811c1a34		I don't know the author, but a quick look at her biography tells me she was a nurse during the war.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	252	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_book_mystery_ea6f4633		So I feel like I could relate to the her.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	252	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_library_book_opium_7f15897b		I have been meaning to read this for a long time.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	269	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_library_book_opium_0de46f29		Maybe now is the time.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	269	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_garden_2b3be8d1		From the great hall, I am ready to go and have a look outside.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	294	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_garden_6ea23b5b		But the weather has worsened, I do not think it is safe to go out tonight.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	294	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_85ad116f		My knocking slightly opens the door.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	318	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_b3fedafa		From the hallway, I can see part of the room.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	318	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_8e8ed769		It is in a dreadful state.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	318	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_2d53f05a		Should I take a peek?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	318	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_24129003		I know and it's probably a bad idea and that I should close this door.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	330	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_2fef76d8		But I've got an intrusive feeling that if don't enter, something bad will happen.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	330	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_a42dfaa7		That is obviously silly, but...	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	330	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_not_enter_e45406f4		Why am I thinking, there is no reason for me to intrude.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	356	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_not_enter_e850a37d		I close the door and leave.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	356	"[what]"
doctor_bedroom_psychic_evening_50c0def1	psychic	Yes? Who is it?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	376	psychic "[what]"
doctor_bedroom_psychic_evening_7bc599c3	doctor	It's Doctor Baldwin.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	380	doctor "[what]"
