doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_enter_a00db05e		I try to remember Samuel Manning, but I cannot say for certain that I ever treated his wife.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	41	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_enter_cb66d162		That does not mean the charge is false.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	41	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_enter_a8f25187		I know I have done similar things to a good many patients. Mrs Manning may well have been among them, and I have simply forgotten.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	41	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_enter_d94f9a90		One thing is certain though. Someone in this house means me harm.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	41	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_enter_79a48df1		And they are trying to use Samuel Manning to hurt me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	41	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_enter_60aefb24		I say they, but it is plain enough who must have written this note.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	41	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_enter_c3759046		Lady Claythorn invited me here. She is the most obvious culprit.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	41	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_enter_1fd169ef		In that case my invitation here was no kindly whim, but a deliberate act.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	41	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_enter_37eb5b4d		Yet I cannot be sure, for I did not recognise her at all when we were introduced.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	41	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_enter_56097cad		But that, again, may mean very little.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	41	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_enter_cb7d6996		It could, of course, be an extraordinary coincidence.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	41	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_enter_e83bd2ea		Perhaps some enemy of mine is numbered among the guests, and Lady Claythorn has nothing at all to do with this.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	41	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_enter_f0691f9a		It is not very likely, yet not impossible.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	41	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_enter_acd642ba		What am I to do now.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	41	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_enter_bbf85bb7		The prudent course might be to warn everyone and abandon the whole business.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	41	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_enter_eee6ba65		But I have no notion how any of them would react to such an announcement.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	41	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_enter_74d5f5b1		That could mean sacrificing the prize money.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	41	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_enter_b14d5cdf		And if this letter were to be spoken of outside these walls, it might cost me my practice as well.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	41	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_enter_77be1505		I cannot afford that.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	41	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_enter_f277ebee		Besides, this could yet prove no more than a cruel jest, or some wretched misunderstanding.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	41	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_enter_8ff0e1a9		If I remain, nothing more may come of it.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	41	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_enter_aa49476d		I need only be on my guard, and watch Samuel Manning closely.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	41	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_enter_d5135ad9		I must decide.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	41	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_enter_9398f9b1		Do I risk my life, or do I risk losing the kind of money that would set me up comfortably for years to come.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	41	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_e77dbf01		Why am I even considering staying here?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	107	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_454e4877		I should leave at once and warn the others.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	107	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_f3cfb2ec		I believe they are all gathered in the billiard room.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	107	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_86298e97		If Lady Claythorn truly is behind this, I would rather face her with witnesses than wait alone for whatever she has planned.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	107	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_a45bb9da		I find most of them assembled around Captain Sinha.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	119	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_4fd30174		I interrupt him.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	119	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_a8902ad1	doctor	Pardon me, Captain, but I have something you should see.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	125	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_5b147553		I hand him the letter.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	129	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_64079dd5		He reads it aloud to the assembled company.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	129	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_64ea55f7	captain	What is the meaning of this?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	135	captain "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_5ddb44f0	captain	Where did you find it?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	135	captain "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_736d0e20	doctor	In Samuel Manning's room.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	141	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_07fb0286	captain	Really? And what were you doing there?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	145	captain "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_90dcac10	doctor	The door was open, and I was—	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	149	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_e9f4ea86	drunk	Wait, you went into my room?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	153	drunk "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_a3054be8	drunk	What gave you the right to do such a thing?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	153	drunk "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_07abdf9c	doctor	That is not the issue. How do you explain this letter?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	159	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_63b5a956	drunk	I have never seen it before.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	163	drunk "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_86ea484c	drunk	It isn't mine.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	163	drunk "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_9b9e6ad5	doctor	Truly? And we are supposed to take you at your word?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	169	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_302de678	drunk	I don't see why anyone should believe you either.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	173	drunk "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_c9bae6bd	drunk	A man who thinks it proper to barge into another's room.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	173	drunk "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_f1820f3a	drunk	Unless, of course, you did not enter it at all, and wrote this yourself.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	173	drunk "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_9560efdb	doctor	Why on earth would I do that? It makes no sense.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	181	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_d1351678	drunk	No less sense than what you're implying, Doctor.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	185	drunk "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_63a1b62a	drunk	Do you truly expect anyone here to believe you?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	185	drunk "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_9cf58935		I glance around the room. All eyes are upon us.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	191	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_4e25bac5		The others look perplexed, unsure what to make of the exchange.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	191	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_9a349fe2		Silence lingers until Captain Sinha finally speaks.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	191	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_dfb1aca8	captain	There is something amiss here, though I cannot tell who is at fault.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	199	captain "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_358fc539	doctor	Surely it cannot be me. Just look at Samuel Manning.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	203	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_63cce7fb	doctor	Is he even sober enough to make sense?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	203	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_68781cce	drunk	What makes you say I am drunk?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	209	drunk "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_56d7f1e1	drunk	I can gather my wits when the occasion calls for it.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	209	drunk "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_8b44228f	captain	Enough, both of you.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	215	captain "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_6c929279	captain	I do not understand any of this. We should think it over with cooler heads.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	215	captain "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_a45ad4ed	captain	Lady Claythorn, what do you make of it?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	215	captain "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_f7769fd9		Our hostess is visibly shaken, yet manages to reply.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	223	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_322af410		I watch her closely.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	223	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_84c318b8		If she wrote the first part of that letter, then this is her handiwork laid bare before everyone.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	223	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_5759bc07		Yet I cannot tell whether her distress is genuine horror or a performance.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	223	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_df2333f9	host	I, I don't know.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	233	host "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_fe0aafbe	host	I'm not certain whom to believe.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	233	host "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_7edf24c4	host	What do you suggest, Captain?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	233	host "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_800bc7a1	captain	We shan't settle this now. It requires thought.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	241	captain "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_2b2d269c	captain	I propose we confine the two of you to your rooms until we reach a conclusion.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	241	captain "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_e9933edb	doctor	What? No.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	247	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_586c3220	doctor	I must leave this place at once. I am not safe here.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	247	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_42668e12	captain	It's far too late to leave now. The storm makes travel dangerous.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	253	captain "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_bc5ca8b2	captain	You'll be safer in your room.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	253	captain "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_f8cca1f3		I ponder that for a moment. The storm is raging outside, leaving now would be perilous.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	262	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_2b0ecfd9		Yet staying in my room hardly feels safer, not with Samuel Manning and perhaps Lady Claythorn herself set against me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	262	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_d7a255e0		The others watch me uneasily. I can tell they do not quite believe me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	262	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_a7a2cf67	doctor	Very well, I'll go to my room.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	270	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_b2670cb0	doctor	But I want your word that I will be allowed to leave at first light.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	270	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_c98ac8e9	doctor	I do not wish to remain here a moment longer than necessary.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	270	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_1bd273eb	captain	You have my word, Doctor.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	278	captain "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_c05dcace	captain	And you, Mr Manning?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	278	captain "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_bfe61392	drunk	All right, I'll go to my room as well.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	284	drunk "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_3d3160b9	drunk	It's late enough.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	284	drunk "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_1ec1538b	captain	Then it's settled. Please, follow me, Doctor Baldwin.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	290	captain "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_8f714453		Captain Sinha escorts me to my room.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	294	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_c9a07fc5		The butler and Lady Claythorn accompany Samuel Manning to his.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	294	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_a425ab76		I am far from reassured, yet see no alternative.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	294	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_1c9392a9		I enter my room as the Captain remain outside.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	294	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_419f594b	captain	My apologies, Doctor Baldwin. I am sure we shall sort this out soon enough.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	306	captain "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_5fefe53e	captain	In the meantime, we shall have to lock you in.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	306	captain "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_77d6e7ec		Before he can close the door, I lower my voice.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	312	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_367f7eac	doctor	Captain, between ourselves, you must see what this implies.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	316	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_837c0f06	doctor	Lady Claythorn invited us both here.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	316	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_d9e0553c	doctor	She is in all likelihood the one who wrote that letter to Samuel Manning.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	316	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_db9be5d1	doctor	Which means something dangerous may be at play here.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	316	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_0150824f		He hesitates, then answers just as quietly.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	326	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_02b0bc6f	captain	I cannot deny the thought has crossed my mind.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	330	captain "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_72f10861	captain	But from my point of view, I have only an anonymous letter that you say you found in rather singular circumstances.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	330	captain "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_7e294641	captain	I cannot possibly accuse our hostess openly on that alone.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	330	captain "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_82e48591	doctor	I understand your position, but please keep it in mind, and be careful.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	338	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_f1f5fa08	captain	You have my word.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	342	captain "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_e4175efe		He leaves me alone, so I lock my door and do what I can to secure it.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	346	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_1cfbc6b4		I have no intention of sitting idly by, so I barricade the door in case Manning, or even Lady Claythorn herself, decides to pay a visit.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	352	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_657d85a8		Now all I can do is wait.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	358	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_5f54d212		After what feels like hours, someone knocks at my door.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	366	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_b3dfbebb	captain	Doctor Baldwin, after some discussion, we have decided you may be right in one respect.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	372	captain "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_4943583e	captain	There is too much here that does not add up.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	372	captain "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_d340dcdb	captain	We shall all leave in the morning.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	372	captain "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_f29fda82	captain	For the time being, we shall all rest easier if you and Mister Manning stay in your rooms for the night.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	372	captain "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_b9ed4ffa	captain	I did not dare accused Lady Claythorn directly, but I will also keep an eye her.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	372	captain "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_6ebea522		Good, he has not dismissed my suspicions entirely.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	384	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_04582365	doctor	Very well. I have barricaded myself anyway.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	388	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_d74de910	captain	A wise precaution, Doctor. Again, my apologies.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	392	captain "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_1172ae20	doctor	Of course, I understand, Captain. Good night.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	396	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_ed95eb32	captain	Good night, Doctor.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	400	captain "[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_9d8bb2e7		At least this dreadful business will soon be over.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	404	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_d9764205		What am I to do now?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	404	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_26f1670c		I do not think I could sleep in this state.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	404	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_32f5dc3a		And perhaps it is better to stay alert.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	404	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_0e766270		But on the other hand, I think I am protected enough here.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	404	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_sleep_047f08b8		I am far too tense.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	428	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_sleep_5277c007		Despite the risk, I cannot resist the urge to calm my nerves.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	428	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_awake_3738f434		I lie on my bed, not expecting to close my eyes before morning.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	440	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_awake_3f8f1e9d		Nevertheless, after a few hours, I doze off, utterly exhausted.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	440	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_awake_2ee56621		I am awakened by a strange noise.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	450	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_awake_1b1ce6a4		What is that?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	450	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_awake_affe8440		I realise I cannot breathe.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	450	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_awake_95b1f42b		Smoke.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	460	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_awake_fd36083a		Something is burning.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	460	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_awake_1407746e		I spring to my feet.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	460	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_awake_660daa88		The walls of the room are ablaze.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	460	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_awake_01ce547d		Smoke fills the air, I can scarcely see a thing.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	460	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_awake_7724baae		I rush towards the door, but the furniture I placed against it blocks my way.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	460	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_awake_4da44f25		I summon all my strength to move it, yet I have no energy left.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	460	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_awake_ec50daa3		My head spins.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	460	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_leave_manor_awake_efccfaf5		I...	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	460	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_stay_c744fc64		I do not believe I am in any great danger.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	488	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_stay_bd941e89		I shall stay, though I must be cautious from now on.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	488	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_stay_db32b8dd		Especially around Samuel Manning.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	488	"[what]"
doctor_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_stay_aea94b70		And I should try to discover who could have written this wretched letter.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 1/2_Evening/2c_bedroom_drunk.rpy	488	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_87eace4d		Awake, and alive.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	27	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_0e2a02ac		Despite my suspicions, it seems no one tried to harm me in the night.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	33	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_1adb647b		It is a relief, though the weekend is far from over.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	33	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_0b8178f0		I should prepare myself for breakfast.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	33	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_93ce04ad		Strange how those two words came to mind first.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	43	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_0903345f		An odd way to begin the day.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	43	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_feb5c70f		No matter. I ought to prepare myself.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	43	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_0c55d0a7		On most mornings, I would begin in the usual manner.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	53	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_58103d4e		But today is not most mornings.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	53	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_3a9d6b85		Today, I must be different.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	53	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_592053a6		I resist the urge and wash thoroughly with cold water.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	53	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_4be7fdc6		Then I dress, ready to face the others over breakfast.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	53	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_94d90097		As always, I begin with my usual routine.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	67	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_ec234563		Much better. I feel calmer now—prepared to greet the day and those within it.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	73	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_71da71fa		I take my seat at the breakfast table. Few have arrived so far.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	81	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_54c02450		Aside from the staff, only Captain Sinha is present.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	81	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_290c62b2		He sits across the room and merely offers a silent nod in greeting.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	81	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_5b5b0737		With nothing to do but eat, I quietly serve myself a plate.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	81	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_2d35d91c		Gradually, the other guests begin to appear.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	81	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_68c428f8		Lady Claythorn and Rosalind Marsh enter together, deep in conversation.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	81	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_0a53177c		Lady Claythorn joins Captain Sinha.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	81	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_93783a35		Rosalind Marsh sits beside me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	81	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_a66c4bac		I know it is not entirely proper to address someone across the table.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	81	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_9fd35241		But at present, she is the only one near enough to speak to.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	81	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_3dd9b203		Suddenly, our host approaches me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	111	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_636423b8		When I reach the dining room, our host turns to me at once.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	123	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_1863d7aa		After a while, everyone has finished eating.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	129	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_0e2a282c		We are to go out on a hunt.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	137	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_03f98ca6		I am not sure I feel up to it, and I do not think I am the only one.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	137	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_7affa4ab		Everyone looks a little uncomfortable.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	137	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_e6f2ccf7		Captain Sinha is the first to break the silence.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	137	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_79571bc8		I can see looks of disapproval at this.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	149	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_bbd5b1a0		But no one dares say anything.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	149	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_98796419		Given Samuel Manning's obvious inebriety, most seem to assume he will fall asleep before the hunt even begins.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	149	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_16bf760e		He says it without much conviction.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	163	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_aa9848fb		One can tell he is on the fence about the whole thing.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	163	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_3f7351f3		Everyone is looking towards me now.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	171	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_d078a4ff		They clearly assume I shall go as well.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	171	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_2f0bc1d7		Yet something troubles me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	179	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_d36744c2		I cannot make sense of Thomas Moody not being truly injured.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	179	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_efe2b5ac		I do not understand it, and it makes me question everything.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	179	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_e9efdfe2		Something is not right, and a hunt is hardly the safest place to be.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	179	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_45fb3cb7		Yet I have not taken my 'medicine' today.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	191	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_796c525e		Withdrawal could set in at any moment.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	191	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_09bba127		In that case, it would be better to remain indoors and manage the symptoms.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	191	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_3df0a1f5		Besides, if I were to stay, I might spend a little more time with my new friend.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	201	"[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_e22e7fae		So, which shall it be?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	205	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_choice_97b094c5	doctor	I shall come as well.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	224	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_choice_f0256626	doctor	You are right. A distraction may serve us.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	224	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_choice_dfa3a31e	host	Excellent. That settles it, then.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	230	host "[what]"
doctor_day2_no_hunt_choice_5f23d216	doctor	I do not feel at all well.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	239	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_no_hunt_choice_3674f137	doctor	I think it would be wiser if I stayed.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	239	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_no_hunt_choice_8c507208	host	I am sorry to hear it, Doctor. Are you quite sure?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	245	host "[what]"
doctor_day2_no_hunt_choice_82678dde	host	The weather has really improved today. It might do you good.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	245	host "[what]"
doctor_day2_no_hunt_choice_677e9011	captain	Yes, there is nothing like fresh air to set a man right.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	251	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_no_hunt_choice_9d7dd3a4	captain	And I do not wish to be dramatic, but it is always prudent to have a doctor with us.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	251	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_no_hunt_choice_166a3d12		They are pressing me from all sides.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	257	"[what]"
doctor_day2_no_hunt_choice_03f65694		I am not certain I can refuse now.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	257	"[what]"
doctor_day2_no_hunt_choice_9d50572f		Not without a very sound reason.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	257	"[what]"
doctor_day2_no_hunt_choice_b9ca3ade		I do have one.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	267	"[what]"
doctor_day2_no_hunt_choice_7312d518		Samuel Manning may very well use this hunt as an opportunity to harm me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	267	"[what]"
doctor_day2_no_hunt_choice_9a827561		To be alone with him, armed and far from the house, would be an unreasonable risk.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	267	"[what]"
doctor_day2_no_hunt_choice_69347292		Yet it would be difficult to refuse without exposing the contents of the letter.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	267	"[what]"
doctor_day2_no_hunt_choice_c8a5abab		And there is a chance I could use the hunt to get an explanation out of Samuel Manning.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	267	"[what]"
doctor_day2_no_hunt_choice_6c5b96e5		I must simply remain alert at every moment.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	267	"[what]"
doctor_day2_no_hunt_choice_55edcfc7	doctor	Perhaps you are right. The fine weather may do me good.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	290	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_no_hunt_choice_1d0c469e	doctor	I shall join you.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	290	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_no_hunt_choice_9db7d5fe	host	That is very good news.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	296	host "[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_nurse_b53490cb	doctor	Good morning, Miss Marsh.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	321	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_morning_nurse_3d009ecd	nurse	Good morning, Doctor.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	325	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day2_breakfast_follow_doctor_lad_remove_mask_a5c10d55		I can't ignore the signs. I need to see for myself.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	336	"[what]"
doctor_day2_breakfast_follow_doctor_lad_remove_mask_60d0289a		But I should be alone for this.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	336	"[what]"
doctor_day2_breakfast_follow_doctor_lad_remove_mask_f76fc263	doctor	Thank you for your help, Mr Harring.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	342	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_breakfast_follow_doctor_lad_remove_mask_1e51ae4b	doctor	I need to examine Thomas Moody's face now.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	342	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_breakfast_follow_doctor_lad_remove_mask_d62583ec	doctor	Would you step outside?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	342	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_breakfast_follow_doctor_lad_remove_mask_c50302e8	lad	Of course.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	350	lad "[what]"
doctor_day2_breakfast_follow_doctor_lad_remove_mask_5fdf9510		Once I'm sure the room is empty, I remove the mask.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	354	"[what]"
doctor_day2_breakfast_follow_doctor_lad_remove_mask_f909b257		Ted Harring is waiting in the hallway.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	362	"[what]"
doctor_day2_behind_the_mask_31a5ea1c		His face is twisted in a horrible grimace.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	373	"[what]"
doctor_day2_behind_the_mask_7017457b		This is not the face of someone dying peacefully in his sleep.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	373	"[what]"
doctor_day2_behind_the_mask_b0779427		It suggests distress in his final moments.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	373	"[what]"
doctor_day2_behind_the_mask_ff7bb6cc		Yet that does not prove it was not a natural death.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	373	"[what]"
doctor_day2_behind_the_mask_4438b7f7		It could have been a violent heart attack.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	373	"[what]"
doctor_day2_behind_the_mask_b24b4cc1		But then, something strikes me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	373	"[what]"
doctor_day2_behind_the_mask_6e6afd4a		I should have noticed it at once.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	373	"[what]"
doctor_day2_behind_the_mask_9586d30b		No disfigurement. No scars.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	373	"[what]"
doctor_day2_behind_the_mask_6ee7f518		His face is untouched.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	373	"[what]"
doctor_day2_behind_the_mask_27bb9726		He never needed a mask.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	373	"[what]"
doctor_day2_behind_the_mask_c1aba2f1		What does that mean?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	373	"[what]"
doctor_day2_behind_the_mask_cef14b8e		I pause, trying to make sense of it.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	401	"[what]"
doctor_day2_behind_the_mask_5d0402d4		There are too many questions at once.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	401	"[what]"
doctor_day2_behind_the_mask_57a9de83		Thomas Moody is dead, and I cannot yet say how it happened.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	401	"[what]"
doctor_day2_behind_the_mask_c7451287		It may have been deliberate.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	401	"[what]"
doctor_day2_behind_the_mask_a04fed43		It may have been an accident.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	401	"[what]"
doctor_day2_behind_the_mask_ad504c25		But what troubles me most is that he chose to hide behind a mask.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	401	"[what]"
doctor_day2_behind_the_mask_594b60d9		I cannot think of a logical explanation for it.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	401	"[what]"
doctor_day2_behind_the_mask_3664f3dc		I should keep this to myself for now.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	401	"[what]"
doctor_day2_behind_the_mask_c1c20dca		I do not feel comfortable sharing it with everyone just yet.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	401	"[what]"
doctor_day2_behind_the_mask_d88fc84d		Not until I know who I can trust.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	401	"[what]"
doctor_day2_behind_the_mask_2c0c6fa1		I replace the mask and leave the room.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	401	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_feeba281		As I had no reason to remain behind, I changed for the hunt.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	30	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_131245fd		Fortunately, I had thought to bring more suitable outdoor clothes for the weekend.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	30	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_834e5b97		It was not difficult to imagine that a hunt would be on the agenda.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	30	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_3c6980ef		Lady Claythorn may pretend it is arranged for our benefit, yet I suspect she will enjoy it most of all.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	30	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_6408ce33		She might even have planned the entire weekend simply for the pleasure of today's event.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	30	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_6b4c006c		After all, I doubt she can readily find hunting partners in so isolated a place.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	30	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_8be3d935		In any case, the butler has provided me with a hunting rifle.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	30	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_22191561		It has been some time since I last handled one, yet I dare say I will remember how to use it.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	30	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_f29cf66c		I step outside to join the others.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	30	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_8ed0e6c4		To my surprise, Samuel Manning is there as well.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	30	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_5e55cfb9		I must watch him carefully.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	54	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_cd3f4ea8		However drunk he appeared this morning, it does not mean he is any less dangerous.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	54	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_3b2ce31e		I can only hope he has sobered up.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	62	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_201d178b		I notice the butler walking just behind Lady Claythorn.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	66	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_7a071d13		Andrew is there too.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	72	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_3cf67f4f		The footman is there as well.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	78	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_72d3ea17		He is attending to Ted Harring, who looks somewhat out of place.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	82	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_5c89e972		The butler clears his throat and addresses us.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	82	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_fdd2cf09		I have barely a moment to gather my thoughts before Samuel Manning is upon me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	90	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_3c409755	drunk	Doctor, I would be honoured to partner with you.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	94	drunk "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_43b993aa	drunk	You don't mind, do you?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	94	drunk "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_d9cc6119		He is too eager to join me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	102	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_1e804dcc		It may mean he is ready to make good on his threat.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	102	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_440cb9b0		I am anxious, yet also curious.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	102	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_ff92da26		I cannot back out now.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	102	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_82ee798a	doctor	No, of course. We may go together.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	112	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_1719d099		I cannot find the words to politely refuse him.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	118	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_49ca4043	doctor	Well... no, of course not.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	122	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_40e580ac	drunk	Splendid!	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	126	drunk "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_0dd22886	drunk	We shall have a jolly time.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	126	drunk "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_7a468fe4	lad	You don't mind if I tag along as well, do you?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	132	lad "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_f90314e5		Andrew stands at his side and gives me a meaningful look.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	138	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_e0fa7bb7	doctor	Of course not.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	142	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_d3d3e965	doctor	Do come with us, Mr Harring.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	142	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_ded26b58	butler	Excellent.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	148	butler "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_dfb9b20a	butler	The parties are settled.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	148	butler "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_9dbc3bf1	butler	Let us have a pleasant afternoon.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/1_main.rpy	148	butler "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_3a0704b3		Our little group made its way into the forest.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	10	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_65075f38		We walked for a while yet encountered nothing.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	10	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_520cae1d		So we stopped for luncheon.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	10	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_c0e4fe58		I should like to speak further with Andrew, but he is exceedingly cautious and professional.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	20	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_95529b15		He does not respond to any of my meaningful looks.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	20	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_afa7b44a		I understand only too well that there is no sense in risking discovery here.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	20	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_14fb8f39		With luck, I shall see more of him later.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	20	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_eee629bd		The footman is exceedingly professional and remains silent whilst preparing our food.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	32	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_f25169d7		If Samuel Manning seemed somewhat sobered at first, he now appears intent on making up for lost drinking.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	36	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_3dd98303		He has a flask which I assume is whisky, and he has been drinking from it non-stop since the start of the hunt.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	36	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_5d5ba578		If I trust the content of the letter, he looks like he is summoning the courage to do something terrible.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	44	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_665a8cbd		I feel like I should talk to him before he is too drunk.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	44	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_b36daddd		On the other hand, it could be prudent to wait for a better time.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	44	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_4c84cc85		If I am on my guard, I could probably avoid him until the hunt is over.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	44	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_35bfd098		I am concerned he is in no condition to handle a gun.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	64	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_a15a4475		He mutters to himself and I have no wish to engage him.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	64	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_f2ebd7ff		Only Ted Harring is willing to make conversation, so I address him.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	64	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_74bf26b3		As I did this morning, I take care to keep Samuel Manning within my line of sight.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	81	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_25f5fc6f		At first, it seems the afternoon will be as uneventful as the morning.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	86	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_b87f2cc0		I walk on mechanically, without thinking.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	86	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_13010ae6		Finding an animal to shoot is far from my mind.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	86	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_86fef780		The fact is that I have begun to notice the first symptoms of withdrawal.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	97	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_f78e1e49		I am sweating profusely, I have cramps, and my hands have begun to tremble.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	97	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_3d3364c0		Hardly ideal for holding a gun.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	97	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_2f692f2e		I knew this was coming, and I am worried now.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	97	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_62895014		From what I have seen in my patients, it will not be easy to manage.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	97	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_81770c61		I hope I can govern it well enough that no one notices.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	97	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_7349e2c9		Despite my caution, my gaze is drawn again and again to Andrew, looking rather dashing in his footman's livery.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	113	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_05acd577		I wonder if we shall see one another tonight.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	113	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_f3a9a6c7		I regret not taking my "medicine" with me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	122	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_fbd28198		All I can think about is when I shall be alone in my room again.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	122	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_6421295d		I hope we shall not hunt for much longer.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	122	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_bbfffb53		I am lost in my thoughts when I hear Samuel Manning shout.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	132	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_560011e9		Damn it, for a moment I have let him out of my sight.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	132	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_858af6aa		I am roused from my stupor by Samuel Manning.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	141	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_ef5724c8		Very quickly I start to enjoy the familiar feeling of calm.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	149	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_0441703d		It won't be long now.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	149	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_08e0bd75		Ironically, I truly believe I would have managed to quit this time.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	157	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_d41be79c		Ironically, this is likely how I was meant to go anyway.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	163	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_lad_conversation_044ccf17	doctor	How are you getting on Mr Harring?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	172	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_lad_conversation_692de59a	lad	Very well Doctor.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	176	lad "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_lad_conversation_a60ec41e		Well, that was hardly the most stimulating conversation.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	188	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_lad_conversation_18a9d7c2		Still, I suppose we're ready to keep going with the hunt.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	188	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_lad_conversation_080afc29		After a short while, we're ready to keep going with the hunt.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	196	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_0e295a49		I summon the courage to go and speak to Samuel Manning.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	207	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_59443129		Ted Harring does not follow me, he probably wants nothing to do with him.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	207	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_884b4436	doctor	Mr Manning?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	213	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_be77712e		He looks bewildered that I am addressing him.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	217	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_485067b6	drunk	Hum... yes?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	221	drunk "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_8a0c63f1	doctor	I was wondering if we could talk alone for a moment.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	225	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_203f2e8c	doctor	I have rather a sensitive subject to broach with you.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	225	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_7324f1bb	drunk	Well, hum... yes, I suppose we could, of course.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	231	drunk "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_ce89efa3	doctor	Very well, if you would come this way.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	235	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_f560a8a6	drunk	Fine.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	239	drunk "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_84bfd813		I move a few paces from our luncheon place, far enough to be out of earshot.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	243	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_07fb182d		But close enough that, if something happens, they can join us quickly.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	243	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_e186e7c6	doctor	Here is perfect, Mr Manning.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	249	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_e3f672ed	drunk	All right, what is it, doctor?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	253	drunk "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_3f3ecb20		I see no reason to beat about the bush.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	257	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_fb5a7461	doctor	It is about the letter I found in your room, the one where you wrote that "I must pay".	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	261	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_3fbdbc08		This confession seems to take him by surprise.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	265	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_72bc49d5		But he quickly regains his composure, and speaks in a more assertive tone.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	265	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_0fa23770		Any trace of intoxication is gone from his face.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	265	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_65473ac4		He was likely faking it.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	265	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_914e3e4b		I should have guessed.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	265	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_da4ee6d6	drunk	What were you doing in my room?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	279	drunk "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_92c59104	drunk	Who gave you permission?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	279	drunk "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_34c34376	drunk	But I should not be surprised, doctors do as they please.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	279	drunk "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_8ff19f2d	drunk	They always do.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	279	drunk "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_4333a46c	doctor	That is not the point, you wrote that you wanted to hurt me, and I am not even certain I know why.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	289	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_1fd1b5ae		My words strike him strongly, and he answers in anger.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	293	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_7f594ca9	drunk	You do not know why?!!!	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	297	drunk "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_8a95e3af	drunk	I thought it was clear enough!	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	297	drunk "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_4ee18d7a	drunk	You killed her.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	297	drunk "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_8a004263	drunk	My poor Margaret.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	297	drunk "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_c5ccc71d	drunk	My God, you stood by her bedside and watched her slip away.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	297	drunk "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_8948cb6e	drunk	And now you come here as though nothing happened, you probably do not even remember, do you?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	297	drunk "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_7ed8776d	drunk	Is it because you killed so many of them?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	297	drunk "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_4c5b3459		I am dumbstruck, I cannot find the right words to say.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	313	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_56d2243c		Samuel Manning raises his gun and points it at me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	313	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_50b3158d	doctor	Lower the weapon, Mr Manning.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	319	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_afaa9569	doctor	It's a misunderstanding, someone is manipulating you.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	319	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_691673c9	doctor	They want you to do this.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	319	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_1516056a	drunk	Well, that is all right, because I want to do it too.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	327	drunk "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_b49c6047		He is about to shoot, so I jump towards him.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	331	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_fe461a0e		He misses me and I am on him.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	337	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_79c801eb		We struggle.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	337	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_4fc55ba9		I grab his rifle and try to wrestle it out of his arms.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	337	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_d6de9cc8		For a moment everything is silent, until I feel the weight of Samuel Manning against me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	349	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_82eea8a3		I push him and he collapses at my feet.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	349	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_f70312b1		The rifle lies beside him.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	349	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_f3bb9891		I kneel at once, though a single glance tells me the truth.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	349	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_664c69f2		He has shot himself in the chest during the fight.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	349	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_1c244619	doctor	Dear God.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	361	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_confront_drunk_2034d137	doctor	What have I done.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	361	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_death_not_careful_2a3ecf9f		I am lost in my thoughts when I a hear the voice of Samuel Manning shouting.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	375	"[what]"
doctor_day2_hunt_accident_death_not_careful_89600e2f		For a second I have forgotten to watch him.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/2_Hunt/2_accident.rpy	375	"[what]"
doctor_downstairs_day2_evening_4bb1e64a		I am about to go downstairs when someone stops me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	82	"[what]"
doctor_downstairs_day2_evening_22bfd17d	maid	Good evening, sir.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	86	maid "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_day2_evening_662b8420	maid	May I help you?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	86	maid "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_day2_evening_34436add	doctor	Well, perhaps.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	94	doctor "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_day2_evening_b9e6fcc8	doctor	I am looking for someone.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	94	doctor "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_day2_evening_59302c1f	doctor	I would like to have a word with your footman.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	94	doctor "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_day2_evening_e1d8d953	doctor	I believe he is called Andrew.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	94	doctor "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_day2_evening_7dd69786	maid	I am sorry, sir, but Andrew is not here any longer.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	104	maid "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_day2_evening_65d2967c	maid	I believe you will find him in his room.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	104	maid "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_day2_evening_8eb0fa79	doctor	Very good.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	110	doctor "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_day2_evening_55eda57b	doctor	And where is that, exactly?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	110	doctor "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_day2_evening_6a552c9b	maid	In the attic, sir.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	116	maid "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_day2_evening_92436f41	maid	The first room to your left after the stairs.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	116	maid "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_day2_evening_35d4a5af	doctor	Perfect, thank you.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	122	doctor "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_day2_evening_8cf6d994	doctor	I was just hoping to have a look downstairs, if you do not mind.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	130	doctor "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_day2_evening_97cc82fb	maid	I am sorry, sir, but Lady Claythorn left very strict instructions.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	134	maid "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_day2_evening_f07e15ef	maid	No guest is to be allowed downstairs.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	134	maid "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_day2_evening_cd8e951b	maid	You may freely visit the rest of the manor, of course.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	134	maid "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_day2_evening_83c08b56	doctor	I understand.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	142	doctor "[what]"
doctor_downstairs_day2_evening_5c699d13		Specific instructions forbidding guests to go downstairs do not sit well with me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	146	"[what]"
doctor_downstairs_day2_evening_f0a90b0d		Still, I do not wish to risk alienating our hostess by forcing my way there.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	146	"[what]"
doctor_downstairs_day2_evening_171c80fa		I shall avoid the downstairs rooms, for the moment.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	146	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_library_efec7492		The library.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	162	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_library_663e46aa		At another time I would gladly have taken a book and settled in to read.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	162	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_library_ed028d0c		Tonight however, I feel it is too dangerous to waste time reading.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	162	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_library_2e41be87		I should look elsewhere.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	162	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_garden_fe4987c2		I walk to the door that opens on to the garden.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	189	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_garden_91fa5224		When I pull it ajar, I find nothing but a wall of darkness beyond.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	189	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_garden_e5dddcb7		It would be far too dangerous to waste time out there at this hour.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	189	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_garden_9491cb9a		I should turn my attention somewhere else.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	189	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_closed_0089a38e		I could try to enter but they might be there and not want to answer.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	218	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_closed_e2619e7b		So I would look too suspicious now, I should just try somewhere else.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	218	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_closed_1cbc148d		Nobody is here either.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	226	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_closed_61f6cbcf		I should move on.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	226	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_psychic_a6e5bd60		She must be wary of speaking with me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	255	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_psychic_aa36559a		I cannot blame her.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	255	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_psychic_e9722f75		After all that has happened, she has little reason to place her trust in me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	255	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_7cbf8a1e		I am still in shock when we reach the mansion.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	30	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_d592c827		I can scarcely recall what happened in the woods.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	30	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_1b7d8c18		Samuel Manning bled to death whilst I tried to save him.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	30	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_2ee92d38		The other group, drawn by the noise, rejoined us to witness the horrific scene.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	30	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bf419a59		Once it was clear the poor man was dead, Captain Sinha took charge and had us carry Samuel Manning back to the house.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	30	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_811c931e		I still can hardly believe it.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	30	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_288040cf		I have killed a man.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	30	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_aa8af1e3		I cannot seem to convince myself that it was him or me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	30	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_5a117000		Yet I must not waste time dwelling on it.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	30	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_141e4d40		The others will have questions.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	30	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_be5add13		I must think very carefully about what I am going to say to them.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	30	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_c363a6b5		As we enter, we are greeted by Rosalind Marsh and Amelia Baxter.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	30	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_83c14e98	psychic	Oh my God! What happened?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	56	psychic surprised "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_49f7418a	psychic	Is that Samuel Manning? Is he injured?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	56	psychic surprised "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_0bfdae88	psychic	Oh no. Is he... dead?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	56	psychic surprised "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_7372e922	captain	I am sorry, my dear, but he is.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	64	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_2ce6f188	psychic	But... what happened?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	68	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bfc01660	captain	It was an accident.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	72	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_6618077e	captain	He got into a fight with Doctor Baldwin.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	72	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_0d5c2cbc	captain	And he accidentally shot himself.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	72	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_9cb26c68	psychic	How terrible. What was the quarrel about, Doctor?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	80	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_07183a25		All eyes turn to me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	84	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_b6eb5a93		I am back in my room, shaken by a wretched mix of nervousness and remorse.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	101	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_7ecbeb8a		I pace the room, my hands still trembling.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	107	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_7509ab50		The urge to reach for my laudanum is almost overwhelming.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	107	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_69e327fa		Yet the words from that book I read yesterday return to me with cruel clarity.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	107	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_c5dd41db		I have been poisoning myself for years.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	107	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_5e0f1736		If I go on like this, I shall end as helpless as any of my poorest patients.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	107	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_b306c20a		With a sudden surge of resolve, I open my bag and look down at the familiar little vials.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	107	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_3591ddef		For a long moment I merely stare at them.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	107	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_fbb7582b		Then I close the bag again, leaving them untouched.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	107	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_68bbb75c		I will endure the shaking and the sleeplessness if I must.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	107	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_2c0beda2		Better a clear mind and a fighting chance than a drugged stupor in this house.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	107	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_de4ddf1e		My first impulse is to seek relief in the usual way.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	131	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_98eba14f		I even reach for my bag before I stop myself.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	131	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_ea25a016		I think of the letter I found in Samuel Manning's room.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	131	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_c67659cc		The image of Thomas Moody without his mask also appears in my mind.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	141	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_07d2187d		That's another thing I can't make sense of.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	141	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_212057b5		All of this is too strange, as though I had stepped into the pages of a mystery novel.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	147	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_cb1210b9		It is plain that someone in this house is hiding something.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	147	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_78c0bc8c		If I dull my senses now, I might miss some vital clue, or fail to react when danger comes.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	147	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_61b07576		I draw my hand back from the bag and clench it into a fist.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	147	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_89460c68		No, I must keep my wits about me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	147	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_ae1a068b		Until I know whom I may trust, I shall remain sober.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	147	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_042a9873		I rest for a while, until the familiar sound of the gong draws me out of my thoughts.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	165	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_e3dda7b3		I suppose I am steady enough to join the others for dinner.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	171	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bc0d4e1f		It seems as though everyone turns to look at me as I enter the room.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	177	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_3cd96bfc		Glances and stares follow me to my seat.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	177	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_f62412f0		When all are present, Lady Claythorn begins to speak.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	177	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_b8d3e129		That is a considerable relief.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	187	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_12f11e58		I just need to make it through one more night and a single morning, then I shall be able to leave this place.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	187	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_3083bfaf		No doubt I shall have to give an account of myself to the police before I go, yet from what I understand it should be little more than a formality.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	187	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_f8ee588a		I turn to my left. Ted Harring is looking rather downcast.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	187	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_0c49d357		Opposite me, Rosalind Marsh now sits alone.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	187	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_4d7397ec		She has kept to her usual seat, though there is no one beside her any longer.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	187	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_c8e3a103		Should I speak to either of them, or remain silent as most of the table seems determined to do?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	187	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_2e515e8a		The dinner is over.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	212	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_046d1203		It seemed longer than usual, for there was scarcely any conversation at all.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	212	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_30a882ad		Like most of the other guests, I retire to my room.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	212	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_reason_silence_023ccd50		I try to think of something to say, yet I am at a loss for words.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	227	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_reason_silence_afb53ed4		My mind feels quite empty.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	227	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_reason_silence_e1bd2f54		Everyone is looking at me with concern.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	227	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_reason_silence_2572c303	captain	There is no need to answer, Doctor.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	235	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_reason_silence_2c677d0c	captain	I am sure it was all a misunderstanding.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	235	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_reason_silence_4f3e821b	captain	It is quite obvious what happened.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	235	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_reason_drunk_a93c32e4	doctor	I have no idea what he was angry about.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	250	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_reason_drunk_6dbcbee5	doctor	I only wished to speak to him about his drinking, and he lost his temper with me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	250	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_reason_drunk_68d1e8a4	doctor	He was not making any sense, then he pointed his gun at me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	250	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_reason_drunk_8e793670	doctor	Without thinking, I tried to jump him and wrest the weapon away, but, but...	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	250	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_reason_drunk_silent_20d56b29	captain	The poor man shot himself by accident.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	267	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_reason_drunk_silent_f361a956	captain	I cannot say I am surprised, I think we all noticed his state of inebriation today and yesterday.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	267	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_reason_drunk_silent_18aa0652	captain	Samuel Manning clearly had troubles he could not master.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	267	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_reason_drunk_silent_0f08a4a1	captain	There is no reason to blame yourself, Doctor.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	267	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_reason_drunk_silent_ab30f4ed	psychic	Of course, we are all quite certain you only wished to help that poor soul.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	277	psychic -surprised "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_reason_drunk_silent_2e798f43		I hear a murmur of assent from everyone.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	281	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_reason_drunk_silent_ab1eacfb		They will not suspect a thing.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	281	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_reason_drunk_silent_55b693b8		It is true that most people will believe a doctor without a second thought.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	281	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_reason_drunk_silent_cc84bd43	doctor	Thank you, everyone.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	289	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_reason_drunk_silent_80f302bc	doctor	It has been a horrific experience.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	289	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_reason_drunk_silent_1801bf50	doctor	If you do not mind, I think I shall retire to my room now.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	289	doctor "[what]"
