doctor_day2_evening_males_room_do_no_enter_d50d780d	doctor	It is Doctor Baldwin.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	22	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_do_no_enter_11d9cae3	footman	Oh.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	26	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_do_no_enter_b78b20d8	footman	What can I do for you, doctor?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	26	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_do_no_enter_b54bf4cf	doctor	Well... I am not entirely sure.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	32	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_do_no_enter_a2596ee5	doctor	I was merely exploring, and wondered what was in the attic.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	32	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_do_no_enter_64dec7da	footman	I do not think you are supposed to be here, doctor.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	38	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_do_no_enter_f621cdcb	footman	This is the servants quarters.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	38	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_do_no_enter_98aae4b4	footman	I was about to go to bed myself, as I have to be up early tomorrow.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	38	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_do_no_enter_175e78f5	doctor	Of course, my apologies for disturbing you.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	46	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_do_no_enter_c44e02e5	doctor	Good night.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	46	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_do_no_enter_cdfdc6c7	footman	Goodnight, sir.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	52	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_do_no_enter_2851d449		Well, that was rather embarrassing.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	56	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_do_no_enter_4c4b7b1d		That is what happens when one wanders about a house without a clear purpose, I suppose.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	56	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_f3316e3e		I answer in a whisper.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	69	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_5e221aee	doctor	Andrew, it is me, Daniel.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	73	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_8ba2e562	footman	Doctor?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	77	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_b84a53e1	footman	You should not be here.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	77	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_ab7ce251	footman	Tonight is not the best time, with... everything that has happened.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	77	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_6a539ab7	doctor	I am well aware.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	85	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_6895daa3	doctor	But I sincerely hope you do not hold me responsible for today's accident.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	85	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_24fc6bda		He pauses for a second before answering.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	91	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_dad7b707	footman	No, of course not.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	95	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_d3fd152e	footman	I am sure it was only a terrible mistake.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	95	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_5c401c7d		There is a pause, then the soft sound of the bolt sliding back.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	101	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_3b4b5ee5		The door opens just enough for me to slip inside.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	101	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_134cc5fc		He closes it carefully behind me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	101	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_1bc8f99b		Words quickly become unnecessary.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	101	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_bf8f7b5b		In a moment we are both on his bed, our clothes discarded on the floor.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	101	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_fd831379		When it is over, reality returns far too quickly.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	115	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_50223ee1	footman	I think you should go back to your room now.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	119	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_d17c4de8	doctor	Already?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	123	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_7ca5f75c	doctor	I was hoping to stay here for the night.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	123	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_26af14d4	footman	I do not think that would be prudent.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	129	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_af908bb7	footman	People might see you in the morning.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	129	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_991d6fdc	doctor	I could rise early and leave before anyone is awake.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	135	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_23c43e0e	footman	I am not certain you could.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	139	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_d4dcd585	footman	Servants are usually up when you would still think it the middle of the night.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	139	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_2d48ff07	footman	I would rather not take that risk.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	139	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_aa68d42c	footman	Besides, in only a few hours I have an errand to run.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	139	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_f1e66f98	doctor	So early?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	149	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_73601c1c	doctor	Why on earth do you have to do that?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	149	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_f9974796	footman	I am sorry, I cannot say.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	155	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_48afb2b8	footman	It is an order from Lady Claythorn.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	155	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_3873f588		I glance towards the small window.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	161	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_9da7d08d		The wind has picked up, and distant thunder rolls across the moor.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	161	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_25b25e8e	doctor	It does look as though it may rain again.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	167	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_d8b79c36	doctor	You will catch your death if you stay outside too long.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	167	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_cf8b0b7f	footman	Do not worry, I shall be taking the car.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	173	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_14f8683a	footman	And besides, I am not made out of sugar.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	173	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_84aee187		The expression strikes me as oddly familiar, and somewhat out of place.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	179	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_90f5b86a	doctor	That is a curious turn of phrase.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	183	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_27e1c1d3	doctor	And yesterday, I recall you mentioning something about whipping cats.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	183	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_8eb9992f	doctor	That was even more peculiar.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	183	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_fb85b58b	doctor	Where did you learn such expressions?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	183	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_7bb8b95a	footman	Hm.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	193	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_4f8cb5e7	footman	You have truly never heard them before?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	193	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_aa645364	footman	I suppose I got them from my grandmother.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	193	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_f17e7cd1	footman	We are from the North, near Sunderland.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	193	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_8b8b2982	footman	People there have rather strange sayings, you know.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	193	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_5ac5204f	doctor	I am aware of that.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	205	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_2cc92bdb	doctor	I have family from that region myself.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	205	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_c470eb30	doctor	Yet I have never heard those expressions.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	205	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_662ff8b6		He looks embarrassed.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	213	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_7cf5a8a8	footman	Well.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	217	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_8ed3fcbc	footman	I might as well tell you.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	217	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_33d0e68d	footman	There is no point in keeping this for myself.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	217	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_c27d574f	footman	I am not British.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	217	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_83a00f01	footman	I was brought here as a young teen, so you would not hear it in my accent.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	217	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_202a3145	footman	But those are French expressions my parents used often.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	217	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_6223e6c5	footman	I suppose I translated them without realising they might not exist in the King's English.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	217	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_60ba5e84	doctor	You are French?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	233	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_1c4ee391	doctor	How interesting.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	233	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_09ad64bb	doctor	But why keep it a secret?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	233	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_8cb15024	footman	I am not bloody French.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	241	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_bbffcd19	footman	People always assume that.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	241	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_1d83b966	footman	I am Belgian, from a French speaking family.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	241	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_c9b5288c	doctor	I see.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	249	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_40f5eb8c	doctor	My apologies.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	249	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_ba6aee5e	doctor	Still, why hide it?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	249	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_261c34b3	footman	Because I am not meant to be here.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	257	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_e83c32aa	footman	My parents were war refugees.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	257	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_a234bc5e	footman	They worked in a weapons factory during the war, in a small northern village called Birtley.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	257	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_96eb812b	footman	When the war ended, we were supposed to return to Belgium.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	257	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_a343147d	footman	But I had spent my teenage years here.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	267	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_2f04b6b4	footman	I did not want to go back.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	267	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_95762101	footman	I was seventeen, and I was in love.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	267	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_18c1bb4d	footman	I could not bear to leave him behind.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	267	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_d3676cce	footman	So I pretended to be British.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	267	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_190b7918	footman	My English was good enough not to raise suspicion.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	267	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_33179420	footman	Ever since, I have hidden my true identity.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	267	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_0ce639f5	footman	That is why I became an actor.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	267	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_f55880b9	footman	And...	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	267	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_e2038c60		He stops short.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	287	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_a00dd6b0		That is information I was not meant to hear.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	287	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_e04b620c	doctor	You are an actor?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	293	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_acdb89ab	doctor	Then what are you doing here, in the middle of the woods?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	293	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_8817c989	doctor	There cannot be many roles for you in a place like this.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	293	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_dad7b707_1	footman	No, of course not.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	301	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_52beed1f	footman	But one must earn a living.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	301	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_ce9fe6fc	footman	Acting is not a secure profession.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	301	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_ad95c81b	footman	I take odd jobs when I must.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	301	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_ea6b9d10	footman	I was never meant to stay in this manor for long.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	301	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_c950d97e	footman	Just long enough to get back on my feet.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	301	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_057c31a8	footman	But it is late now.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	301	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_70bfd9ee	footman	I have spoken far too much about myself.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	301	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_b55ae363	footman	I need my rest for tomorrow.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	301	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_736bc251	footman	You should go now, Doctor.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	301	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_a85c7eaf	footman	Before we are both discovered.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	301	footman "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_907a02d7		The dismissal is abrupt.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	325	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_79a686d2		Nevertheless, I nod reluctantly.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	325	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_1ddfbd13	doctor	If you insist, I shall be on my way.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	331	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_53120bbf		I dress in silence.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	335	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_36277fe8		Then he opens the door just enough for me to slip back into the corridor.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	335	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_males_room_enter_9faf5fdd		The bolt slides shut behind me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_attic.rpy	335	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_default_c091f2f0	doctor	Hello?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	8	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_default_4a921aa7	nurse	Yes?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	12	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_default_53e0afce	nurse	Is that you Doctor Baldwin?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	12	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_default_daa5f45e	doctor	Yes, it is.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	18	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_default_651cc88f	doctor	Do you mind if I come in for a minute?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	18	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_default_c99b3001	doctor	I have something important to discuss.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	18	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_default_76f5a8b7	nurse	I do not know, Doctor.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	26	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_default_884c82ed	nurse	It is late, and that would be rather inappropriate.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	26	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_default_e73b2c86	nurse	Also, with everything that has happened today, I would prefer to stay alone.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	26	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_default_4b86ba43	nurse	I hope you understand.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	26	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_do_not_remember_941582c9		She is right.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	43	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_do_not_remember_7ebf3402		I cannot simply insist upon entering the room of a woman I scarcely know at this hour.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	43	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_do_not_remember_f37e7bf2		I should not press the matter.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	43	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_do_not_remember_9d28e16b	doctor	My apologies for disturbing you.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	51	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_do_not_remember_87632eeb	doctor	I shall leave you in peace, Miss Marsh.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	51	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_do_not_remember_c44e02e5	doctor	Good night.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	51	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_do_not_remember_9ad8d92c	nurse	Good night, Doctor.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	59	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_remember_b86ccc94	doctor	I do understand, believe me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	70	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_remember_6783b8e9	doctor	Yet, as you reminded me earlier, you and I have worked side by side in far less proper circumstances than this.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	70	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_remember_24e23885	doctor	I would not trouble you now without very good reason.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	70	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_remember_57aabde8		There is a brief pause.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	78	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_remember_3137368d		I hear the soft creak of a floorboard, as if she has stepped closer to the door.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	78	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_remember_831eaa44	nurse	Very well, what is it then?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	84	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_remember_7de3c2cd	doctor	It is not something I care to discuss in the hallway.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	88	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_remember_0d59b7e1	doctor	May I come in, just for a moment?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	88	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_remember_aa091760		For a few seconds there is only silence, and the faint crackle of a fire from within her room.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	94	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_remember_406a131e	nurse	All right.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	98	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_remember_186f66b8	nurse	Please come in, Doctor.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	98	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_remember_5dc44673		I step into Miss Marsh's room.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	108	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_remember_7268db7c		She has not yet undressed, but her shoulders sag with weariness, and there are dark shadows beneath her eyes.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	108	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_remember_42e5e9fe	doctor	Thank you.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	114	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_remember_e9c20dc2	doctor	I shall be as brief as I can.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	114	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_remember_0b2bec33		I give her a concise account of the letter I discovered in Samuel Manning's room.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	120	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_remember_46d45e92		Then I explain how it urged him to provoke me before the hunt, and how it led, step by step, to his death.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	120	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_remember_5ef3e5b6		As I speak, the colour drains from her face.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	120	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_remember_e9f3c334	nurse	Good heavens.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	128	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_remember_90630083	nurse	Are you saying someone lured you both into that situation on purpose?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	128	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_remember_ce166ee3	doctor	That is precisely what I fear.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	134	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_remember_4b7a51d6	doctor	Whoever wrote that letter knew far too much, and I doubt they are finished.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	134	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_remember_b0f8b49f	doctor	I believe they may try again, with me or with someone else in this house.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	134	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_remember_7dee0073	nurse	And you came to me because we worked together before?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	142	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_remember_a4fd652b	nurse	Because you think you can trust me?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	142	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_remember_7494ab9c	doctor	Indeed, I would rather face this night with an ally than entirely alone.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	148	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_remember_535dd8d3	nurse	I cannot pretend I am not frightened.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	152	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_remember_90c9d129	nurse	Every sound in this place sets my nerves on edge.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	152	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_remember_f50b0de5	nurse	I am thinking, to be perfectly safe maybe you could ...	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	152	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_remember_422018ab	nurse	No, never mind, it's probably not a good idea.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	152	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_remember_2d819deb	doctor	What could be? In these circumstances, we shouldn't be afraid to share what we think.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	162	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_remember_0bbd42b1	nurse	All right then, I meant that , if we really are in danger, you should probably ... sleep here tonight.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	166	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_remember_eada773f	nurse	Not on the bed I mean, maybe on a chair.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	166	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_remember_81c52b08	nurse	I know it's very unconventional, but that would make me feel better.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	166	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_yes_60866fce	doctor	Very well.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	185	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_yes_6b23cec3	doctor	If you will permit it, I shall take that chair by the door.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	185	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_yes_2324d36a	doctor	You may lie down and try to sleep, and I shall keep watch.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	185	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_yes_ccf7de48	nurse	Thank you, Doctor.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	193	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_yes_710fa5a4	nurse	I confess I shall feel safer knowing you are here.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	193	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_yes_345b5d3f	nurse	And I am sorry if I am not good company, but I imagine I shall be asleep in a few moments.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	193	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_yes_e878e42d	doctor	No worries, please rest.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	201	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_yes_c3fddb54		I move a straight-backed chair to a position where I can see both the door and the window.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	205	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_yes_d325b136		Miss Marsh sits upon the edge of the bed, then lies down without undressing, her eyes already half closed.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	205	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_yes_50f09faf	nurse	Wake me if anything seems amiss.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	211	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_yes_8eb55b7d	nurse	Otherwise, let us hope the night passes quietly.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	211	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_yes_405528cd	doctor	You have my word.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	217	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_yes_b30226e3	doctor	Try to rest.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	217	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_yes_efc61e31		The fire burns low in the grate, filling the room with a dull orange glow.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	223	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_yes_3b0dab42		I settle into the chair, listening to the ticking of the clock, and the slow deepening of Miss Marsh's breathing as she drifts into sleep.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	223	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_yes_5b283d1e		Pretty soon it's my turn to doze off.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	223	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_yes_4a03607e		I am deep asleep when the door suddenly rattles.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	235	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_yes_2cf446ac		I blink myself awake and see Rosalind Marsh standing close to it, one hand still near the bolt.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	235	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_yes_3c15f7f8	doctor	Miss Marsh?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	241	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_yes_91b8aa2c	doctor	What are you doing?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	241	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_yes_5231586a	doctor	Are you going somewhere?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	241	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_yes_390bdfbc	nurse	Oh, of course not, Doctor.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	249	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_yes_e4a0ed49	nurse	I am afraid I am becoming rather paranoid.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	249	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_yes_d39e1b85	nurse	I only wanted to be certain the door was properly fastened.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	249	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_yes_3db8f16e	nurse	But it is, so I can return to bed now.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	249	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_yes_90d06219	nurse	I am sorry to have woken you.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	249	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_yes_80fc5eaf	doctor	Do not apologise.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	261	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_yes_1c9784bc	doctor	Try to get some rest.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	261	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_yes_ca180d70	doctor	Good night, Miss Marsh.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	261	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_yes_07dd38c0	nurse	Good night, Doctor Baldwin.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	269	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_yes_89161ccd		Strange.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	273	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_yes_714ebae4		Still, I cannot blame her for being on edge.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	273	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_no_7a607688	doctor	I am truly sorry but I don'think this would be right.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	286	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_no_b71b868c	doctor	I believe it would best if we sleep in our own bed tonight.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	286	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_no_71067b65	doctor	But we can convene first thing in the morning and get ready for whatever awaits us.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	286	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_no_a78a308f	nurse	As you wish, Doctor.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	294	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_no_a4e47a09	nurse	And... thank you for telling me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	294	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_no_d74ee99b	nurse	Whatever happens, I am glad you did not keep this to yourself.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	294	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_no_534eae91		I incline my head and step back into the corridor.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	302	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_no_6b98fabc		Miss Marsh follows me to the threshold and closes the door softly behind me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	302	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_sleep_no_7bdd2014		The hallway feels colder than before, and the silence of the sleeping house presses in on every side.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_bedroom_nurse.rpy	310	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_2b1a4817		Just as I imagined, the room is almost deserted.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	9	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_58ee495e		I can see only Captain Sinha seated upon a sofa, and the butler standing discreetly in the corner.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	9	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_1d8d06ac		The bar is still available, but I promised myself to keep a clear head, so I ought to avoid it.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	9	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_13c1e3d9		I find myself once more in the billiard room.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	27	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_bar_726ba820		In spite of knowing full well it is a mistake, my steps carry me straight to the bar.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	38	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_bar_3ed3fc48		Before I have quite registered it, I am already pouring myself a glass of sherry.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	38	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_bar_51b04d16		The moment I realise what I have done, a wave of shame washes over me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	38	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_bar_ef598117		Yet now that the glass is in my hand, I cannot simply set it aside.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	38	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_bar_e813d174		I might as well drink it.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	38	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_bar_3ea104b4		But this will be the last one.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	38	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_bar_31a9d6ed		At last, I have a chance to free myself from opium entirely.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	54	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_bar_1ee41032		I shouldn't exchange one addiction for another.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	54	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_852f1f2d		I go over to Captain Sinha.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	65	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_03580b51		He notices my approach and sets his book down upon the table.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	65	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_4bacaf42	captain	Doctor Baldwin, it is good to see you.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	71	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_ca04410a	captain	I fear most of the other guests have decided to remain in their rooms.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	71	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_f752cca3	doctor	Really?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	77	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_e4fd4e12	doctor	Why do you say that?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	77	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_368bc066	captain	I cannot be certain.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	83	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_dab3abe5	captain	But after what has happened today, I should not be surprised if some of our fellow guests are afraid to leave their rooms.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	83	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_ef9e03dc	doctor	What should they be afraid of?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	89	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_94545b34	captain	Well, nothing, of course.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	93	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_e9b5f5f4	captain	It is obvious to me that the two unhappy deaths this weekend were both tragic, but unfortunate events.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	93	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_456bd467	doctor	Yet you believe not everyone agrees with you.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	99	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_50650f9d	doctor	So they are afraid, but of what exactly?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	99	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_a00199c4	doctor	Ah.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	99	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_1e133e5b	doctor	I suppose they must be afraid of me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	99	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_9b097e26	doctor	And here I thought they had accepted that what occurred during the hunt was a dreadful accident.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	99	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_48ed870b	captain	I am sure they still think so, but they prefer to be cautious.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	111	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_72a4c760	captain	Most of them are not accustomed to being so close to death as you and I.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	111	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_795e73b3	doctor	Quite.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	117	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_456108a1	doctor	I had not considered it from that angle.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	117	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_2da97acb	captain	But tell me, was there something in particular you wished to speak to me about, Doctor?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	123	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_avoid_2febbe69	doctor	I am sorry for disturbing you but I don't really have anything else to say.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	140	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_avoid_59d5f454	doctor	I will leave you to your book.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	140	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_letter_c3c579ba	doctor	There is something I need to share with you.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	150	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_letter_2d332c3d	doctor	I have not been entirely honest about what happened before the hunt.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	150	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_letter_6512e773		I lower my voice and give him a brief account of the letter I found, and how it led to the quarrel with Samuel Manning and, in the end, to his death.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	156	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_letter_8a038505		The captain listens to it all without the slightest change in his expression.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	156	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_letter_2ff67572		When I have finished, he answers at last.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	156	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_letter_e2d54ccd	captain	I admit this is very strange.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	164	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_letter_ae524298	captain	But you must forgive me, I am not quite sure what to do with this information.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	164	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_letter_bc13a068	doctor	What do you mean?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	170	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_letter_d8b83418	doctor	This surely proves beyond doubt that something very wrong is happening here.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	170	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_letter_d3d242c9	doctor	I am telling you so that we may work together to discover what is truly going on.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	170	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_letter_87f4701c		Sushil Sinha studies me in silence for a moment.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	178	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_letter_499543b1	captain	I see.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	182	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_letter_0b5cd24f	captain	Do not take this the wrong way , Doctor, but I cannot simply accept your word on what you have just told me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	182	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_letter_d8ae0edd	captain	Do you have any proof of it?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	182	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_letter_15d65481	doctor	Not really.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	191	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_letter_e4b88ad2	doctor	I did not take the letter with me, that would have appeared far too suspicious.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	191	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_letter_0e3ed573	doctor	And I have been in Samuel Manning's room since.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	199	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_letter_38e26895	doctor	He burned the letter before leaving for the hunt.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	199	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_letter_38686208	captain	That's not ideal.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	205	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_letter_5690b080	captain	I do not say that I disbelieve you.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	205	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_letter_5fa39b83	captain	But put yourself in my place.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	205	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_letter_95bad82d	captain	If I were to accuse our hostess, or any of the guests, on this alone, I should be thought excitable at best, malicious at worst.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	205	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_letter_e1b5431c		He does not trust me, not entirely.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	215	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_letter_34a934d4		I understand.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	215	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_letter_c7d9ff07		In the end, I am the one who killed Samuel Manning, so to him I must be the most suspicious person in this house.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	215	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_letter_be689530		If I truly wish to convince him, I will need stronger evidence.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	215	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_67a9a1fe	doctor	There is indeed something else.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	230	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_56061d94	doctor	It concerns Thomas Moody.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	230	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_ecd003fe	captain	Moody?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	236	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_d6cd6483	captain	Did you discover something about his death?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	236	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_f9eacf96	doctor	Yes.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	242	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_4081d030	doctor	But I think it is best if you see for yourself, so that you don't need to take my word for it.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	242	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_3572902e	captain	Hm.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	248	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_845eafc5	captain	Very well, I suppose we could go to his room.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	248	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_69f44d17	captain	Please, lead the way, Doctor.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	248	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_ff8b12de		I see that he has no intention of turning his back on me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	256	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_37291fc0		We leave the billiard room together, moving as quietly as we can along the corridor.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	256	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_dc11c51a		The house feels oddly hollow, as though all life has retreated behind closed doors.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	256	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_2dcb6871		When we reach Thomas Moody's room, I open the door and step inside first.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	266	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_8798ef75	doctor	Here he is, Captain.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	270	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_21af6029	doctor	I must warn you, it may not be a pleasant sight.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	270	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_1112d001	captain	Do not trouble yourself, Doctor.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	276	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_4b433749	captain	I have seen the dead before.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	276	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_492205ec		He crosses to the bed and looks down at the still form, his expression grave but composed.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	282	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_54026573	captain	So, what is this about?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	286	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_5ad57b5b		I lay my hands upon Thomas Moody's mask and lift it away, revealing a contorted and intact face.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	290	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_ea80125f	captain	Good Lord, what a face he is making.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	294	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_ce26f6e6	captain	What could have caused that, Doctor?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	294	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_1da3a749	doctor	I am not certain, but it was no peaceful death, that much is clear.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	300	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_d06c3bf1	doctor	Yet you are not seeing the most peculiar part.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	300	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_c877391e	captain	What do you mean?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	306	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_598fc48f	captain	Oh.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	306	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_6390ab1d	captain	His face, it is... normal.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	306	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_3a6121f9	captain	He made everyone believe that he had been disfigured during the war.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	306	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_1a79fb83	captain	Yet it was all an act.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	306	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_24379b82	captain	But why would he do such a thing?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	306	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_14aeaa09	captain	What are we to make of this?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	306	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_4869ef5d	doctor	I have no idea.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	322	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_929f7597	doctor	It is suspicious enough that I did not wish to alert anyone else.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	322	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_7844e3cb	captain	I understand what you mean, Doctor.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	328	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_2e78a629	captain	Of course you were right, something is amiss.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	328	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_e6b3161e	captain	I cannot pretend any longer that these are merely unfortunate accidents.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	328	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_dc07e072		He pauses for a moment, pondering the implications of what he has just learnt.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	336	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_36f750d0		Then his gaze lingers on the nightstand.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	336	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_359734ed		Thomas Moody's hip flask lies on its side, a greenish liquid spilling from its mouth and pooling upon the wood.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	336	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_dfe5a532	captain	I assume our friend was drinking from this before he died.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	344	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_bfc0d4d1	captain	What kind of alcohol could that be?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	344	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_94ed3e87	captain	Crème de menthe, perhaps?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	344	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_a036806a		He picks up the flask and brings it to his nose.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	352	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_a00c2c1e	captain	How odd.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	356	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_222867fc	captain	That smells like whisky, heavily peated I might add.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	356	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_476986ba	captain	But why is there a green puddle on the nightstand?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	356	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_e5f4a4e1		Of course.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	364	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_f49d1cd1		I cannot believe I did not notice this before.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	364	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_ce7daa93	doctor	Do not drink it, Captain.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	370	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_ea63ccf9	doctor	I believe you may have found the murder weapon.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	370	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_d09c3bdb	captain	Ah, so this is the poison that caused Thomas Moody's premature death, you think?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	376	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_918ebb7c	doctor	Precisely.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	380	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_794fcee0	doctor	Everything points to a form of strychnine poisoning.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	380	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_4a51ad74	doctor	It is a common active ingredient in certain rat poisons.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	380	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_9f179d8b	doctor	That is probably what has given his whisky this greenish hue.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	380	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_499543b1	captain	I see.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	390	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_df4c84e2	captain	So we now have two deaths that are highly suspicious.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	390	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_61a6349d		He thinks for few seconds about what that implies.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	396	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_c6b18397		If someone in this house is prepared to kill once, perhaps even twice, there is no reason to imagine they will stop there.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	400	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_5dfe3da7		I believe we may both be in danger.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	400	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_077d39f3		I simply do not understand why.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	400	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_d2487c9f		Who could wish me dead?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	400	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_26ddb528		It is not as though I have no enemies, but nothing so severe that it ought to come to this.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	400	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_f6b4ae0d		At least, I do not think so.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	400	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_102c7266		What about you?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	400	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_142b8e48	doctor	Well, as a doctor, I may have left a few unpleasant patients here and there.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	417	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_e9fa2080	doctor	But, like you, I do not believe there is anything so serious that it should lead to murder.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	417	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_6c4a567e		I am not entirely sure that I believe my own words.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	423	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_228b2392		But I see no point in sharing those doubts.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	423	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_bcb32442	captain	So, we have no notion of what may be happening.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	429	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_fe5918bc	captain	We know only that we are in danger here, presumably from Lady Claythorn herself, even if we have no proof we could present.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	429	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_9484f51e	doctor	That is what I believe as well.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	435	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_aa07feac	doctor	I am simply not sure what we ought to do about it.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	435	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_5210a77d	captain	Well, it would be difficult to leave now, in the middle of the night.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	441	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_e1b162f8	captain	So we should at least be prepared to spend one more night here.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	441	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_5f5e2780	captain	And attempting to confide in more people could be dangerous.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	441	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_680309c2	captain	Lady Claythorn may not be acting alone in this enterprise.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	441	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_1c8adbd8	captain	If we confront her, she will become suspicious and it will be even harder to escape this place.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	441	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_9ec69397	captain	We must take every precaution we can.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	441	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_ca3d76f5	doctor	I agree, but what do you suggest we do?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	455	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_1a426224		I believe we should not sleep alone tonight.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	459	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_35ea4498		Come and share my room.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	459	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_617a0299		There is a perfectly decent sofa, and we shall be within earshot of one another.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	459	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_5be15203		If anything happens, at least we shall not be taken unawares.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	459	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_8e205757		I am not sure I like this idea.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	469	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_d041b6dc		Yet, it may be the best chance I have of surviving this weekend.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	469	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_dbb2607e		On the other hand, it forces me to trust Sushil Sinha with my life.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	469	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_mask_c57c6b69		I am not sure that I can do that.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	469	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_captain_sleep_yes_b44fa237	doctor	You are right.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	491	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_captain_sleep_yes_174b21c8	doctor	It would be foolish to ignore the danger.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	491	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_captain_sleep_yes_53d5dbc8	doctor	I think it is better if we stay together.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	491	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_captain_sleep_yes_39aa109e	captain	Good.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	499	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_captain_sleep_yes_f823863d	captain	You can collect whatever you need from your room, then you may settle on my sofa.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	499	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_captain_sleep_yes_8ad5e507	captain	Between us, I doubt anyone will find us easy prey.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	499	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_captain_sleep_yes_d14a09e6		It is not an arrangement with which I feel entirely at ease.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	507	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_captain_sleep_yes_836ebe85		Yet I feel a little less exposed than before at least.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	507	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_captain_sleep_yes_26e8262a		I return briefly to my own room to gather my things, then I join Sushil Sinha in his.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	507	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_captain_sleep_yes_411e87a2	captain	Well, it is rather late, so I suppose we had best settle for sleep.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	517	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_captain_sleep_yes_9f63138b	captain	You can take the sofa, or if you find it too uncomfortable, there is space enough in the bed.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	517	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_captain_sleep_yes_3b9f13e6	captain	I have slept in worse conditions, so I do not mind.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	517	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_captain_sleep_yes_d2946e9c	doctor	The sofa will do very well, thank you.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	525	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_captain_sleep_yes_69248490	doctor	I doubt I shall sleep much in any case.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	525	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_captain_sleep_yes_cf7620d5		There is no point in attempting anything further tonight.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	531	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_captain_sleep_yes_ea87ce05		So we bid each other good night and resign ourselves to hope for the best.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	531	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_captain_sleep_yes_6c5a0b8d		Before closing my eyes, I see Sushil Sinha place a revolver upon his bedside table.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	531	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_captain_sleep_yes_37fccf1d		The sight troubles me as much as it makes me feel safer.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	531	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_captain_sleep_options_607d699a		Now that I have settled, the cravings grow stronger than ever.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	552	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_captain_sleep_options_5a1090a2		I toss and turn upon the sofa, praying for the light of day.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	552	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_captain_sleep_options_5222352e		After what feels like an eternity, I finally fall asleep.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	552	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_captain_sleep_options_e480148a		Now that I am alone with my thoughts, every possible scenario runs through my mind.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	562	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_captain_sleep_options_7ad2e428		I feel certain I shall never fall asleep, yet at some point I do.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	562	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_captain_sleep_no_0fb27d7a	doctor	I am grateful for your concern, Captain, but I would rather not impose upon you.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	573	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_captain_sleep_no_f1f2632b	doctor	I shall manage well enough in my own room.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	573	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_captain_sleep_no_1d9f018a	captain	As you wish.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	579	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_captain_sleep_no_331a68b4	captain	I cannot compel you.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	579	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_captain_sleep_no_fc00155c	captain	But at least lock your door.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	579	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_captain_sleep_no_b91c96e5	captain	I would rather not discover we have misjudged the danger come morning.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	579	captain "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_captain_sleep_no_93e41e64		I nod, though my resolve feels far less steady than I should like.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	589	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_captain_sleep_no_f958772f		If I insist upon facing the night alone, I must be ready for whatever it may bring.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_billiard_room.rpy	589	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_exploration_6148b956		I now find myself faced with several courses of action.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	9	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_exploration_28775a97		The most obvious would be to remain here in my room and wait for the morning.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	9	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_exploration_a661af29		I could even move some furniture against the door to make certain no one can enter.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	9	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_exploration_e2243906		Yet that, too, feels dangerous. There are other ways for someone to reach me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	9	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_exploration_36822b6c		The alternative is to attempt to discover who wrote that note to Samuel Manning.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	9	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_exploration_09d9a4a4		That is the person I ought to fear.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	9	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_exploration_4193701a		Everything points towards Lady Claythorn, yet I cannot be sure.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	9	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_exploration_1df57049		If only I could trust at least one other person, I might ask for their assistance.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	9	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_exploration_8d4ec0d1		It would be safer to investigate in company, but in whom ought I place my trust?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	9	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_exploration_908b1537		It would be ideal to have someone implicitly trustworthy, like a judge.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	9	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_exploration_157e28d7		But everyone here appears suspicious to me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	9	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_exploration_95134a01		I might turn to Andrew. After the time we have spent together, I find it hard to picture him as a likely culprit.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	35	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_exploration_9a5ba9ec		He is probably downstairs with the staff at present, unless he has already retired for the night.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	35	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_exploration_d6f4a4fc		By good fortune, I already know Nurse Rosalind Marsh. That acquaintance makes me more comfortable about approaching her.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	43	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_exploration_de1bc941		I also have to manage symptoms of withdrawal.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	49	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_exploration_4df9bb17		My hands tremble, and I am sweating more than is reasonable.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	49	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_exploration_c4d31b7f		They will only grow worse as the night wears on, which will not be in my favour.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	49	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_exploration_38f1756b		I feel very much at a crossroads.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	57	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_exploration_7c0a5330		What I decide to do now may mean the difference between life and death.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	57	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_exploration_d46db12c		So what shall it be?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	57	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_exploration_ba8f43bf		It's getting very late, I should go to bed.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	75	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_lad_a41b50c2	doctor	Mr Harring, are you there?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	90	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_lad_407bd55a		For a moment there is no answer.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	94	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_lad_460542d9		Then I hear a faint voice from behind the door.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	94	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_lad_37b9cba7	lad	Doctor Baldwin, is that you?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	100	lad "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_lad_f9eacf96	doctor	Yes.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	104	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_lad_e97e9b9c	doctor	I should like a word with you, it is rather important.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	104	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_lad_855c13b0	doctor	May I come in?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	104	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_lad_e41d4371	lad	Well, I don't know, doctor.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	112	lad "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_lad_049afa8e	lad	I've already dragged a desk in front of the door.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	112	lad "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_lad_4dc71861	lad	Might be better if we did the talking through it.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	112	lad "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_lad_4c394dbd	doctor	I am afraid it is a very sensitive matter.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	120	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_lad_82806fe8	doctor	I would not care for anyone overhearing us.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	120	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_lad_900f89cc	lad	Oh.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	126	lad "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_lad_2f909b6e	lad	In that case, it is probably best if we wait until the morning.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	126	lad "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_lad_020a38b5	lad	It will be easier to talk then.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	126	lad "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_lad_bf2d7161	lad	Good night, doctor.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	126	lad "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_lad_79e4b441	doctor	No, it might be too late by then, I need to...	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	136	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_lad_a026462f		I hear his footsteps recede and the faint creak of floorboards further inside the room.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	140	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_lad_ca3182e3		It seems Mr Harring has no intention of opening his door tonight.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	140	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_lad_d591ce68		I had better try somewhere else.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	140	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_broken_57b10e78		Thomas Moody's room looks exactly as it did this morning.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	155	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_broken_cf8ae22f		With all that has transpired since, I have scarcely given a thought to the mystery of Thomas Moody's mask.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	161	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_broken_49b37845		It is one more reason to question everything that is happening in this house.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	161	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_broken_9ccef5b4		But there is nothing I can do about it from here.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	161	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_broken_90736cdf		I should leave.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	161	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_broken_71f68daf		The poor man's body lies just as before upon the bed.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	173	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_broken_b5c3255c		This morning I chose not to look beneath his mask, out of respect.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	173	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_broken_b30cb95d		After all that has occurred since, that restraint feels misplaced.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	173	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_broken_c05fd359		I am compelled to examine him more closely.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	173	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_broken_7aedb816		I step nearer to the bed and lean over him.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	173	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_broken_022ffc4e		At once I notice small details, such as the way the face beneath the mask does not seem as peaceful as it ought.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	173	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_broken_86a81ea9		Almost before I realise what I am doing, my hand reaches for the mask and I lift it away.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	173	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_sleep_alone_7e62fa32		I reach my room alone.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	200	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_sleep_alone_1eed8b87		I lock my door and do what I can to secure it.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	200	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_sleep_alone_1d146fb8		Then I drag a chair and the small chest of drawers against the door, in case Lady Claythorn or one of her accomplices decides to pay me a visit.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	208	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_sleep_alone_62f16456		Now that everything is in place, I lie down upon the bed, fully dressed in case I need to move quickly.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	214	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_sleep_alone_209fab0a		I do not know how long I have slept when a faint sound rouses me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	226	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_sleep_alone_df755367		It is a soft scrape, close by my ear, out of place in the stillness of the room.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	226	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_sleep_alone_73cd425c		Before I can stir, a hand clamps hard across my mouth, stifling any cry.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	232	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_sleep_alone_f1ef8c14		The weight of a body leans over me, pinning me to the mattress.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	232	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_sleep_alone_072fae23		I clutch at the arm that holds me, but my limbs feel heavy and slow, still dulled by sleep.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	238	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_sleep_alone_40f3c50a		My heart hammers so loudly that I can scarcely hear my own thoughts.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	238	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_sleep_alone_4fea3f46		Something cold touches the bare skin of my throat.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	244	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_sleep_alone_d0a621b7		For one dreadful instant I understand exactly what is about to happen.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	244	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_sleep_alone_2fb39dde		Pain sears across my neck in a sudden, burning line.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	250	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_sleep_alone_d28c3f41		Hot wetness spills down my collar, soaking the front of my shirt.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	250	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_sleep_alone_c3302e5c		I struggle blindly, fingers clawing at the air and at the implacable hand that silences me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	256	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_sleep_alone_362e000f		My strength ebbs almost at once, as if it were pouring away with my blood.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	256	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_drunk_ce054acb		I am back in Samuel Manning's room.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	269	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_drunk_8b8268b7		It is still a mess.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	269	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_drunk_43caf680		But now Samuel Manning is lying on his bed, seemingly at peace.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	269	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_drunk_32e86d60		I remember that Captain Sinha and Ted Harring carried him here.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	269	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_drunk_f4183f14		I do not know why I have come back.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	269	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_drunk_65e94b9a		Perhaps I wished to look one last time upon the man I killed.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	269	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_drunk_fa02ea2f		I approach the bed.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	269	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_drunk_e2d4df38		He looks peaceful.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	269	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_drunk_6ca47554		I try to convince myself that I had no choice, that it was either him or me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	269	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_drunk_1e31d014		But that does not make the guilt go away.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	269	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_drunk_11457f1b		My thoughts return to the simple letter that set all of this in motion.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	269	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_drunk_e8420c3c		I wonder if it is still here.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	269	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_drunk_a5873639		I look around and do not find it on the desk.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	269	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_drunk_2e387f48		Then I spot something in the fire.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	269	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_drunk_7a53412d		The letter is there, burned so badly I cannot make out what was written.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	269	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_drunk_1283c114		If I had hoped to use it as proof of my innocence, I am too late.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	269	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_drunk_e6b4a997		Samuel Manning has taken care to erase all trace of his plans.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	269	"[what]"
doctor_day2_evening_bedroom_drunk_671b247a		There is no point in lingering here any longer.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 2/3_Evening/2_exploration.rpy	269	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_f9a18797	captain	Doctor Baldwin.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	5	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_e711e3ec	captain	Doctor Baldwin, are you awake?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	5	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_495b477a		I slowly open my eyes to find Captain Sinha standing over me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	11	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_5da2c0c3	doctor	Yes, Captain.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	15	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_eb72e573	doctor	I am awake.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	15	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_e9f0734f	captain	I apologise for the intrusion, Doctor, but it is already well past eight o'clock.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	21	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_5e284df6	captain	I believe we should leave the room without delay.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	21	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_60866fce	doctor	Very well.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	27	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_e52794ef	doctor	Give me a moment.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	27	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_2130b4d1	captain	Of course.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	33	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_dd983e9c		A quick glance at Sushil Sinha tells me he is perfectly prepared.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	37	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_919fa83b		I do not know when he woke up, but he must have been waiting for quite some time.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	37	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_05fd4dae		In contrast, I must look a terrible sight.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	45	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_f781a882		I have been sweating all night, my body aching for a dose of laudanum.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	45	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_cc7e974f		Fortunately, I was not in my own room, or I might have relapsed.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	45	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_b76a5455		I can only hope that today will be easier.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	45	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_0dc15347	captain	I suggest we go to the dining room first.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	55	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_c390d8b6	captain	We should see who is already awake.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	55	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_87ecaf12	doctor	That seems reasonable.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	61	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_12fa5f81		I make myself as presentable as I can, and we set off together.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	65	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_f40704df	captain	This is odd.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	73	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_9f33ddaa	captain	There is no one here.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	73	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_92cd573c	doctor	And breakfast has not been laid out either.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	79	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_3be84a08	captain	Which is unusual, considering the hour.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	83	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_eb07bfc8	doctor	Indeed.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	87	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_4dda53ea	doctor	Perhaps we should look elsewhere.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	87	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_77899981	captain	I agree.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	93	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_fbd29ef8	captain	The kitchen would be the logical next stop.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	93	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_52ab9905	doctor	Let us go.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	99	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_7219e3e0	captain	It is completely silent.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	107	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_89d70c9a	captain	That is not normal.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	107	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_a6820510	captain	Something is very wrong.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	107	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_d8a5453d	captain	We should proceed with caution and search the house for the others.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	107	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_1e5a8593	doctor	I was thinking the same.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	117	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_f6523f91		We search the manor methodically for some time.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	125	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_ad356139		Room after room yields nothing, and we begin to lose hope.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	125	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_6ae057eb		Then, as we descend the stairs to the entrance hall, we hear the faint sound of voices below.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	125	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_07acb555	captain	Is anyone here?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	133	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_89782300	lad	Captain Sinha, is that you?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	137	lad "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_bd42014d		We look down and spot Ted Harring and Amelia Baxter.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	141	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_2189596c	captain	At last, living, breathing souls.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	145	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_813a795e	captain	We were beginning to feel as though we were wandering a ghost house.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	145	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_6fa23ef1	psychic	We feel the same.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	151	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_6c8ec3ee	psychic	You are the first people we have encountered all morning.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	151	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_85ae2cd0	psychic	I cannot understand where everyone else could have gone.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	151	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_dd008fdf	captain	Nor can we.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	159	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_6b17c142	doctor	There is one place we have not checked.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	163	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_11441506	doctor	Miss Marsh's room.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	163	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_22d0faff	psychic	I knocked earlier.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	169	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_c5a0a4d3	psychic	There was no answer.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	169	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_f0195d34	psychic	I tried to enter, but it was locked.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	169	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_59a1ad4a	captain	Yes, we received no answer as well.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	177	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_3d862a63	captain	I think it is time we check anyway.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	177	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_402fb2f0		We all stand in front of Miss Marsh's room.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	187	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_946fbb8b		Captain Sinha tests the handle.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	187	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_e92bcaa7	captain	Locked.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	195	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_51e70aed	captain	Miss Marsh?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	199	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_e2c8af44	captain	Are you inside?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	199	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_f8253610		There is no reply.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	205	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_df995e52	captain	Doctor, Mister Harring,	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	209	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_122292fa	captain	I believe if the three of us shove together, the door will give way.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	209	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_79c55656	psychic	Are you sure it is wise to do this?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	215	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_d69f779b	captain	I am afraid that under the circumstances, we have no other choice.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	219	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_3e5aac63	psychic	Very well.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	223	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_4fe273a6	captain	Lads, on my command.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	227	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_5142eab2	captain	One.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	227	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_448b90c4	captain	Two.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	227	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_837cb67e	captain	Three.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	227	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_c968bcb3		The lock gives way and the door swings open.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	239	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_937d6f48		We all enter the room.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	239	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_91985a15	captain	There is nobody here.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	247	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_ff351be0	lad	So she just vanished?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	251	lad "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_a5b56b52	lad	Along with half the house?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	251	lad "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_31e2ad4f	captain	It would appear so.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	257	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_3138a626		A heavy silence settles over us.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	261	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_fbdf887c	captain	I do not understand what is happening.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	265	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_b4e44720	captain	We need to discuss this.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	265	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_e418ad92	psychic	Of course.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	271	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_0b697bb5	psychic	Perhaps we should settle somewhere more comfortable, like the tea room?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	271	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_captain_cf41912f	captain	A good idea.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2a_captain.rpy	277	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_ee103d43		I wake up to the soft sound of someone entering the room.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	5	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_040a045f		Miss Marsh is coming in.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	5	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_7782c0cf	nurse	I've just come from the dinner room, it's empty.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	11	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_53819e76	nurse	In fact I didn't see anyone anywhere.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	11	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_cec52f18	nurse	No staff at all.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	11	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_c596c8e9	doctor	How is it possible?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	19	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_8e8c8a6a	doctor	Where could everyone have gone?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	19	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_e94e5bd0	doctor	That doesn't make sense.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	19	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_66d4a797	nurse	I don't know, but it is indeed very suspicious.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	27	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_d0ec64f0	nurse	We were right to be cautious, something weird is definitely happening here.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	27	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_be1871d1	doctor	But what should we do then?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	33	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_463e6a94	doctor	Should we...	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	33	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_4447fb31	nurse	Shh. I hear someone coming.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	39	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_d160fe30		She puts her ear to the door.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	43	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_ce21e34a		I get up quietly and join her.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	43	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_3bb66186		We hear two people walking together, talking in low voices.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	49	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_7f38c0c6		I recognise Ted Harring and Amelia Baxter.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	49	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_15da032e		After they have passed, Rosalind Marsh confirms it.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	49	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_daaf17b9	nurse	Ted Harring and Amelia Baxter.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	57	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_62b989b6	nurse	What are they doing here? There is no reason for them to pass by my door.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	57	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_35f82e07	nurse	I don't like this.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	57	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_c69cbf66	doctor	Maybe they're just looking for the staff.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	65	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_9dec8fe4	doctor	They must be as surprised as we are.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	65	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_35c41a22	nurse	Maybe, but I don't know.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	71	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_a7653fa9	nurse	It could be something else entirely.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	71	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_361a4610	nurse	I don't really trust those two.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	71	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_70da2519	nurse	I prefer if we avoided them at the moment.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	71	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_1f010fe9	doctor	If it helps keep your mind at ease, why not.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	81	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_ac822cf5	doctor	But what should we do instead?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	81	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_2dc3acc7	nurse	Well, we can't stay in this room.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	87	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_461a2f14	nurse	They might come looking here eventually.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	87	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_57238724	doctor	So what do you propose?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	93	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_00686240	nurse	I know a place where we can hide for a while until we know more.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	97	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_1b3b4d19	doctor	Very well. Where are we heading?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	101	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_c8658f6f	nurse	Come with me, I'll show you.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	105	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_0f439845		Without waiting for an answer she slightly opens the door and takes a peek outside.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	109	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_16050653	nurse	The hallway is clear. Come with me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	113	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_24990bbb	doctor	Fine.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	117	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_5cdab734		We make it only a few steps before we hear another set of footsteps.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	123	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_332b6530		Miss Marsh pulls me into a narrow recess beside a service door.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	123	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_9329fe09		I press my back against the cold wood, holding my breath.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	123	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_9cf8b940		Captain Sinha appears in the corridor, moving with quiet purpose.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	123	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_2ac73ae2		He pauses for a moment, as if listening, then continues on his way downstairs.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	123	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_9066ea74		I glance at Miss Marsh.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	123	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_d70c711c		She is perfectly still, her breathing shallow and controlled.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	123	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_0114d827		She knows exactly how to make herself invisible.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	123	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_ac44278c		It is impressive, and slightly unsettling.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	123	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_a6cccc22		It feels like this is not the first time she has had to hide like this.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	123	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_aeb9bf64		When the danger is over, she signals for me to follow her.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	123	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_f5a856f5		We take a flight of stairs up to the attic.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	123	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_a2263e90	nurse	Perfect. There is a room here where we will be comfortable.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	151	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_08bc5274	nurse	I don't think they would look here.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	151	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_deb86fbf		She unlocks the door next to us and goes in.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	157	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_3fa6176c	nurse	Come on in, Doctor, it's empty.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	163	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_70c03490		I follow her, and she immediately closes the door behind me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	169	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_fce503c4	nurse	We should sit tight here for a bit.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	175	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_717b94a0	nurse	My guess is that they will try to look everywhere but here.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	175	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_aa198447	nurse	In a while, either they'll have found someone or realise we are the only ones left in the Manor.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	175	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_481240f1	nurse	We can go check again then.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	175	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_1ccfdb9d		She thought of everything. I don't think I would have acted that way on my own.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	185	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_e9e15bbf		It's unsettling.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	185	"[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_28cd4b0a	doctor	Excuse me, but how did you get the key to this room?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	191	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_3a4bc194	nurse	Oh, I found it in the main hall earlier this morning, on a table.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	195	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_2e2fa22c	nurse	It's a pass that opens all the doors in the mansion apparently.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	195	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_ffdbe0e8	nurse	Wherever he went, the butler didn't think he would need his key anymore.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	195	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_a860516e	doctor	Right, so he's probably gone for good then.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	203	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_34c7f4f3	nurse	That's what I think, and the rest of the staff probably went with him.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	207	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_9cc1c026	doctor	As well as Lady Claythorn.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	211	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_morning_nurse_1a4338b3	nurse	Yes, it's very likely.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/1_Morning/2b_nurse.rpy	215	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_6997644a		We are all seated in the tea room, Captain Sinha, Ted Harring, Amelia Baxter, and I.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	5	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_49ffe780		Each of us is deep in thought.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	5	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_fb395ca3		The manor feels hollow now, stripped of its usual life.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	5	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_c3decd99		Captain Sinha breaks the silence.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	5	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_223112d6	captain	Whatever happened here was coordinated.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	15	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_658b5ba2	captain	Staff and guests alike did not simply wander off.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	15	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_890a23d7	lad	But why?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	21	lad "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_1c33be96		Captain Sinha leans towards me and whispers in my ear.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	25	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_f52634da	captain	Perhaps it is better to tell them everything.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	29	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_17ad3df0	captain	We might need their help if we are to get out of here intact.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	29	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_8b9330f6	captain	What do you think, Doctor?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	29	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_9357ca28	psychic	Excuse me, what are you two whispering about?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	37	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_aeb03bdf	psychic	Is there something we should know?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	37	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_5bcbc3c1		Once again, we all fall silent.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	52	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_65f9b991		Trying to make sense of what is happening to us.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	52	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_57fed57f	lad	Right, as I see it, we don't know much more than we did this morning.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	58	lad "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_422b9c89	lad	So what now?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	58	lad "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_5670ea04	lad	I feel like we've explored the whole place already.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	58	lad "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_3af6f6a1	lad	And we can't just sit around waiting for answers.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	58	lad "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_845f31db	captain	No.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	68	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_4ed5066a	captain	We must act sensibly.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	68	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_88bbb53d	captain	It is obvious now that we have to leave.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	68	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_18c46f3b	psychic	Of course, but how?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	76	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_3f344fbd	psychic	The nearest town is miles away.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	76	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_afe4eae9	psychic	I can't walk that far.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	76	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_9e01ce6a	psychic	And even if I could, I'm not prepared for such a journey.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	76	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_30c8ca16	captain	You might be right.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	86	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_329b2edd	captain	It would be a long walk, and the weather might turn at any moment.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	86	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_dc0c237f	captain	We could be caught in another storm.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	86	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_a5d8b51a	captain	It is probably unsafe for you to join us.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	86	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_8e278b58	psychic	But you're not going to leave me here alone, are you?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	96	psychic surprised "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_5d42ac09	psychic	What would become of me?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	96	psychic surprised "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_b71a508f	captain	We could lock you in a room.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	102	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_1090c90a	captain	Though that is far from ideal.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	102	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_326483fd	captain	Perhaps one of us should stay with you.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	102	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_1d0526f9	psychic	Yes!	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	110	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_bca72e4c	psychic	Mr Harring can stay with me, right?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	110	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_e5dba536	psychic	The two of us should be safe until you return with help.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	110	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_3cc8caea	captain	That seems to be the wisest choice.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	118	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_46220ac6	captain	What do you think, Mr Harring?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	118	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_do_not_share_d17adca1	doctor	No, it is nothing.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	138	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_do_not_share_83ab5efe	doctor	Captain Sinha merely noticed that my shirt was not sitting properly.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	138	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_do_not_share_941277d5	doctor	It is fixed now.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	138	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_do_not_share_478f803b		I quickly tuck my shirt in.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	146	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_do_not_share_6939391d		Captain Sinha gives me a disapproving look. He would have preferred to explain everything.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	146	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_do_not_share_052c2137		But I do not know that I can trust those two just yet.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	146	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_do_not_share_5992e1ea		In any case, Amelia Baxter seems reassured by my very plausible answer.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	146	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_do_not_share_00fd75e0	psychic	All right, but please, no whispering.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	156	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_do_not_share_0833ec5a	psychic	We are already tense as it is.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	156	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_do_not_share_c55dce1b	captain	Of course. My apologies.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	162	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_973dc7c7	doctor	I believe you are right, Captain.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	171	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_b83de6e4	doctor	We might as well tell you everything we know.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	171	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_c3333a57		So I tell them about the letter we found in Samuel Manning's room, and how it lead to our fight, and his death.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	177	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_0c38180f		They look at me puzzled at first, taking it in.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	177	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_182b05fd		When the implications are clear to them, they look frightened.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	177	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_f522aa98	psychic	How terrible.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	185	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_4e573f8e	psychic	But who could be behind this?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	185	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_a7334a73	captain	That's what we've been trying to figure out, without success.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	191	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_0ee7eee6		Of course, we are not saying what everyone is thinking.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	195	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_0d12d0a9		We are all suspects to the others.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	195	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_65270c87		We may have made a choice to trust them, but deep down we'll stay watchful.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	195	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_e84ba336	psychic	Right, so right now you don't have more idea than we do.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	203	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_b37bec96	captain	That is correct.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	207	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_7b165769	captain	We only believe that the obvious suspect is Lady Claythorn.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	207	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_7f844b6f	psychic	Of course, but we don't know enough to be sure are we?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	213	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_54921582	psychic	We need more information to really know what's happening.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	213	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_footman_db02143a	doctor	There is something else you should know.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	232	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_footman_18eb1f74	doctor	The footman was not who he claimed to be.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	232	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_footman_8a4ca569	doctor	He told me he was an actor.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	232	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_footman_47d771b6	captain	An actor?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	240	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_footman_b8ec6c90	captain	Now that you mention it, I remember he made a few mistakes during dinner.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	240	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_footman_0e677ca6	captain	I assumed he was new to the job.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	240	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_footman_c7cb9513	psychic	It is true, he was a bit inexperienced.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	248	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_footman_b8c43ac9	captain	And now that you mention it, so were the others.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	252	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_footman_4c4cdffa	psychic	Right, and there were not many of them either.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	256	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_footman_5aaed7f3	psychic	A house this big should have twice the staff, at least, compared to what I have seen.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	256	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_footman_61a0823f	psychic	I simply thought it was due to a labour shortage.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	256	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_footman_e4e1565f		Ted Harring remains silent through the whole exchange.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	264	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_footman_a9925573		He clearly did not notice anything out of place.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	264	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_footman_028ece35		I must admit I did not either.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	264	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_footman_a1cd960e	doctor	So, in your view, the staff was not what you expected.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	272	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_footman_545ad1dc	psychic	Perhaps not.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	276	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_footman_c850e1e1	captain	Not at all, in my opinion.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	280	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_footman_6457de8a	captain	But that doesn't say much.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	280	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_footman_a459e590	captain	I assume a lot of struggling artist end up doing this kind of work.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	280	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_footman_3456c782	captain	The times have changed, it is no longer the case that you were born in service and stay in it your whole life.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	280	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_footman_b1c50047	psychic	Sadly.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	290	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_footman_738fba26	captain	On the other hand, it could also mean they were part of whatever is happening here.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	294	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_footman_b7e6d3da	captain	It would explain why we cannot see any of them here today.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	294	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_footman_f0e25e26	psychic	Maybe, but again, there is no way to know for sure.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	300	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_footman_2130b4d1	captain	Of course.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	304	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_footman_5b8c04ae		I do not believe Andrew was involved, at least not in anything that would harm us.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	308	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_footman_84d0b5f4		But I cannot tell them why.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	308	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_footman_4a304f51		Besides, I did not know him all that well.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	308	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_nurse_69f502d6	doctor	I am not sure if it is relevant, but I realised earlier that Miss Marsh and I were already acquainted.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	323	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_nurse_d0740e2b	doctor	I don't know if it is relevant or if it just a coincidence.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	323	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_nurse_359b30f7	captain	It would be a very improbable coincidence indeed.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	329	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_nurse_246f0d59	captain	That out of the millions of people in the realm, Lady Claythorn chose two that know each other.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	329	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_nurse_7a1ddac0	captain	You could be onto something doctor.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	329	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_nurse_73d1ec92	captain	How well did you know her?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	329	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_nurse_d6a0865d	doctor	Not very well of course, I didn't even recognize her at first.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	339	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_nurse_dd63c492	doctor	We met a very long time ago, during the Boxer's rebellion, you see we...	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	339	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_nurse_df9f9e68	captain	Wait, Doctor. You were in China during the Boxer's Rebellion?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	345	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_nurse_9cfd6ca5	doctor	Yes, as was miss Marsh apparently.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	349	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_nurse_d725b93d	captain	In that case, that can't be a coincidence Doctor.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	353	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_nurse_d1987011	captain	You see, I was there myself.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	353	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_nurse_e32697d4	doctor	You were?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	361	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_nurse_90f08d6c	doctor	I don't remember you.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	361	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_nurse_af1e86ec	captain	Well, there was a vast among of Indian soldiers fighting for the country.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	367	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_nurse_2d6a1f40	captain	It may have been different for you to tell us apart.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	367	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_nurse_106fde95	captain	In any case, we didn't associate a lot with people from the metropolis.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	367	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_nurse_364830d1	captain	But know that I try to remember, I think I can see talking to a young doctor looking a bit like yourself.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	367	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_nurse_651a5f9b	doctor	Well, right.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	377	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_nurse_a429b951	doctor	It's possible we've met before as well, then.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	377	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_nurse_f28c5365	lad	How queer.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	383	lad "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_nurse_39e5a4d6	lad	What are the chances of that?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	383	lad "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_nurse_413f17d3	captain	That it happened by chance that at least three people present here tonight met before?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	389	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_nurse_7b011ceb	captain	I would say close to to zero Mr Harring.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	389	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_nurse_8fe83b97	captain	I would even dare to say that what happened in China could be the reason we are all here this weekend.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	389	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_nurse_0e0104e5		Everybody pounders that for a second.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	397	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_nurse_9e396e94	lad	But I'be never been to China.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	401	lad "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_nurse_ddb47b22	psychic	Neither have I.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	405	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_nurse_4a4182e3	psychic	And I am confident I never met anyone here before as well.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	405	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_nurse_125a9689	captain	Right, still this a very weird coincidence, we shouldn't overlook it.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	411	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_broken_d137d292	doctor	There was something else that struck me as strange, though I do not yet see how it helps us make sense of our situation.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	422	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_broken_56061d94	doctor	It concerns Thomas Moody.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	422	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_broken_9de22f3e	psychic	What about him?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	428	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_broken_c8668f6d	doctor	You all noticed the mask he wore to hide his war injuries, I presume.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	432	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_broken_e418ad92	psychic	Of course.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	436	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_broken_c8b53e92	lad	How could we miss it?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	440	lad "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_broken_65b1d584	doctor	When I examined him, I had to remove the mask to determine the cause of death.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	444	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_broken_dc7bebc9	doctor	I confess I was apprehensive about what I might find.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	444	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_broken_56c309aa	doctor	But behind it, there were no injuries at all.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	444	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_broken_296dbf37	lad	No injuries?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	452	lad "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_broken_d29afd09	lad	Then why wear the bloody thing?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	452	lad "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_broken_f8edd220	doctor	Honestly, I cannot offer a logical explanation.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	458	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_broken_1678d488	doctor	It was so unsettling that I kept it to myself, as I wished to understand more before speaking of it.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	458	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_broken_3f7028e9	doctor	When I shared what I knew with Captain Sinha, he helped me realise something else.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	458	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_broken_d6edc79c	doctor	That Thomas Moody may have been poisoned.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	458	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_broken_b3ed47d7	psychic	Poisoned?!	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	468	psychic surprised "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_broken_d9490688	psychic	And you did not think you ought to have told us?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	468	psychic surprised "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_broken_910fc2ce	captain	At the time, we realised something was terribly wrong in the manor.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	474	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_broken_47576beb	captain	But we did not know whom we could trust.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	474	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_broken_54a97c3c	captain	So we kept it to ourselves.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	474	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_broken_f0dbb82d	psychic	Right.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	482	psychic -surprised "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_broken_59366bf1	psychic	I am not sure how that helps us just now.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	482	psychic -surprised "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_broken_9b142bd3	psychic	It is one more reason to worry, and nothing that truly helps us.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	482	psychic -surprised "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_broken_e573c1cd	psychic	Still, at least you have told us.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	482	psychic -surprised "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_share_broken_6c60e55a	doctor	I am sorry.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2a_captain.rpy	492	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_02cfe100	nurse	I believe it has been long enough.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	5	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_820ffcac	nurse	We should head back downstairs, and see where the others have settled.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	5	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_c317d8c6		We climb down from the attic and reach the top of the main staircase.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	11	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_aa3bd5b7		From there, we can hear voices coming from the tea room.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	17	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_50d4c259		We go down and linger by the doorway, careful not to be seen.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	17	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_988dbd59		We try to make out what they are saying.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	17	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_340687fb		We cannot catch every word, but the gist is clear.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	25	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_23d6a25d		Captain Sinha intends to leave on his own.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	25	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_151b9118		Ted Harring and Amelia Baxter will wait for him to return with help.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	25	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_67bc606c	nurse	I think they are coming.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	33	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_d50d761c	nurse	Quickly.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	33	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_f40b9c7c		She darts towards the library to hide.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	39	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_a59addd7		I follow her at once.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	39	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_d9d213c6	nurse	Good.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	47	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_acccb271	nurse	We should be safe in here, for the moment.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	47	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_60866fce	doctor	Very well.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	53	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_956e4828	doctor	But what do we do next?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	53	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_fdc591d0	doctor	From what we heard, they are no closer to understanding what is happening than we are.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	53	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_073b23a2	doctor	It may be safe to speak with them, do you not agree?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	53	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_92b5107b	nurse	I am not sure.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	63	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_47b5b9b9	nurse	One of them could be lying to the others.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	63	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_50afc593	nurse	Mostly, I am frightened of Captain Sinha.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	63	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_65b28a59	nurse	I do not think the other two are as dangerous.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	63	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_516906d3	nurse	We should at least wait for him to leave.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	63	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_1c3b0d8a	nurse	After that, I do not know.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	63	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_1673b267	nurse	We could remain hidden, and see whether the police come.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	63	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_63bc66cc	nurse	Or we could try to speak to them.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	63	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_5aae950e	nurse	What do you think?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	63	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_deb1ef9e	psychic	Doctor?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	89	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_cd650eae	psychic	And Miss Marsh?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	89	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_9d5e86d0	psychic	Where have you been?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	89	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_db66b90d	lad	You two gave us a fright.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	97	lad "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_7b49f6bd	lad	Thought you'd done a runner like the others.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	97	lad "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_a24bfe37	nurse	We have been searching the house.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	103	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_f2d2fa89	nurse	We did not find anything useful.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	103	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_761c311a	nurse	We heard the front door close, so we came at once.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	103	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_4a09d1df	nurse	Has someone just left?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	103	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_44fd3847	psychic	Yes, Captain Sinha.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	113	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_149f5e61	psychic	He has gone to fetch help.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	113	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_c6a62eb0	psychic	He says he can make it alone, and that we should not all risk ourselves on the road.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	113	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_9aa523cd	psychic	So we shall wait for him here.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	113	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_f6cde5c8	nurse	That seems sensible.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	123	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_9a924015	nurse	Then we shall wait with you.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	123	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_7f4157df	psychic	All right.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	129	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_41512f3c	psychic	In the meantime, none of us has eaten properly in hours.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	129	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_5d74bdf7	psychic	Since we have little else to do, we ought to prepare something.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	129	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_4395d8a5	psychic	That would at least keep us occupied until the police arrive.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	129	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_d258ff6e	nurse	I agree.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	139	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_c8ceee7c	nurse	We should go and see what is in the kitchen.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	139	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_06c3cd22	psychic	Good idea.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	145	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_1ef6de4e	psychic	Let's go.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	145	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_wait_captain_leave_406a131e	nurse	All right.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	158	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_wait_captain_leave_3e1e2dc2	nurse	Let us wait a little.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	158	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_wait_captain_leave_2d0cc32b		We do not have to wait long.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	168	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_wait_captain_leave_9367ee85		A few minutes later, we hear the Captain say his goodbyes.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	168	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_wait_captain_leave_290f3697		Then the front door closes.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	168	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_talk_b4ef3d62	doctor	I think we should speak to them.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	183	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_talk_86f21462	doctor	We can wait for Captain Sinha to leave, if you would prefer.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	183	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_talk_1e77908f	nurse	Right.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	191	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_talk_f22215f2	nurse	He has left.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	191	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_talk_84c01b48	nurse	We can safely approach the others now.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	191	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_talk_db997dea		We slip out of the library and cross the hall.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	199	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_talk_e2dbb413		Ted Harring and Amelia Baxter are still there.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	205	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_talk_cd00e06e		They look startled to see us.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	205	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_hide_1faba571	doctor	I believe we should remain hidden for the moment.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	217	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_hide_d44a7b09	doctor	Not out of cowardice, but out of prudence.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	217	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_hide_9e92e3c0	doctor	There is no point in taking unnecessary risks.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	217	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_hide_ba7414c9	doctor	From what I understand, Captain Sinha is going to find help.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	217	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_hide_3d0275fc	doctor	We can stay concealed until he returns.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	217	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_hide_1a3c40d1	doctor	That is probably the safest course.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	217	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_hide_d9d213c6	nurse	Good.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	231	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_hide_49cbef53	nurse	I was hoping you would say that.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	231	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_hide_58825de8	nurse	We just have to find a safe spot and wait there.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	231	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_hide_80e37c38	nurse	But first, let us be certain Captain Sinha has gone.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	231	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_hide_60866fce	doctor	Very well.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	241	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_hide_1e77908f	nurse	Right.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	247	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_hide_f22215f2	nurse	He has left.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	247	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_hide_d80fed02	doctor	All right.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	253	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_hide_e076173e	doctor	Let us go then.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	253	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_hide_d857f9cb		I step out of the library, thinking the entrance hall will be empty.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	259	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_hide_dd313598	nurse	Doctor, wait,...	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	263	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_hide_e35c1412		But of course Ted Harring and Amelia Baxter are still there, lingering by the front door.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	269	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_hide_2ba5cdf0		Bloody hell, what a fool I am.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	269	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_hide_02643fee		Too late to back out now.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	269	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_hide_9d3a8dd0		I shall simply have to make the best of it.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	269	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_84241024		The kitchen is cold, but not abandoned.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	288	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_7f4e115a		A few pots still sit where they were left.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	288	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_02944d7e		A loaf of bread rests beneath a cloth, as if someone meant to return.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	288	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_a5b20be3	nurse	There should be enough here for a simple meal.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	296	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_539b582e	nurse	Bread, some cheese, and perhaps soup if the range still works.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	296	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_17791e6a	nurse	We do not need a feast.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	296	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_739eed77	nurse	Just enough to keep our strength.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	296	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_60866fce	doctor	Very well.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	306	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_7ba5e9ac	doctor	What can I do to help?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	306	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_c1611f4a	psychic	I think Rosalind and I can manage, Doctor.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	312	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_8e1f4477	psychic	Perhaps you could set the table?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	312	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_c887c4b6	doctor	Certainly.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	318	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_0e2e4f1f	doctor	I shall do that.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	318	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_6a21e925	psychic	And maybe Mr Harring can go with you?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	324	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_dc3f2d24	lad	Yeah, alright.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	328	lad "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_25a617ab	lad	I'll tag along, Doctor.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	328	lad "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_f5b5fdbc		Ted Harring and I set the table, then he excuses himself.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	338	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_02291fab		I linger a moment, looking at the place where we have eaten for three days.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	338	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_75b40da4		It feels oddly grand for just the four of us.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	338	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_01b1bc39		I cannot help thinking of my own home, and my own table.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	338	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_7e418f56		Soon enough, the two ladies join us with our makeshift lunch.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	338	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_460b15d0		Ted Harring returns a moment later.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	338	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_3a9cd996	psychic	There you are.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	352	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_9a7e6ce0	psychic	It is not much, but it will see us through the day.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	352	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_acc007d1	doctor	It looks excellent.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	358	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_42e5e9fe	doctor	Thank you.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	358	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_d58da20d		We sit and begin to eat at once.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	364	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_697dd485		I believe we are all famished.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	364	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_9626aff5		For a time, we eat without speaking.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	364	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_46390de2		Halfway through my bread, an odd taste blooms at the back of my tongue.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	376	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_f05f6afe		Bitter.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	376	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_e9a1d2cb		Metallic.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	376	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_2da4fecc		I pause, chewing more slowly.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	376	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_b0839d06		My stomach tightens as if a fist has closed around it.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	376	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_b4a99683		I set my knife down carefully, as though the smallest sound might split my skull.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	376	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_fb2d635f		The room seems to tilt, ever so slightly.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	376	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_bcf6dd4d		No.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	376	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_e396f948		Not the room.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	376	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_4997fee2		It is me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	376	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_e066997e	doctor	Forgive me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	398	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_33bde4ba	doctor	I feel quite unwell.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	398	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_e17bd28e	lad	What?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	404	lad "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_a858f2e0	lad	Doctor, you alright?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	404	lad "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_b8a80719	nurse	Doctor?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	410	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_5951e9be	nurse	Daniel, what is it?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	410	nurse "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_fd70e395		Heat rushes through my chest, then drains away at once.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	416	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_79e2e15a		My hands have gone cold.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	416	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_12b871e0		The edges of my vision darken, as if someone is drawing curtains.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	416	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_bc73afe6		I try to stand.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	416	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_a09d7bc4		My legs do not answer properly.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	416	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_419641b2		The chair scrapes.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	416	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_4b236812		The sound is far too loud.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	416	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_e672b1e7		I reach for the table, but my fingers miss the edge.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	416	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_49d060c1	lad	Careful!	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	434	lad "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_d57ad649	lad	Doctor!	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	434	lad "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_3fa4af9b		The floor rises to meet me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	440	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_7ca69a5b		My shoulder strikes first, then my cheek.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	440	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_67165a5b		Voices rush in, muffled and distant, as though I am submerged.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	440	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_6fc77545		The ceiling swims.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	440	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_nurse_kitchen_b90f4c3e		Then the light folds in on itself.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_nurse.rpy	440	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_8e0221b2		Ted Harring pauses for a second.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	6	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_b92343a2		I can see my revelations have troubled him.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	6	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_1746642b		He does not seem certain what he ought to do.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	6	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_450d1918		Ted Harring answers without hesitation.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	16	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_618cd510	lad	Of course, I'll stay.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	20	lad "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_c85bf0ac	lad	Only a monster would leave you alone like this.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	20	lad "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_83853800	psychic	Thank you, Mr Harring.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	26	psychic normal "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_f8d7357c	psychic	That means the world to me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	26	psychic normal "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_a001c80a	captain	Very well.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	32	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_79848eb3	captain	Doctor Baldwin and I will go at once.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	32	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_99317e13	captain	I do not wish to lose time, darkness will be upon us soon.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	32	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_81cd0af7	captain	With luck, we shall be back with help tonight.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	32	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_6ab028df	psychic	Very well, we will wait here.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	42	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_b3f03bfd	psychic	Hopefully nothing will happen until then.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	42	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_1b09f633	captain	Then it is decided.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	48	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_b6ca7f71	captain	Doctor, let us take the bare necessities from our rooms and be on our way.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	48	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_c4e948f4	captain	The sooner, the better.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	48	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_8b77cd6d		We took only a few things to help us on the road.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	60	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_a4f311b3		Most of our luggage remains at the manor.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	60	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_9c2cdf1a		We shall have it back soon enough, I hope.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	60	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_3d095c3a	doctor	That was a rather swift departure.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	68	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_3c125b67	captain	Perhaps.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	72	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_347e689a	captain	But we were at an impasse.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	72	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_9b22d76d	captain	I do not believe we would have learned more by staying.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	72	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_cef267ad	captain	There was no point in delaying the inevitable.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	72	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_32f45e3f	captain	Night will be upon us before long, and we must not waste a moment.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	72	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_eb07bfc8	doctor	Indeed.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	84	doctor "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_7cf05a63		We set off at a brisk pace, hoping to reach the town before dark.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	88	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_1b6999d9		A couple of hours in, I am exhausted.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	96	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_ce0a7aca		If I had been at my best, I might have kept up with Captain Sinha.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	106	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_be800511		But my withdrawal is at its peak, and my pace is wretchedly slow.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	106	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_83feb9e3		He tried to encourage me at first.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	106	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_bc4678a8		Soon enough, he grew tired of waiting.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	106	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_b6894e4e		He is now well ahead, and with darkness drawing in, I can barely make him out in the distance.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	106	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_c1463164		It does not slow.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	122	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_4429a6c8		It is coming at full speed towards me.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	122	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_1681ed27		Have they not seen me?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	122	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_4aafb9bc		I turn and try to run.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	122	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_9aa0a2c9		But I am too weak.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	122	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_f9b9a7fa		My legs give way, and I fall hard to the ground.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	122	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_1a220d1e		I look back at the car.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	138	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_aeb8d23d		It only seems to be gaining speed.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	138	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_06e56be6		I brace for impact.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	138	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_4244ef81		If Captain Sinha is tired as well, he does not show it.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	150	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_9179b56f		I do not dare ask him to slow down.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	150	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_eefde9f6		I will have to endure until we reach the town.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	150	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_79b88840		Hopefully it will not be much longer now.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	150	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_4f49a8be		It stops right beside us.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	164	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_without_psychic_88e9c63b		I can't see the driver, so I step closer, hoping to find a familiar face.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	164	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_hear_car_dbeec255		I think I can hear something coming.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	177	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_hear_car_e798b18c		It sounds like a motor car.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	183	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_hear_car_5c667539		It is coming from behind.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	183	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_hear_car_e726ae14		Could it be that the others finally found a way out?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	183	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_hear_car_5986887c		I turn around.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	183	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_hear_car_a3add2d4		I think I recognise Lady Claythorn's car.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	183	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_hear_car_fb7d8fcf		I wave at it.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	183	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_f625be39	lad	I don't know.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	202	lad "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_86434a3a	lad	After everything they've just told us, I don't think we're safe.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	202	lad "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_2605cd17	lad	Not even if the two of us stay behind.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	202	lad "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_7d532dbb	psychic	But I cannot travel that far.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	210	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_73289b65		Ted Harring stares at the floor, ashamed.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	214	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_03f1d30d		He looks as though he wishes he could vanish into the carpet.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	214	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_0253a351	lad	I'm sorry.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	220	lad "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_95e52e9c	lad	I can't stay here any longer.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	220	lad "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_0449e077	lad	I can't.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	220	lad "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_e7722f62	psychic	What?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	228	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_3e5b4f5d	psychic	Are you truly going to abandon me?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	228	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_6f389123	psychic	And you, Doctor?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	228	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_ce3a78bf	psychic	Or you, Captain?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	228	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_636ad59a	psychic	Can't one of you stay with me?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	228	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_350140a5		An awkward silence follows.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	240	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_9caff37d		None of us replies.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	240	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_e44c67bf	psychic	Oh, I see.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	246	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_2f1cc96b	psychic	So there is no chance of convincing you, is there?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	246	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_89cf62f6	captain	I would stay, of course.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	252	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_01026afc	captain	But I am afraid you will need my experience to make the journey.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	252	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_4ef1fa11		Experience to walk along a road.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	258	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_6114d98d		It is an odd remark from a decorated soldier.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	258	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_50c73572		Could it be that, behind his impassive face, he is frightened after all?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	258	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_3e5aac63	psychic	Very well.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	266	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_582a142c	psychic	Then I have no choice but to come with you.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	266	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_b80e26cb	captain	Are you quite certain?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	272	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_c39e2856	captain	It will not be an easy walk.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	272	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_c9524329	psychic	I am certain.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	278	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_521739d6	psychic	I will likely be slower than you.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	278	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_4122e952	psychic	I trust you will not leave me behind.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	278	psychic "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_a001c80a	captain	Very well.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	286	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_749cb13a	captain	Let us prepare ourselves before we set off.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	286	captain "[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_3bf152a0		Captain Sinha instructs us to take the bare minimum from our rooms.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	292	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_cc7b5ce3		He tells us to meet outside without delay.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	292	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_5a4f82ce		Once the four of us were ready, we wasted no time and took to the road.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	300	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_555bcd39		Our progress was slow, but we stayed together for two long hours.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	300	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_acd42945		I had begun to lose hope when we finally reached Aberdeen.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	300	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_e55186e3		After a quick search, we located the police station.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	300	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_c325d3ef		We entered in a rush, calling for help.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	316	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_e10b5471		We must have looked half-mad.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	316	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_bc4ec342		It took some time before anyone took us seriously.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	316	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_91c7e237		They sent men to check on the manor, while we remained to give our statements.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	316	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_12aa2b20		I explained everything, insisting on the peculiar situation of Samuel Manning.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	316	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_51bb2b19		A couple of hours later, they returned.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	332	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_cb88ff8f		By then, we had given our statements twice over.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	332	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_9d655d63		With sombre faces, they told us they had found another body.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	332	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_8ee25edd		Rosalind Marsh.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	332	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_3d9a1080		She was in the attic, stabbed to death.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	332	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_d35ccde1		Even if we half expected it, the news struck us hard.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	332	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_aa9287e2		My mind went at once to Andrew.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	332	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_cb5b45fe		What could have become of him?	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	332	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_648c2566		They had found nothing to explain where Lady Claythorn and the staff had gone.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	332	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_ebd1d27b		In the days that followed, the police contacted the families of the missing guests.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	332	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_f5d50465		We were asked to remain nearby for a short while.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	332	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_33210d38		They soon dismissed us as suspects.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	332	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_e1d72f36		They accepted the most obvious conclusion.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	332	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_35187d58		The culprits were among the missing.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	332	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_2c913902		Their motives remained unclear.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	332	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_0458d7f3		Captain Sinha, Ted Harring, and Amelia Baxter eventually returned home.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	364	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_7d06a23d		As for me, I tried to find Andrew again.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	364	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_2ab43e26		I asked after him.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	364	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_a4eaaeb4		I described him.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	364	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_c987635c		I waited near the station, hoping he would appear as if nothing had happened.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	364	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_eeefaeab		He never did.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	364	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_5df75097		I can only hope he is all right.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	364	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_f55bc011		And that he had the sense to keep moving.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	364	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_4ff43692		A week later, I returned to the police station one last time.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	382	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_2c4c48c6		They were ready to move on.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	382	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_26ec0dbe		Yet they had just received unsettling news.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	382	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_aa8c22c2		They had found Thomas Moody's mother, and informed her of her son's death.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	382	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_54300fdd		But when they told her Thomas was dead, she said they were mistaken.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	382	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_b5dc2611		Thomas Moody had died months ago, apparently from war injuries.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	382	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_a29f1fd7		Then she added something else.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	382	"[what]"
doctor_day3_afternoon_captain_escape_with_psychic_0caec45c		Her other son, Archibald, had been missing for a week or more.	game/scripts/doctor/Day 3/2_Afternoon/3a_captain_escape.rpy	382	"[what]"
doctor_ending_escape_16a28bb6		You escaped.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_endings.rpy	8	"[what]"
doctor_ending_escape_0a079de8		Three other guests were fortunate enough to leave the manor alive with you.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_endings.rpy	8	"[what]"
doctor_ending_escape_978f1433		By now, you may have a clearer understanding of what has been happening.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_endings.rpy	8	"[what]"
doctor_ending_escape_1e7acc2e		But do not blame yourself too harshly if you don't.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_endings.rpy	8	"[what]"
doctor_ending_escape_e57817de		There are still plenty of secrets to uncover at Claythorn Manor.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_endings.rpy	8	"[what]"
doctor_ending_poisoned_3bec7c03		You chose to trust, and you paid the price.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_endings.rpy	29	"[what]"
doctor_ending_poisoned_069840bc		You were close to the end but you let your guard down.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_endings.rpy	29	"[what]"
doctor_ending_run_over_dbe245fd		You were hit by a car while crouching on the floor.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_endings.rpy	45	"[what]"
doctor_ending_run_over_71d6ac71		If you had more strength, you probably could have outrun it, or at least avoided it.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_endings.rpy	45	"[what]"
doctor_ending_run_over_b344de1d		Perhaps you didn't pick the best of times to stop taking drugs.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_endings.rpy	45	"[what]"
doctor_ending_shot_ae3e9023		You were shot in the face.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_endings.rpy	63	"[what]"
doctor_ending_shot_e46a31e8		It happened so quickly that you did not even see who pulled the trigger.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_endings.rpy	63	"[what]"
doctor_ending_shot_a0fdf2b9		There was no warning.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_endings.rpy	63	"[what]"
doctor_ending_shot_19af065f		No time to think.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_endings.rpy	63	"[what]"
doctor_ending_shot_4086799f		Only the sharp crack of a pistol, and a brief, dreadful heat.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_endings.rpy	63	"[what]"
doctor_ending_shot_0ea32858		You were so close to getting out alive.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_endings.rpy	63	"[what]"
doctor_ending_shot_e5dff5e2		What a pity.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_endings.rpy	63	"[what]"
doctor_ending_burn_5c284ab3		A dreadful fire burned the manor down.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_endings.rpy	89	"[what]"
doctor_ending_burn_df513904		Trapped in your room, there was no possible way to escape.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_endings.rpy	89	"[what]"
doctor_ending_burn_0c5e61f1		What a ghastly end.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_endings.rpy	89	"[what]"
doctor_ending_overdose_55b047b9		You thought you could manage it, but you were mistaken.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_endings.rpy	107	"[what]"
doctor_ending_overdose_c8b7964b		That last spoonful was one too many.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_endings.rpy	107	"[what]"
doctor_ending_overdose_fd5e85a0		You will have to be more careful next time.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_endings.rpy	107	"[what]"
doctor_ending_shot_by_drunk_d28f9d31		Despite knowing better, you still joined a hunt with a half-drunk man and a loaded gun.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_endings.rpy	132	"[what]"
doctor_ending_shot_by_drunk_8d2d452b		At least this dreadful end might teach you to make wiser choices next time.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_endings.rpy	132	"[what]"
doctor_ending_throat_cut_01b7f085		You believed yourself safe.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_endings.rpy	148	"[what]"
doctor_ending_throat_cut_abb26407		Yet there was something you failed to see.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_endings.rpy	148	"[what]"
doctor_ending_throat_cut_426e31f7		Alone in your room, you were an easy target for whoever wished you harm.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_endings.rpy	148	"[what]"
doctor_ending_throat_cut_1a86bc36		Sometimes the safest path lies in choosing whom to trust, rather than trusting no one at all.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_endings.rpy	148	"[what]"
doctor_ending_throat_cut_530d2787		It's dangerous to go alone.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_endings.rpy	148	"[what]"
doctor_generic_weather_friday_16f8bc4d	doctor	A dreadful storm, if you ask me.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_choices.rpy	19	doctor "[what]"
doctor_generic_weather_friday_89da7f21	doctor	I don't know what's planned for tomorrow, but I hope it doesn't involve leaving this house.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_choices.rpy	19	doctor "[what]"
doctor_generic_weather_saturday_bc481e4d	doctor	We are lucky that the weather improved greatly today.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_choices.rpy	29	doctor "[what]"
doctor_generic_weather_saturday_fd26c2a2	doctor	For a while, I thought we would be trapped inside the manor all weekend.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_choices.rpy	29	doctor "[what]"
doctor_generic_weather_saturday_9e6c59b4	doctor	But everything seems fine now.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_choices.rpy	29	doctor "[what]"
doctor_generic_background_8cb5ccff	doctor	I am the chief physician at St. Margaret's Hospital.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_choices.rpy	42	doctor "[what]"
doctor_generic_background_c47b9446	doctor	It's a charity hospital for those in need.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_choices.rpy	42	doctor "[what]"
doctor_generic_background_29bb6bb6	doctor	Before that, I worked a bit all over the place.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_choices.rpy	42	doctor "[what]"
doctor_generic_background_e30c1206	doctor	I also served in the army several times, including the last one.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_choices.rpy	42	doctor "[what]"
doctor_generic_background_96cad275	doctor	That one was the worst, of course.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_choices.rpy	42	doctor "[what]"
doctor_generic_heroic_act_02098290	doctor	Well, I recently celebrated my ten years at St. Margaret's.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_choices.rpy	61	doctor "[what]"
doctor_generic_heroic_act_0b959352	doctor	Not many people stay that long at this type of institution.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_choices.rpy	61	doctor "[what]"
doctor_generic_heroic_act_c6a7ef16	doctor	Usually, doctors stay for a few years to build a reputation, then move on to a more luxurious practice.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_choices.rpy	61	doctor "[what]"
doctor_generic_heroic_act_f289d882	doctor	Lady Claythorn must have understood the sacrifice I've made, hence the reward.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_choices.rpy	61	doctor "[what]"
doctor_generic_heroic_act_0958fd5b	doctor	Not that I consider it a sacrifice, of course.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_choices.rpy	61	doctor "[what]"
doctor_generic_heroic_act_06c55d29	doctor	I love my job and wouldn't change it for the world.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_choices.rpy	61	doctor "[what]"
doctor_generic_heroic_act_b6b89a71	doctor	Still, it's always nice to receive some recognition.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_choices.rpy	61	doctor "[what]"
doctor_generic_manor_077d4ca1	doctor	It's a nice house.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_choices.rpy	83	doctor "[what]"
doctor_generic_manor_22750301	doctor	But I can't say much more about it.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_choices.rpy	83	doctor "[what]"
doctor_generic_manor_996f90a4	doctor	I'm not used to visiting such places.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_choices.rpy	83	doctor "[what]"
doctor_generic_manor_4d2e97a9	doctor	This is the first time I've been invited to a grand mansion as a guest and not as a doctor.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_choices.rpy	83	doctor "[what]"
doctor_generic_manor_bfad5a83	doctor	The truth is, my job doesn't pay that much.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_choices.rpy	83	doctor "[what]"
doctor_generic_manor_f0b461e7	doctor	Nevertheless, I'm content with my small apartment.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_choices.rpy	83	doctor "[what]"
doctor_generic_manor_12ed998e	doctor	I wouldn't want anything this big; it must be such a hassle to manage.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_choices.rpy	83	doctor "[what]"
doctor_generic_manor_f439cc28	lad	So you're not accustomed to having a butler and footmen around?	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_choices.rpy	100	lad "[what]"
doctor_generic_manor_5be65b5c	doctor	No, I can't say that I am.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_choices.rpy	104	doctor "[what]"
doctor_generic_manor_33e212d7		Well, that's rather comforting.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_choices.rpy	108	"[what]"
doctor_generic_age_095d54c0	doctor	I'm 39 years old. Why do you ask?	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_choices.rpy	118	doctor "[what]"
doctor_generic_age_09631219	lad	Actually, I'm not sure.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_choices.rpy	123	lad "[what]"
doctor_generic_room_fcbf77e5	doctor	I'm staying in the Edward II room.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_choices.rpy	133	doctor "[what]"
doctor_tea_room_default_5f170ed7		There is not a soul in here and nothing to do at the moment.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_locations.rpy	23	"[what]"
doctor_tea_room_default_7ca33d49		No need to stay any longer.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_locations.rpy	23	"[what]"
doctor_library_default_ed71b42e		That is a well-furnished library.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_locations.rpy	38	"[what]"
doctor_library_default_da4ead7d		But with everything that has happened, I do not feel like reading today.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_locations.rpy	38	"[what]"
doctor_library_default_3eb097a1		I really don't feel like reading today.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_locations.rpy	48	"[what]"
doctor_portrait_gallery_default_ea39dd4d		This is clearly where the Claythorn family display their portraits.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_locations.rpy	61	"[what]"
doctor_portrait_gallery_default_c9d49b45		It's rather odd to have so many crammed into such a small room.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_locations.rpy	61	"[what]"
doctor_portrait_gallery_default_fdd1183b		It gives the place quite an eerie atmosphere.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_locations.rpy	61	"[what]"
doctor_portrait_gallery_default_0d1b7cf8		I don't feel comfortable lingering here too long.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_locations.rpy	61	"[what]"
doctor_portrait_gallery_default_545c1465		It still gives me an eerie feeling.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_locations.rpy	75	"[what]"
doctor_portrait_gallery_default_cd7f6a54		I'd rather not stay.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_locations.rpy	75	"[what]"
doctor_dining_room_default_f256735b		The dining room.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_locations.rpy	103	"[what]"
doctor_dining_room_default_0f2bf6cf		No need to linger, nobody will come back here until tomorrow.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_locations.rpy	103	"[what]"
doctor_entrance_hall_default_d67f3e10		I feel compelled to take another look at this entrance hall.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_locations.rpy	129	"[what]"
doctor_entrance_hall_default_d75ea669		It is quite magnificent.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_locations.rpy	129	"[what]"
doctor_entrance_hall_default_689a50e8		I take in the view for a few minutes.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_locations.rpy	129	"[what]"
doctor_entrance_hall_default_e90e7307		Nobody comes.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_locations.rpy	129	"[what]"
doctor_bedroom_default_c29a4ffd	doctor	Hello, is anyone there?	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_locations.rpy	149	doctor "[what]"
doctor_bedroom_default_cde4eaca		There is no answer.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_locations.rpy	153	"[what]"
doctor_attic_default_96169023		I decide to take the stairs to the attic.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_locations.rpy	200	"[what]"
doctor_attic_default_126d7e47		I probably shouldn't be here but I could still feign ignorance if I am spotted.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_locations.rpy	200	"[what]"
doctor_attic_closed_79805797		The door is locked.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_locations.rpy	215	"[what]"
doctor_attic_closed_0be35494		That's no surprise.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_locations.rpy	215	"[what]"
doctor_attic_closed_f94a27f8		Whoever is sleeping here must keep the key close to themselves.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_generic_locations.rpy	215	"[what]"
doctor_generic_other_guests_friday_5fbe33e0	doctor	Oh, I haven't talked to many people so far.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_other_guests.rpy	9	doctor "[what]"
doctor_generic_other_guests_friday_b5406c7b	doctor	I think the only person I've heard speak is Mr Sinha.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_other_guests.rpy	9	doctor "[what]"
doctor_generic_other_guests_friday_b88b3ccd	doctor	And by "heard," I really just mean heard.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_other_guests.rpy	9	doctor "[what]"
doctor_generic_other_guests_friday_0bd5ac13	doctor	Because I don't think I was able to contribute anything to the conversation.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_other_guests.rpy	9	doctor "[what]"
doctor_generic_other_guests_friday_07a957e5		Yes, I can understand that feeling.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_other_guests.rpy	21	"[what]"
doctor_generic_other_guests_saturday_6b5ca168	doctor	I haven't spoken in detail with anyone yet.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_other_guests.rpy	31	doctor "[what]"
doctor_generic_other_guests_saturday_71b731eb	doctor	So, I don't really have an opinion on the guests.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_other_guests.rpy	31	doctor "[what]"
doctor_generic_drunk_6f628454	doctor	Well, I think by now you can tell as well as I can that he is a dangerous drunk.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_other_guests.rpy	41	doctor "[what]"
doctor_generic_drunk_fc4d5169	doctor	We'd better stay away from him.	game/scripts/doctor/doctor_other_guests.rpy	41	doctor "[what]"
drunk_generic_weather_friday_dinner_a59ee269	drunk	The weather?	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	17	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_weather_friday_dinner_53c71378	drunk	Splendid.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	21	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_weather_friday_dinner_6652fdc5	drunk	Absolutely... splendid.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	21	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_weather_friday_dinner_6ebda6e9	drunk	Or is it dreadful?	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	21	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_weather_friday_dinner_b46600b1	drunk	No matter.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	21	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_weather_friday_dinner_f84ea5f4	nurse	Of course.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	31	nurse "[what]"
drunk_generic_weather_friday_dinner_3b77f234		Well, at least he is not worried about the storm.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	35	"[what]"
drunk_generic_background_nurse_7d7cf2eb	drunk	About myself?	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	44	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_background_nurse_7c469190	nurse	Yes, if you don't mind.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	48	nurse "[what]"
drunk_generic_background_nurse_954355e2	nurse	What is your profession?	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	48	nurse "[what]"
drunk_generic_background_nurse_a3938b18	drunk	Ah, well.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	54	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_background_nurse_ca4963c7	drunk	I am a man of the law.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	54	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_background_nurse_772f05e6	drunk	A barrister, you see.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	54	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_background_nurse_d6ec9415	drunk	Or I was.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	54	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_background_nurse_15c02ce0	drunk	Doesn't... doesn't quite matter now, does it.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	54	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_background_nurse_497336e0	nurse	Oh, and what sort of barrister were you?	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	66	nurse "[what]"
drunk_generic_background_nurse_b9ab6902	drunk	A defence barrister.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	70	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_background_nurse_26013131	drunk	Look, it's... it's complicated.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	70	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_background_nurse_be25da6a	drunk	I'd rather not bore a lady.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	70	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_background_nurse_824ff5e1	nurse	Why did you stop, Mr Manning?	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	78	nurse "[what]"
drunk_generic_background_nurse_16f15c6e	drunk	Why did I stop.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	82	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_background_nurse_44bab723	drunk	There were cases.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	82	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_background_nurse_0d320e20	drunk	Cases I should not have taken.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	82	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_background_nurse_6cf13503	drunk	Or should have... handled differently.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	82	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_background_nurse_6ca9251c	drunk	The law is a merciless thing when you get it wrong.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	82	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_background_nurse_0766dcc4	nurse	What happened?	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	94	nurse "[what]"
drunk_generic_background_nurse_7de9ee52	drunk	Nothing worth repeating.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	98	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_background_nurse_7e15d25a	drunk	Ancient history, all of it.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	98	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_background_nurse_2840c842		He trails off and stares into his glass.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	104	"[what]"
drunk_generic_background_nurse_0ee373a7		Hard to believe this person is, or at least was an attorney.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	104	"[what]"
drunk_generic_background_nurse_56d5801a		I wonder what could have happened to him to make him like this.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	104	"[what]"
drunk_generic_heroic_act_nurse_ac61d1ad	nurse	Why were you invited here, Mr Manning?	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	119	nurse "[what]"
drunk_generic_heroic_act_nurse_cb4d60d6	drunk	Invited?	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	123	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_heroic_act_nurse_4a379eef	drunk	I was... invited because I am a man of... of the people.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	123	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_heroic_act_nurse_ad2ee8ed	drunk	Or so they seem to think.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	123	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_heroic_act_nurse_6bc8c9c6	drunk	I've taken on cases no one else would touch.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	123	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_heroic_act_nurse_bd3b8648	drunk	The poor, the... the desperate.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	123	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_heroic_act_nurse_f882e871	drunk	Someone has to, don't they?	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	123	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_heroic_act_nurse_548f0a36	nurse	That is rather admirable of you.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	137	nurse "[what]"
drunk_generic_heroic_act_nurse_b45dbb87	drunk	Admirable.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	141	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_heroic_act_nurse_2706915e	drunk	Ha.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	141	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_heroic_act_nurse_4ee5a783	drunk	Yes, well.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	141	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_heroic_act_nurse_ff70c272	drunk	Don't go writing it in the papers.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	141	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_heroic_act_nurse_e609645b		A brief, bitter laugh escapes him.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	151	"[what]"
drunk_generic_heroic_act_nurse_3ca40732		Whatever good he has done, it clearly brings him little comfort.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	151	"[what]"
drunk_generic_manor_ef6f869b	drunk	Grand old place, isn't it.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	164	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_manor_2108edea	drunk	Full of... full of history, I suppose.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	164	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_age_3a6908cb	drunk	How old am I?	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	175	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_age_ca5cdef7	drunk	Too old for all of this.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	175	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_age_65bb4eb4	drunk	Fifty-five years, if you must know.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	175	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_age_b71af74b	drunk	Fifty-five years and... and not a thing to show for it.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	175	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_age_6578f116		He empties his glass.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	185	"[what]"
drunk_generic_age_9aef1433		Then he waves to the footman for another one.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	185	"[what]"
drunk_generic_age_8a8412ce		Fifty-five years.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	185	"[what]"
drunk_generic_age_096abd3d		Yet he looks a great deal older.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	185	"[what]"
drunk_generic_room_friday_359cfa4f	drunk	A room?	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	202	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_room_friday_2f125fdf	drunk	They've given me a room, have they.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	202	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_room_friday_eea67997	drunk	Generous of them.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	202	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_room_friday_a398b005	drunk	I... I couldn't tell you which one.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	202	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_room_friday_64018fd3	drunk	I haven't had the chance to see it yet.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	202	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_room_nurse_9b145179	drunk	The... the "George IV" room, I believe.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	219	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_room_nurse_7386dfd4	drunk	Or some such name.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	219	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_room_nurse_c5cf3552	drunk	Those kings, they all run together after a while.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	219	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_other_guests_friday_dinner_75452f9b	drunk	The other guests?	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	234	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_other_guests_friday_dinner_9452f293	drunk	Interesting lot.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	238	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_other_guests_friday_dinner_30fedf91	drunk	Very... very interesting.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	238	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_other_guests_friday_dinner_54e784f1	drunk	I'm sure they're all perfectly fine.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	238	drunk "[what]"
drunk_generic_other_guests_friday_dinner_706c124a		He waves a hand vaguely in the direction of the dining table.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	246	"[what]"
drunk_generic_other_guests_friday_dinner_84b7b312		I suppose that is as much as I shall get from him.	game/scripts/drunk/drunk_generic_choices.rpy	246	"[what]"
ending_generic_9e793168		You made it out alive.	game/scripts/endings.rpy	13	"[what]"
ending_generic_9220702b		But it's not the perfect ending either.	game/scripts/endings.rpy	13	"[what]"
ending_generic_01e3b003		Don't get me wrong, it's still an impressive feat.	game/scripts/endings.rpy	13	"[what]"
ending_generic_89839b75		But surviving Claythorn Manor is merely the first step.	game/scripts/endings.rpy	13	"[what]"
ending_generic_b18039d1		Your goal is to save everyone.	game/scripts/endings.rpy	13	"[what]"
ending_generic_8b5ad905		And to do that, you need to start the story over.	game/scripts/endings.rpy	26	"[what]"
ending_generic_0a22607b		Don't worry, you'll have more chances to change the fate of this character.	game/scripts/endings.rpy	34	"[what]"
ending_generic_f99991b1		You can start again now. Ideally, you've learned something that will help you in your next attempts.	game/scripts/endings.rpy	34	"[what]"
ending_generic_8982cf3b		But perhaps you haven't learned anything.	game/scripts/endings.rpy	34	"[what]"
ending_generic_2cd1d5bf		In that case, try to look at the story from a different perspective.	game/scripts/endings.rpy	34	"[what]"
ending_generic_350af135		This story isn't about just one hero.	game/scripts/endings.rpy	34	"[what]"
ending_generic_98944632		You'll get to play as different characters.	game/scripts/endings.rpy	34	"[what]"
ending_generic_5c700a8f		And you must.	game/scripts/endings.rpy	34	"[what]"
ending_generic_c767a620		Otherwise you will never uncover the whole truth of what happened that weekend at Claythorn Manor.	game/scripts/endings.rpy	34	"[what]"
host_introduction_dbee7c6b	butler	Al right, from now on you are the lady of this place. Don't forget it.	game/scripts/host/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	25	butler "[what]"
host_introduction_7b86e200	host	I don't understand why you can't be the lord.	game/scripts/host/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	29	host "[what]"
host_introduction_280e0f46	host	You will clearly be better at it than I.	game/scripts/host/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	29	host "[what]"
host_introduction_33029a59	butler	You mean because I am the better actor?	game/scripts/host/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	35	butler "[what]"
host_introduction_01aba996	host	I didn't say that.	game/scripts/host/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	39	host "[what]"
host_introduction_6e4fe814	host	And you are not.	game/scripts/host/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	39	host "[what]"
host_introduction_7f5030a2	host	But I know you are familiar with that type of house.	game/scripts/host/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	39	host "[what]"
host_introduction_d9529d9c	butler	Right, I was a footman when I was younger, a very long time ago.	game/scripts/host/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	47	butler "[what]"
host_introduction_351caf3c	butler	But that's precisely why I should be the butler.	game/scripts/host/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	47	butler "[what]"
host_introduction_3973ddd5	butler	You see, in this kind of environment, the staff is more scrutinize that than the host.	game/scripts/host/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	47	butler "[what]"
host_introduction_e5ded49c	butler	That's a rule.	game/scripts/host/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	47	butler "[what]"
host_introduction_89b0113c	butler	As the Lady of the house, you can do almost anything.	game/scripts/host/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	47	butler "[what]"
host_introduction_e3b3616d	butler	At worst you'll be labelled "eccentric".	game/scripts/host/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	47	butler "[what]"
host_introduction_41adcd87	butler	But to maintain the illusion, the staff can't afford a mistake.	game/scripts/host/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	47	butler "[what]"
host_introduction_7c6aacb0	butler	That's why I have to be in charge of them.	game/scripts/host/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	47	butler "[what]"
host_introduction_e146c6ce	butler	Besides, a butler must always be a man.	game/scripts/host/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	47	butler "[what]"
host_introduction_045c030e	host	Right.	game/scripts/host/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	67	host "[what]"
host_introduction_f1cee129	butler	But let's go in, the rest of our staff arrived yesterday to prepare the house.	game/scripts/host/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	71	butler "[what]"
host_introduction_cb0c350c	butler	Now it's time to explain what's expected of them.	game/scripts/host/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	71	butler "[what]"
host_introduction_d70e9749		The "Staff", are actually all actors, some with very little domestic experience, if any.	game/scripts/host/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	77	"[what]"
host_introduction_d87aea00		But I've been assured that the guests we are receiving won't be accustomed to all this.	game/scripts/host/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	77	"[what]"
host_introduction_6485e6a8		None of them is from a standing important enough so that they should notice little mistakes with the service.	game/scripts/host/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	77	"[what]"
host_introduction_8d40e561		Still, that would an incredible feat if the weekend goes as planned.	game/scripts/host/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	77	"[what]"
host_generic_weather_f549eeba	host	A mixture of rain and good weather.	game/scripts/host/host_generic_choices.rpy	17	host "[what]"
host_generic_weather_49503293	host	That is actually as good as it gets for the region, I am afraid.	game/scripts/host/host_generic_choices.rpy	17	host "[what]"
host_generic_weather_77eca2ac	host	One must learn to appreciate the mist as much as the sun.	game/scripts/host/host_generic_choices.rpy	17	host "[what]"
host_generic_background_1b56b705	host	There isn't much to say.	game/scripts/host/host_generic_choices.rpy	30	host "[what]"
host_generic_background_85fb0c0d	host	I have been the mistress of this estate since my late father passed away.	game/scripts/host/host_generic_choices.rpy	30	host "[what]"
host_generic_background_2a24e15b	host	That would have been nearly ten years ago.	game/scripts/host/host_generic_choices.rpy	30	host "[what]"
host_generic_background_b79db0c3	host	I now manage the domain as well as I can.	game/scripts/host/host_generic_choices.rpy	30	host "[what]"
host_generic_background_b4a5649c	host	But I don't really like to talk about myself.	game/scripts/host/host_generic_choices.rpy	30	host "[what]"
host_generic_background_nurse_70422dd8		That's peculiar, the gentry usually love to talk about themselves.	game/scripts/host/host_generic_choices.rpy	49	"[what]"
host_generic_background_nurse_0065993c		But she could just be a little shy.	game/scripts/host/host_generic_choices.rpy	49	"[what]"
host_generic_invite_nurse_bf871ff8	host	Everything was explained in the letter, was it not?	game/scripts/host/host_generic_choices.rpy	59	host "[what]"
host_generic_invite_nurse_ae3d9215	nurse	True, but it didn't mention the reasons for this very selfless act.	game/scripts/host/host_generic_choices.rpy	63	nurse "[what]"
host_generic_invite_nurse_87b6e487	host	One does not think reasons are necessary to thank people who did exceptional things.	game/scripts/host/host_generic_choices.rpy	67	host "[what]"
host_generic_invite_nurse_43d8b0f0	host	Such as yourself.	game/scripts/host/host_generic_choices.rpy	67	host "[what]"
host_generic_invite_nurse_d1c6f4bd	host	What a great sacrifice you have made, giving most of your life for the welfare of others.	game/scripts/host/host_generic_choices.rpy	67	host "[what]"
host_generic_invite_nurse_f9326757	host	It is my great pleasure to give you something in return, since I have been blessed myself.	game/scripts/host/host_generic_choices.rpy	67	host "[what]"
host_generic_invite_nurse_b156f5d7	nurse	That's very generous.	game/scripts/host/host_generic_choices.rpy	77	nurse "[what]"
host_generic_invite_nurse_ac1ff6b4	nurse	So you've been doing that often?	game/scripts/host/host_generic_choices.rpy	77	nurse "[what]"
host_generic_invite_nurse_e987e953	host	Well, no, that is the first time I am giving away this prize.	game/scripts/host/host_generic_choices.rpy	83	host "[what]"
host_generic_invite_nurse_ec9f33ac	host	But I might do for other people in the future of course.	game/scripts/host/host_generic_choices.rpy	83	host "[what]"
host_generic_other_guests_nurse_c697968a	host	A group of people of great value.	game/scripts/host/host_generic_choices.rpy	93	host "[what]"
host_generic_other_guests_nurse_60b1da5e	host	But we shouldn't talk about them behind their backs.	game/scripts/host/host_generic_choices.rpy	93	host "[what]"
host_generic_other_guests_nurse_863e46bb	host	That is improper.	game/scripts/host/host_generic_choices.rpy	93	host "[what]"
host_generic_manor_188a32c9	host	This "place" has been in my family for quite some time.	game/scripts/host/host_generic_choices.rpy	106	host "[what]"
host_generic_manor_201d1208	host	I have always found it rather quaint.	game/scripts/host/host_generic_choices.rpy	106	host "[what]"
host_generic_manor_3702f54a	host	It is a trifle too large for me and my staff, I am afraid.	game/scripts/host/host_generic_choices.rpy	106	host "[what]"
host_generic_manor_b45b30f7	host	But I can't really give it up, it's my legacy.	game/scripts/host/host_generic_choices.rpy	106	host "[what]"
host_generic_age_nurse_dc40f9e4	host	I beg your pardon? You want to know my age?	game/scripts/host/host_generic_choices.rpy	121	host surprised "[what]"
host_generic_age_nurse_693186aa	nurse	Oh, it's just that you look so young.	game/scripts/host/host_generic_choices.rpy	125	nurse "[what]"
host_generic_age_nurse_1b05433f	nurse	And managing such a large estate must be difficult for a young lady.	game/scripts/host/host_generic_choices.rpy	125	nurse "[what]"
host_generic_age_nurse_3958d06a	host	I am not as young as I might look.	game/scripts/host/host_generic_choices.rpy	131	host -surprised "[what]"
host_generic_age_nurse_de7154cb	host	And I manage it quite well, thank you.	game/scripts/host/host_generic_choices.rpy	131	host -surprised "[what]"
host_generic_room_30cd1e5c	host	The master bedroom is named after Henry IV.	game/scripts/host/host_generic_choices.rpy	142	host "[what]"
host_generic_room_a9e81d46	host	Why, I am not sure exactly.	game/scripts/host/host_generic_choices.rpy	142	host "[what]"
lad_introduction_02033c81		As I approach my destination, I read the letter that has brought me on this trip for the tenth time.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	28	"[what]"
lad_introduction_54914e0b	letter	5th September, [current_year]	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	32	letter "[what]"
lad_introduction_996f97ad	letter	Dear Mr Harring,	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	32	letter "[what]"
lad_introduction_041e4064	letter	I am pleased to announce that you have been selected as one of the recipients of the "Exceptional Act of Bravery Award".	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	32	letter "[what]"
lad_introduction_ea79939a	letter	You'll be receiving the prize, along with six other courageous individuals, at a reception organised in your honour.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	32	letter "[what]"
lad_introduction_ca9128c1	letter	As a thank you, a weekend of leisure at Claythorn Manor has been planned for all of you to enjoy.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	32	letter "[what]"
lad_introduction_a447451d	letter	Afterwards, a prize of one thousand pounds in bearer bonds will be handed to you.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	32	letter "[what]"
lad_introduction_1e6fa86a	letter	Please note that your presence is mandatory in order to receive the prize.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	32	letter "[what]"
lad_introduction_d1389fc5	letter	All you have to do is be at Aberdeen Station, on the 13th of October around 4PM, where someone will drive you to the manor.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	32	letter "[what]"
lad_introduction_17708218	letter	Hoping to see you soon, ...	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	32	letter "[what]"
lad_introduction_e1c6b98a		More information follows, but that's about the content of it.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	52	"[what]"
lad_introduction_8a6fd04f		It is signed by "Lady Claythorn".	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	52	"[what]"
lad_introduction_031ae690		I've never heard of her.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	52	"[what]"
lad_introduction_bf874adf		I couldn't really believe it at first.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	52	"[what]"
lad_introduction_d6ca56e5		I don't think I am that deserving. At least no more than hundreds of other guys in this country.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	52	"[what]"
lad_introduction_f042ff7f		But no matter the reason, I can't possibly say no to this amount of money.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	52	"[what]"
lad_introduction_10f032c8		So I feel as if I do not have much choice.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	52	"[what]"
lad_introduction_017ffba8		But still, there's a part of me thinking,	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	52	"[what]"
lad_introduction_48a05a4a		maybe I should never have come.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	52	"[what]"
lad_introduction_52b6decd		As I step off the train, a man approaches me.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	78	"[what]"
lad_introduction_cd3257ba	footman	Welcome, sir. Are you by any chance heading to Claythorn Manor?	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	82	footman "[what]"
lad_introduction_1b7886bf	lad	Yes, as a matter of fact I am.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	86	lad "[what]"
lad_introduction_27ae9ae7		As proof, I hand him the letter that I still have in my hand.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	90	"[what]"
lad_introduction_2b13f8cc	footman	Very well, sir. Allow me to assist you with your luggage. You can follow me to the car.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	94	footman "[what]"
lad_introduction_047fa876		And just like that, we are on our way.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	98	"[what]"
lad_introduction_40afd89d	lad	So, you're Lady Claythorn's driver?	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	104	lad "[what]"
lad_introduction_a4e9988a	footman	Yes— I mean, no.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	108	footman "[what]"
lad_introduction_ba54d5d8	footman	I am actually her footman. I also drive people when necessary.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	108	footman "[what]"
lad_introduction_1b0158e4	lad	Oh. The driver must be busy with all the guests coming, I suppose.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	114	lad "[what]"
lad_introduction_a58480e4	lad	Do you know how many people have been invited this weekend?	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	114	lad "[what]"
lad_introduction_c8b265bc	footman	Well... I am not sure, sir. Half a dozen at least, I believe.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	120	footman "[what]"
lad_introduction_d6c09df9	footman	I'm sorry, sir, but I must concentrate on the road. Lady Claythorn doesn't like it when I'm distracted.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	120	footman "[what]"
lad_introduction_f9ac74ee	lad	Of course, I am sorry.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	126	lad "[what]"
lad_introduction_0d1d8cfa	footman	No need for apologies, sir.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	130	footman "[what]"
lad_introduction_e76ee63b		I seem to have made him uneasy. Perhaps he's not used to small talk with guests.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	134	"[what]"
lad_introduction_39cc19a5		This feels odd, as I'm usually on the other end of this treatment.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	134	"[what]"
lad_introduction_143ac34f		I wonder how well I'll blend in with the other folks at the manor.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	134	"[what]"
lad_introduction_4ac3eeb6		They might be used to this kind of service.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	134	"[what]"
lad_introduction_6dae6201		But then again, perhaps not. Maybe Lady Claythorn likes to help people like me.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	134	"[what]"
lad_introduction_ccd78b76		We'll see.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	134	"[what]"
lad_introduction_283ec2df		After we leave Aberdeen, we drive into the countryside, then into what seems to be a vast forest.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	134	"[what]"
lad_introduction_0627ea49		About twenty minutes later, all signs of human life disappear.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	134	"[what]"
lad_introduction_e5bb9feb		It's nothing but dense woodland as far as the eye can see.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	134	"[what]"
lad_introduction_a74443ae		The isolation makes me feel a bit uneasy, being so far from everywhere else.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	134	"[what]"
lad_introduction_2e0be89f		And the sight of an approaching storm in the sky only adds to my unease.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	134	"[what]"
lad_introduction_1d05768c		Eventually, an imposing mansion emerges on the horizon.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	164	"[what]"
lad_introduction_8ce8cec2		It's bigger than any house I've ever been in.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	164	"[what]"
lad_introduction_af26a13a		A big country house.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	164	"[what]"
lad_introduction_63686e1f		Everyone who was anyone in England used to have one.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	164	"[what]"
lad_introduction_cd839bfc		Now I've heard a lot of people can't afford them anymore.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	164	"[what]"
lad_introduction_2e9f2464		They're sold, turned into hotels, or simply abandoned—left there to rot.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	164	"[what]"
lad_introduction_b49fa377		What a shame.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	164	"[what]"
lad_introduction_3fb30bec		As the footman unloads my luggage from the car, I approach the entrance, where a butler opens the door to welcome me.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	164	"[what]"
lad_introduction_f6686c1e		I step into the most remarkable hall I've ever set foot in.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	164	"[what]"
lad_day1_evening_garden_6052df6a		I reach the great hall and prepare to open the door.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	105	"[what]"
lad_day1_evening_garden_82674b80		However, the weather is so bad that only a madman would venture out now.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	105	"[what]"
lad_day1_evening_garden_ff3b428f		I'd be better off doing something else at the moment.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	105	"[what]"
lad_bedroom_stay_away_7a7de327		Should I try to enter anyway?	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	131	"[what]"
lad_bedroom_stay_away_7ea233fb		No, that's probably a bad idea.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	131	"[what]"
lad_bedroom_drunk_default_a29689bd		After knocking, the door slightly opens.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	158	"[what]"
lad_bedroom_drunk_default_5ef83bdb		It was not even closed.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	158	"[what]"
lad_bedroom_drunk_default_b82d71ce		It would be easy to go in if I wanted to.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	158	"[what]"
lad_day1_evening_af7c6abf	butler	Welcome, sir.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	31	butler "[what]"
lad_day1_evening_bfc5411e	lad	Hello, I'm Ted Harring. I've been invited by Lady Claythorn.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	35	lad "[what]"
lad_day1_evening_3c49ff91	butler	Yes, of course, Mr Harring.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	39	butler "[what]"
lad_day1_evening_5fb86b28	butler	Welcome to Claythorn Manor.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	39	butler "[what]"
lad_day1_evening_eb4df465	butler	I am afraid you won't have time to change right now.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	39	butler "[what]"
lad_day1_evening_6d2ee9e0	butler	Everyone is already there, and dinner will be ready very soon.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	39	butler "[what]"
lad_day1_evening_5fe3f131	butler	If you'll follow me to the tea room, you may join the rest of the party for some drinks.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	39	butler "[what]"
lad_day1_evening_ab566d1f		Well, it's not as if I have multiple changes of clothes anyway. So, I follow him.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	51	"[what]"
lad_day1_evening_3ad3f9af		As I step into the room, the butler loudly announces me.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	57	"[what]"
lad_day1_evening_2ce34aae	butler	Mr Ted Harring!	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	61	butler "[what]"
lad_day1_evening_25b87273		Everyone turns their heads towards me.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	65	"[what]"
lad_day1_evening_6bebd625		Some people nod in my direction, while others barely acknowledge my presence.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	65	"[what]"
lad_day1_evening_1bd87379		From afar, the butler provides me with a brief introduction to each guest.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	65	"[what]"
lad_day1_evening_ccf17a3a	butler	The older gentleman speaking is from India, and his name is Sushil Sinha.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	74	butler "[what]"
lad_day1_evening_cac103d4	butler	He is in conversation with Rosalind Marsh...	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	81	butler "[what]"
lad_day1_evening_6540b945	butler	... and with Daniel Baldwin, the gentleman with spectacles.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	87	butler "[what]"
lad_day1_evening_21976c23	butler	Do not be alarmed by the man in the mask.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	93	butler "[what]"
lad_day1_evening_4b24db31	butler	He is a war veteran, Mr Thomas Moody.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	93	butler "[what]"
lad_day1_evening_3c6a37cf	butler	The person on the sofa, who looks rather exhausted, is Mr Samuel Manning.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	101	butler "[what]"
lad_day1_evening_9500777f	butler	The lady in the corner is Mrs Amelia Baxter.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	107	butler "[what]"
lad_day1_evening_86c98c02	lad	I don't see our host in the room.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	112	lad "[what]"
lad_day1_evening_5dd83bae	butler	Lady Claythorn is still busy at the moment.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	116	butler "[what]"
lad_day1_evening_8c058084	butler	You'll meet her at dinner.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	116	butler "[what]"
lad_day1_evening_ce243226		After this introduction, he leaves me and goes to stand in the corner of the room.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	122	"[what]"
lad_day1_evening_a34a9fa5		Most of the guests are already engaged in conversation.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	122	"[what]"
lad_day1_evening_16e13f9b		However, Amelia Baxter and Samuel Manning are alone.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	122	"[what]"
lad_day1_evening_6eab3870		They seem more approachable than the rest.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	122	"[what]"
lad_day1_evening_77eb372d		What is that? A gong?	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	150	"[what]"
lad_day1_evening_6afc3c60	butler	Dinner is served. Please, follow me to the dining room.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	154	butler "[what]"
lad_day1_evening_85e5ca08		Everyone takes a seat at the spot labelled with their names.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	168	"[what]"
lad_day1_evening_be953ab1		As I observe each person, Lady Claythorn makes her entrance into the room.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	168	"[what]"
lad_day1_evening_389de44e		She looks younger than I had imagined.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	168	"[what]"
lad_day1_evening_2aaf76b2		I don't know why, but I pictured an elderly, bored lady. Yet she looks nothing like that.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	168	"[what]"
lad_day1_evening_5262775e		Her clothes, which are the most impressive of anyone's in the room, make her status clear.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	168	"[what]"
lad_day1_evening_2c3f7049		She proceeds to take her seat at the table.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	168	"[what]"
lad_day1_evening_52fab469		After her speech, everyone appears pleased.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	186	"[what]"
lad_day1_evening_87aa7235		A few of the guests begin to express their appreciation to the host.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	186	"[what]"
lad_day1_evening_eee3e8d6	host	Please, there's no need to thank me.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	192	host "[what]"
lad_day1_evening_6605e31f	host	The food will be served shortly.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	192	host "[what]"
lad_day1_evening_5addb080	host	Enjoy your meal.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	192	host "[what]"
lad_day1_evening_78c3f2b5		At that moment, the butler enters the room, accompanied by the footman.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	200	"[what]"
lad_day1_evening_6aba31a4		They begin to serve the first dish and pour drinks for everyone.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	200	"[what]"
lad_day1_evening_b9320286		The mood in the room gradually relaxes, and the sound of various conversations fills the space.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	200	"[what]"
lad_day1_evening_e1d85416		I turn my attention to the guests seated next to me.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	200	"[what]"
lad_day1_evening_58717700		I find myself sitting between Amelia Baxter and Daniel Baldwin.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	200	"[what]"
lad_day1_evening_c77b35aa		The dinner comes to an end.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	227	"[what]"
lad_day1_evening_3b10d2f0		The host explains that we can continue our discussion and enjoy drinks in the billiard room, or, for those tired from the journey, we can simply retire for the night.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	227	"[what]"
lad_day1_evening_8d663315		Since I haven't seen my room yet, I should probably head there first.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	227	"[what]"
lad_day1_evening_bfceec02		I ask the footman to show me the way.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	227	"[what]"
lad_day1_evening_a02a60f5		The footman escorts me up the grand staircase, leading me to the first floor.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	241	"[what]"
lad_day1_evening_b251f5e7	footman	Here you are, sir.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	245	footman "[what]"
lad_day1_evening_52798528	footman	You've been assigned the 'William the Conqueror' room.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	245	footman "[what]"
lad_day1_evening_9c874b99		I step into the bedroom.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	255	"[what]"
lad_day1_evening_30915c26		It is more spacious than my flat, and more luxurious than I could have imagined.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	255	"[what]"
lad_day1_evening_1a231ce1	footman	I hope the room suits your taste.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	261	footman "[what]"
lad_day1_evening_a58f4ddc	lad	This is... this is good, yes. Thank you.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	265	lad "[what]"
lad_day1_evening_6f2033a8		The footman exits the room.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	269	"[what]"
lad_day1_evening_389f4b1b		I look around in disbelief.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	269	"[what]"
lad_day1_evening_fdee7ca1		After a while, I unpack my modest luggage.	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	269	"[what]"
lad_day1_evening_9647743f		It does not take long. So, what should I do now?	game/scripts/lad/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	269	"[what]"
