nurse_downstairs_approach_ffbe024c		Years of moving discretely in hospitals and large houses have taught me how to remain unseen.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	506	"[what]"
nurse_downstairs_approach_85eff5c1		I reach the kitchen door and ease it open an inch.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	506	"[what]"
nurse_library_default_21fd6917		There is nothing more for me to find here.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	525	"[what]"
nurse_library_default_2608e112		I already know what I need to know about Zanzibar.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	525	"[what]"
nurse_library_default_cb5e0c68		The library remains as it was.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	535	"[what]"
nurse_library_default_b510d7d4		The volumes of "A History of the British Army" are still on the shelf.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	535	"[what]"
nurse_library_default_bd7cb5d7		A well-appointed library.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	547	"[what]"
nurse_library_default_fb8a4761		"A Genealogical and Heraldic Dictionary of the Landed Gentry of Great Britain" lies open on a table.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	547	"[what]"
nurse_library_default_8965bcf6		I cast my eye along the shelves.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	547	"[what]"
nurse_library_default_9917a61a		Mostly heraldry, county histories, and bound journals.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	547	"[what]"
nurse_library_default_9322ab9b		Nothing worth taking — far too heavy, and of no particular value.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	547	"[what]"
nurse_library_default_029b1256		I am about to leave when a title catches my attention.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	547	"[what]"
nurse_library_default_1cf6d1a1		"A History of the British Army" — Fortescue.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	547	"[what]"
nurse_library_default_e39226fa		Fourteen volumes.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	547	"[what]"
nurse_library_default_c9039bda		I have seen this set before, in the officers' mess at Netley.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	547	"[what]"
nurse_library_default_44d8c9b4		The Captain mentioned Zanzibar at some point, I remember.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	547	"[what]"
nurse_library_default_92028a68		Something in the way he spoke of it nagged at me, though I could not quite place it at the time.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	547	"[what]"
nurse_library_default_ac14c859		I could try to learn more about that conflict, though it may take some time.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	547	"[what]"
nurse_library_war_book_ead2b815		I take down the volume covering the latter campaigns in India and East Africa.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	584	"[what]"
nurse_library_war_book_25e3c219		I find the index and look up Zanzibar.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	584	"[what]"
nurse_library_war_book_635b19de		A single page.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	584	"[what]"
nurse_library_war_book_e7a18e4d		The engagement lasted thirty-eight minutes.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	584	"[what]"
nurse_library_war_book_40c922e1		The shortest war in recorded history, apparently.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	584	"[what]"
nurse_library_war_book_65815b92		The British bombardment was overwhelming.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	584	"[what]"
nurse_library_war_book_4dc15a29		Casualties on the British side were minimal — one man, lightly wounded.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	584	"[what]"
nurse_library_war_book_64d5b93c		If what the Captain said is true, he would be the only injured soldier from the entire war.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	584	"[what]"
nurse_library_war_book_ffb1276e		That seems most unlikely.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	584	"[what]"
nurse_library_war_book_f8943884		He may well have invented the whole story — but to what end?	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	584	"[what]"
nurse_portrait_gallery_default_1f47acb7		The portraits remain as they were, their silent judgement unchanged.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	617	"[what]"
nurse_portrait_gallery_default_78c0b9de		There is nothing here for me.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	617	"[what]"
nurse_portrait_gallery_default_b38a5246		The gallery is lit by a single gas lamp.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	629	"[what]"
nurse_portrait_gallery_default_9a59d904		The Claythorn ancestors gaze down from their frames with an air of collective disapproval.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	629	"[what]"
nurse_portrait_gallery_default_e9846c64		I feel rather as though I am being assessed.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	629	"[what]"
nurse_portrait_gallery_default_ec709533		I do not linger.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	629	"[what]"
nurse_attic_approach_4cb70cdc		The attic staircase creaks with every step.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	652	"[what]"
nurse_attic_approach_54d85a30		Up here, the air is close and smells of dust and old timber.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	652	"[what]"
nurse_attic_approach_d226890c		The corridor runs the length of the house, doors on either side.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	652	"[what]"
nurse_attic_approach_e530a6c1		With the servants all occupied below, there is no one to question what I am doing up here.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	652	"[what]"
nurse_attic_females_room_ac292ef0		It looks exactly the same as before.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	675	"[what]"
nurse_attic_females_room_69e30bff		No need to search any further.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	675	"[what]"
nurse_attic_females_room_fc472e3d		It is a small, spare space — two narrow beds, a washstand, a single trunk between them.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	687	"[what]"
nurse_attic_females_room_30c8b607		On the shelf above one of the beds, a small collection of things: a dog-eared playbill from a London theatre, another from a touring company.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	687	"[what]"
nurse_attic_females_room_fdfefbf5		A faded photograph is tucked behind them.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	687	"[what]"
nurse_attic_females_room_230a1aec		I take the photograph down.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	687	"[what]"
nurse_attic_females_room_03312fb8		A young woman in stage dress, posed with a man I do not recognise.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	687	"[what]"
nurse_attic_females_room_fe99eeb6		She is smiling broadly. I recognise the young maid working here.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	687	"[what]"
nurse_attic_females_room_681d1381		So she is, or was, an aspiring actress.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	687	"[what]"
nurse_attic_females_room_80994a57		How peculiar for her to end up here.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	687	"[what]"
nurse_attic_females_room_02f8bbc0		I wonder what her story is.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	687	"[what]"
nurse_attic_females_room_8f4d2038		I replace everything as it was and step back out.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	687	"[what]"
nurse_attic_butler_room_13eaf381		The cabinet stands open, emptied of anything worth taking.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	728	"[what]"
nurse_attic_butler_room_7da5e42c		There is nothing more for me here.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	728	"[what]"
nurse_attic_butler_room_c78112ba		The reinforced cabinet still stands against the far wall.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	738	"[what]"
nurse_attic_butler_room_8e9a0b3f		But this time, I have the master key.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	738	"[what]"
nurse_attic_butler_room_c78112ba_1		The reinforced cabinet still stands against the far wall.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	748	"[what]"
nurse_attic_butler_room_d7c432ba		Without the butler's key, there is nothing I can do here.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	748	"[what]"
nurse_attic_butler_room_250c4b59		The room itself is surprisingly ordinary.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	756	"[what]"
nurse_attic_butler_room_523c0291		However, standing against the far wall is a large, reinforced cabinet.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	756	"[what]"
nurse_butler_cabinet_lockpick_0e9462ab		I approach the cabinet and attempt to pick the lock.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	790	"[what]"
nurse_butler_cabinet_lockpick_392a6de0		But this is no ordinary lock.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	790	"[what]"
nurse_butler_cabinet_lockpick_2baa947a		The mechanism inside is far more intricate than those I am used to.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	790	"[what]"
nurse_butler_cabinet_lockpick_6a729e24		After a few moments of fruitless effort, I am forced to admit defeat.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	790	"[what]"
nurse_butler_cabinet_lockpick_dd7a1e45		I shall not be able to open this by force or skill alone.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	790	"[what]"
nurse_butler_cabinet_lockpick_43c5ab36		I will need the butler's key.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	790	"[what]"
nurse_butler_cabinet_open_with_master_key_32f294d1		I approach the cabinet.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	809	"[what]"
nurse_butler_cabinet_open_with_master_key_e68e6bdd		But before I waste time with my lockpicks, I remember the master key.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	809	"[what]"
nurse_butler_cabinet_open_with_master_key_1e11a491		I take it from my pocket and fit it into the lock.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	809	"[what]"
nurse_butler_cabinet_open_with_master_key_cf9b328c		It turns with a satisfying click.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	809	"[what]"
nurse_butler_cabinet_open_with_master_key_427a7adb		The cabinet doors swing open.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	809	"[what]"
nurse_butler_cabinet_open_with_master_key_99810ab9		No bearer bonds.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	809	"[what]"
nurse_butler_cabinet_open_with_master_key_52500024		Disappointing, but I was expecting it.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	809	"[what]"
nurse_butler_cabinet_open_with_master_key_d6739c64		Luckily, the cabinet is not empty.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	809	"[what]"
nurse_butler_cabinet_open_with_master_key_f36d8f7c		A pair of candlesticks, a salver, a set of heavy serving spoons — all solid, all worth a good deal more than sentiment.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	809	"[what]"
nurse_butler_cabinet_open_with_master_key_8000bef7		I take what I can fit in my bag.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	809	"[what]"
nurse_butler_cabinet_open_with_master_key_b1ff99db		Then I close the cabinet and step back.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	809	"[what]"
nurse_butler_cabinet_open_with_master_key_5c0de4b0		This changes everything.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	809	"[what]"
nurse_butler_cabinet_open_with_master_key_df19543c		This might actually be enough.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	809	"[what]"
nurse_butler_cabinet_open_with_master_key_faea08ea		Enough to matter.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	809	"[what]"
nurse_attic_males_room_ac292ef0		It looks exactly the same as before.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	852	"[what]"
nurse_attic_males_room_69e30bff		No need to search any further.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	852	"[what]"
nurse_attic_males_room_b75c226b		Two beds, a chest of drawers, a peg for each man's jacket.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	864	"[what]"
nurse_attic_males_room_f2768c38		I check the drawers quickly — folded shirts, a penknife, a few coins.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	864	"[what]"
nurse_attic_males_room_cb69bfb5		No valuables here.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	864	"[what]"
nurse_attic_males_room_eff34edd		Tucked at the very back of the bottom drawer, beneath folded shirts, I find a letter.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	864	"[what]"
nurse_attic_males_room_54fde9e8		It is from a theatre company in London — a rejection, politely worded but unmistakable.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	864	"[what]"
nurse_attic_males_room_b465aa22		"We regret to inform you that the role has been filled. We wish you every success in your future endeavours."	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	864	"[what]"
nurse_attic_males_room_0e2a4fac		An actor. Playing at being a servant.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	864	"[what]"
nurse_attic_males_room_112e1958		But why would he stay so far from a theatre?	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	864	"[what]"
nurse_attic_males_room_18cd1ff0		That is rather suspicious.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	864	"[what]"
nurse_attic_males_room_30b6d85e		I fold the letter and replace it exactly as I found it.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	864	"[what]"
nurse_two_actors_realisation_e66da2a9		Two actors in the same household, so far from any major city.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	898	"[what]"
nurse_two_actors_realisation_b57faef8		That cannot be a coincidence.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	898	"[what]"
nurse_attic_storage_21fd6917		There is nothing more for me to find here.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	917	"[what]"
nurse_attic_storage_e645a4a2		I have already gone through the important items.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	917	"[what]"
nurse_attic_storage_0042c41e		The storage room remains a jumble of trunks and boxes.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	925	"[what]"
nurse_attic_storage_375d4d39		I still have not searched it thoroughly.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	925	"[what]"
nurse_attic_storage_a907e29f		The storage room is vast.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	937	"[what]"
nurse_attic_storage_69f9aa6e		Trunks stacked three deep, old furniture draped in dust sheets, boxes of every shape and size.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	937	"[what]"
nurse_attic_storage_77ef1ab4		I barely know where to begin.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	937	"[what]"
nurse_attic_storage_search_all_e6bc7167		The trunks are packed tightly and most of them are locked.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	962	"[what]"
nurse_attic_storage_search_all_e0b589f1		I manage to open one — old curtains, heavy and mildewed.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	962	"[what]"
nurse_attic_storage_search_all_32adc9c4		Another: crockery wrapped in cloth.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	962	"[what]"
nurse_attic_storage_search_all_0b36ae6b		I lift a dust sheet from what turns out to be an old escritoire.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	962	"[what]"
nurse_attic_storage_search_all_58c925cb		The drawers are empty save for a few dried-up pen nibs and a folded invoice from eighteen ninety.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	962	"[what]"
nurse_attic_storage_search_all_c73974cd		The shelves near the door hold rows of old tins and jars, most unlabelled.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	962	"[what]"
nurse_attic_storage_search_all_f9a80517		I move some aside — and then I stop.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	962	"[what]"
nurse_attic_storage_search_all_6e7703b5		Behind a row of old paint tins, stacked neatly and deliberately out of sight:	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	962	"[what]"
nurse_attic_storage_search_all_2ebe283f		Bullets.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	962	"[what]"
nurse_attic_storage_search_all_d1b5fc2c		A good number of them.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	962	"[what]"
nurse_attic_storage_search_all_aa469341		Someone has gone to some trouble to hide these.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	962	"[what]"
nurse_attic_storage_search_all_741f308c		I take them out and carefully load the small revolver I took from the gun room.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	990	"[what]"
nurse_attic_storage_search_all_fd9e8245		It is good to be prepared.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	990	"[what]"
nurse_attic_storage_search_all_8c50bc67		I shall need a gun to use these, but I take them regardless.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	998	"[what]"
nurse_attic_storage_search_all_89352aaf		Then I replace the tins exactly as they were, and leave the room as quietly as I came.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	1002	"[what]"
nurse_attic_storage_give_up_3ca005e7		I have been in here long enough.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	1012	"[what]"
nurse_attic_storage_give_up_340a0202		There is too much to search properly, and I am beginning to feel uneasy.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	1012	"[what]"
nurse_attic_storage_give_up_c5cffa87		I leave without having found anything of note.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	1012	"[what]"
nurse_butler_room_first_visit_bbc30afc		The room itself is surprisingly ordinary — a head servant's quarters.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	1025	"[what]"
nurse_butler_room_first_visit_a3ee721b		A neat bed, a small washstand, and a plain wooden chair.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	1025	"[what]"
nurse_butler_room_first_visit_523c0291		However, standing against the far wall is a large, reinforced cabinet.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	1025	"[what]"
nurse_butler_room_first_visit_5e03b409		Through its glass panes, I can see the household silver and other valuables gleaming in the dim light.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	1025	"[what]"
nurse_butler_room_first_visit_0eb7202d		This must be where the true wealth of the house is kept.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_generic_locations.rpy	1025	"[what]"
nurse_generic_other_guests_saturday_morning_30704ffb	nurse	Oh, up until now, I've mostly kept to myself.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	3	nurse "[what]"
nurse_generic_other_guests_saturday_morning_8407cbab	nurse	I haven't talked to many people.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	3	nurse "[what]"
nurse_generic_other_guests_saturday_morning_b141f7f8	nurse	I am seated next to Samuel Manning, but we haven't had a very deep conversation yet.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	3	nurse "[what]"
nurse_generic_other_guests_saturday_morning_2f7aecd2	nurse	Our host is the only other person I've had any real exchange with.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	3	nurse "[what]"
nurse_generic_other_guests_saturday_morning_8284d917	nurse	But we stuck mostly to simple pleasantries.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	3	nurse "[what]"
nurse_generic_drunk_saturday_morning_e149f905	nurse	I usually don't like to spread gossip.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	22	nurse "[what]"
nurse_generic_drunk_saturday_morning_e9d4944c	nurse	But in this case, I don't think it's a big secret.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	22	nurse "[what]"
nurse_generic_drunk_saturday_morning_989bcef9	nurse	I believe Samuel Manning is an alcoholic.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	22	nurse "[what]"
nurse_generic_drunk_saturday_morning_b3cf5016	nurse	He was barely intelligible both at dinner yesterday and this morning.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	22	nurse "[what]"
nurse_generic_drunk_saturday_morning_2cbf3139	nurse	Those were two pretty unpleasant meals for me.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	22	nurse "[what]"
nurse_generic_drunk_saturday_morning_409c04e1		Well, that's nothing I didn't already know.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	36	"[what]"
nurse_generic_other_guests_saturday_evening_doctor_ed42fbda	nurse	Well, I must admit I have not tried to socialise much.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	48	nurse "[what]"
nurse_generic_other_guests_saturday_evening_doctor_b27b15cd	nurse	I have spoken a little with our host, though nothing of any real substance.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	48	nurse "[what]"
nurse_generic_other_guests_saturday_evening_doctor_c765303e	nurse	This afternoon I shared lunch with Amelia Baxter, quite an interesting character.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	48	nurse "[what]"
nurse_generic_other_guests_saturday_evening_doctor_a8d8c1b3	nurse	And of course there was our poor Mister Manning, ...	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	48	nurse "[what]"
nurse_generic_other_guests_saturday_evening_doctor_d76517f2		She realises to whom she is speaking and falls silent.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	58	"[what]"
nurse_generic_other_guests_saturday_evening_doctor_4d745126	doctor	Yes, a most tragic event. I still can scarcely believe what has happened.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	62	doctor "[what]"
nurse_generic_other_guests_saturday_evening_doctor_1e6615e8	nurse	I am terribly sorry, Doctor. I did not mean to upset you.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	66	nurse "[what]"
nurse_generic_other_guests_saturday_evening_doctor_3268e862	doctor	That is all right.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	70	doctor "[what]"
nurse_generic_psychic_saturday_evening_doctor_b2864fec	nurse	Miss Baxter is a very pleasant woman, quite easy to talk to.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	81	nurse "[what]"
nurse_generic_psychic_saturday_evening_doctor_17777a08	nurse	But she made me a little uneasy when she spoke of her "gift".	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	81	nurse "[what]"
nurse_generic_psychic_saturday_evening_doctor_a129ddd0	doctor	Gift? What do you mean?	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	87	doctor "[what]"
nurse_generic_psychic_saturday_evening_doctor_e50330ed	nurse	She is convinced that she can speak with the deceased, or with some other version of them that exists upon another plane.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	91	nurse "[what]"
nurse_generic_psychic_saturday_evening_doctor_ab5607a6	nurse	I must confess I did not follow every word. I do not care to speak of the dead, and I found it most unsettling.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	91	nurse "[what]"
nurse_generic_psychic_saturday_evening_doctor_89f14168	doctor	I can imagine. It is a delicate subject to raise with a stranger.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	97	doctor "[what]"
nurse_generic_psychic_saturday_evening_doctor_13944985	doctor	Did she seem well otherwise?	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	97	doctor "[what]"
nurse_generic_psychic_saturday_evening_doctor_ee3a7a9e	nurse	She did.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	103	nurse "[what]"
nurse_generic_psychic_saturday_evening_doctor_a7b72f51	nurse	You might be thinking as I did at first. That she might be ill.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	103	nurse "[what]"
nurse_generic_psychic_saturday_evening_doctor_155060ce	nurse	I have seen this sort of thing in certain patients, particularly those approaching the end of their lives.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	103	nurse "[what]"
nurse_generic_psychic_saturday_evening_doctor_8fafb300	nurse	But the rest of her behaviour was perfectly normal, and that was what troubled me most.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	103	nurse "[what]"
nurse_generic_psychic_saturday_evening_doctor_33085062	doctor	I see. It is not unheard of for someone to hold a fixed idea upon a single matter, yet remain entirely sound in all others.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	113	doctor "[what]"
nurse_generic_psychic_saturday_evening_doctor_abe9feab	doctor	In my experience such notions may arise from strain or some powerful emotional shock, even when the mind is otherwise quite stable.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	113	doctor "[what]"
nurse_generic_psychic_saturday_evening_doctor_137e51cd	doctor	So she could be perfectly well in every other respect.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	113	doctor "[what]"
nurse_generic_psychic_saturday_evening_doctor_2b1fc424	doctor	Of course, we cannot disregard the possibility of a more serious condition.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	113	doctor "[what]"
nurse_generic_psychic_saturday_evening_doctor_8dcb4643	doctor	In rare cases a fixed belief of that nature may be an early sign of dementia praecox, or what some of my colleagues have begun to call schizophrenia.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	113	doctor "[what]"
nurse_generic_psychic_saturday_evening_doctor_697de4fb	doctor	But I would not draw conclusions too hastily. It is far more likely that Miss Baxter is of sound mind, eccentricities notwithstanding.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	113	doctor "[what]"
nurse_generic_psychic_saturday_evening_doctor_6ef3dd2f	nurse	Thank you. That is a relief.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	127	nurse "[what]"
nurse_generic_host_saturday_82cf6465	nurse	I only share a few words with the Lady of the house.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	138	nurse "[what]"
nurse_generic_host_saturday_bdc1d868	nurse	I tried to know more about the details of the Manor, the staff, that sort of things.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	138	nurse "[what]"
nurse_generic_host_saturday_3d0ae17d	nurse	She was quite polite, but her responses were short and not very informative.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	138	nurse "[what]"
nurse_generic_host_saturday_8cd9c398	nurse	I hope I wasn't rude to her.	game/scripts/nurse/nurse_other_guests.rpy	138	nurse "[what]"
psychic_introduction_bbeeda27		This invitation really isn't well written.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	25	"[what]"
psychic_introduction_17ec1418		Vague instructions on how to reach the manor.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	25	"[what]"
psychic_introduction_f4ef8b78		There's little information about who has been invited.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	25	"[what]"
psychic_introduction_c648509c		I suppose it wouldn't be surprising if some of the participants did not show up.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	25	"[what]"
psychic_introduction_1f881e4e		I cannot help feeling nervous about the whole thing.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	25	"[what]"
psychic_introduction_8a83ec2b		Well, it's too late to turn back now.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	25	"[what]"
psychic_introduction_41c37e77		We shall see what happens.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	25	"[what]"
psychic_introduction_bd856402		I step off the train and look around me.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	47	"[what]"
psychic_introduction_835bba2c		On the platform, I spot a young man in a footman's livery.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	53	"[what]"
psychic_introduction_0de6939c		He is talking to a tanned man with a serious expression.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	53	"[what]"
psychic_introduction_b649cee4		I walk towards them.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	53	"[what]"
psychic_introduction_8c3860bc	psychic	Excuse me, gentlemen. I'm heading to Claythorn Manor and was wondering if you could assist me.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	61	psychic "[what]"
psychic_introduction_8ce17ce4	footman	Yes, of course. You must be Amelia Baxter.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	65	footman "[what]"
psychic_introduction_117ed534	psychic	That's correct.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	69	psychic "[what]"
psychic_introduction_6e5746f7	footman	Perfect. I work for Lady Claythorn and have been instructed to take you to the manor.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	73	footman "[what]"
psychic_introduction_105620c0	footman	The gentleman here is also coming with us.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	73	footman "[what]"
psychic_introduction_76007f58	captain	Nice to meet you, Miss Baxter.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	79	captain "[what]"
psychic_introduction_41e9afd7		He takes my hand and kisses it lightly.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	83	"[what]"
psychic_introduction_8913eb72		At least here's someone with manners.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	83	"[what]"
psychic_introduction_7af67313	psychic	How do you do, Mr ...	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	89	psychic "[what]"
psychic_introduction_6826a9af	captain	Sinha, Sushil Sinha.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	93	captain "[what]"
psychic_introduction_b87b6ce5	psychic	Ah.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	97	psychic "[what]"
psychic_introduction_1251ada6	psychic	Nice to meet you too, Mr Sinha.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	97	psychic "[what]"
psychic_introduction_9af0b179	footman	I believe there's still someone on this train who is supposed to accompany us.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	103	footman "[what]"
psychic_introduction_96cd6f9e	footman	A Mr Manning.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	103	footman "[what]"
psychic_introduction_abdc8bac	footman	Have either of you met him by any chance?	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	103	footman "[what]"
psychic_introduction_0405d5e2	captain	I don't think so.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	111	captain "[what]"
psychic_introduction_862b8212	psychic	Me neither.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	115	psychic "[what]"
psychic_introduction_d147d74f	footman	Alright, maybe he missed it.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	119	footman "[what]"
psychic_introduction_ddb39774	footman	Let us wait a few minutes to be sure everyone has left this train, then we can move on.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	119	footman "[what]"
psychic_introduction_14332a9f		As the train prepares to leave the station, I see someone stumbling out of a door, almost falling.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	125	"[what]"
psychic_introduction_ab2af6c6		Since we're the only people left on the platform, he walks towards us, looking uncertain.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	125	"[what]"
psychic_introduction_788ce7cc	footman	Hello, sir. Are you going to Claythorn Manor?	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	131	footman "[what]"
psychic_introduction_b92e3b89	drunk	I am indeed.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	135	drunk "[what]"
psychic_introduction_9a7ad935	footman	Perfect, that should be everyone.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	139	footman "[what]"
psychic_introduction_eaa0d0b0	footman	You can follow me to the car, and we'll be on our way.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	139	footman "[what]"
psychic_introduction_d27907a8	footman	It will take about an hour to reach the manor.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	139	footman "[what]"
psychic_introduction_848781d7		I take a seat in the back.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	149	"[what]"
psychic_introduction_7d221ab2		Sushil Sinha joins me.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	149	"[what]"
psychic_introduction_c3a14e89	captain	I hope you don't mind my sitting with you.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	155	captain "[what]"
psychic_introduction_794579f2	captain	I think it's better to let Mr Manning sit in front.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	155	captain "[what]"
psychic_introduction_7798d935	psychic	Of course not.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	161	psychic "[what]"
psychic_introduction_86f4d724		I understand all too well what he means.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	165	"[what]"
psychic_introduction_aef229b6		Samuel Manning seems quite out of sorts.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	165	"[what]"
psychic_introduction_4b003b6d		He attempts to make small talk with the driver, but his speech is incoherent.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	165	"[what]"
psychic_introduction_1d8cd9d1		The poor fellow does his best to ignore him and focus on the road.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	165	"[what]"
psychic_introduction_d7d82835		When he realises no one wishes to talk to him, Samuel Manning takes a sip from a flask and immediately falls asleep in his seat.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	165	"[what]"
psychic_introduction_c835922e		The driver sighs with relief.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	165	"[what]"
psychic_introduction_40f3d00e	captain	Well, he's certainly had one too many.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	179	captain "[what]"
psychic_introduction_30e6000d	captain	I hope he can sleep it off.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	179	captain "[what]"
psychic_introduction_369684dd	captain	It would be embarrassing for our host to greet him in this state.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	179	captain "[what]"
psychic_introduction_354db0cb	psychic	You are certainly right.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	187	psychic "[what]"
psychic_introduction_a99e39cb	psychic	I would rather discuss something else, if you do not mind.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	187	psychic "[what]"
psychic_introduction_b146ab41	captain	Not at all.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	193	captain "[what]"
psychic_introduction_c2fdabc0		After what seems an eternity, the manor appears on the horizon.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	220	"[what]"
psychic_introduction_2ca47814		That finally puts an end to Captain Sinha's monologue.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	220	"[what]"
psychic_introduction_e226a226	captain	Ah, it looks like we're arriving at our destination.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	226	captain "[what]"
psychic_introduction_7b54e9d7	captain	What a magnificent home.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	226	captain "[what]"
psychic_introduction_f6747335		He's right, it is beautiful.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	232	"[what]"
psychic_introduction_7e5f3a49		However, the storm lends it a somewhat sinister aspect.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	232	"[what]"
psychic_introduction_a3df2d9a		Nevertheless, its appearance reassures me somewhat.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	232	"[what]"
psychic_introduction_cb87c2fd		Such a house suggests its owner must be incredibly wealthy.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	232	"[what]"
psychic_introduction_cf3127f1		Everything ought to be fine from now on.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	232	"[what]"
psychic_introduction_797be909		The three of us walk towards the entrance while the driver attends to our luggage.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	246	"[what]"
psychic_introduction_01d88ab3		Samuel Manning wakes up when the car stops. He looks somewhat better than before.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	246	"[what]"
psychic_introduction_e4c9b4fe		When we reach the main door, a butler greets us.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	246	"[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_garden_1b94f8d8		I reach the large hall and prepare to open the door.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	67	"[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_garden_87b1e534		But the weather is dreadful, so it would be madness to go out now.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	67	"[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_garden_e1a4e928		It makes more sense to do something else for the time being.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	67	"[what]"
psychic_bedroom_stay_away_048d4e61		I do not think it would be wise to simply enter someone's room like that.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	80	"[what]"
psychic_bedroom_stay_away_bc43b6dd		They might return at any moment.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	80	"[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_9ee0da30		On the other hand, I notice that the door to this room is not properly closed.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	102	"[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_bedroom_drunk_b4658dbf		I feel tempted to go in, yet I cannot. It would be too dangerous, for now.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	102	"[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_95b6d984		Astonishing. He looked passed out drunk in the car.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	31	"[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_45d3251f		How could he possibly want another drink now?	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	31	"[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_0d586cad	butler	What about you, Miss ...?	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	39	butler "[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_0bbfd4d9	psychic	Miss Baxter.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	43	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_0ee5107a	psychic	I believe I shall freshen up in my room first.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	43	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_bed849e2	psychic	It has been a very long journey.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	43	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_36f12990	butler	Of course, please follow me upstairs.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	51	butler "[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_f68694ab	butler	Here we are, Miss.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	57	butler "[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_421d6bd6	butler	The "Elizabeth I Bedroom."	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	57	butler "[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_d0141625	butler	I hope it's to your liking.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	57	butler "[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_443c8a5e		He opens my room and lets me in.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	69	"[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_cef254c1		At the same time, the driver arrives with my luggage.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	69	"[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_3edad9fc		He leaves them there and then excuses himself.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	69	"[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_7608ed7b	butler	Well, it looks like you're all set.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	77	butler "[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_35fe0feb	butler	Please join us in the dining room when you're ready.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	77	butler "[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_68b029dc		I nod and take a look at my room.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	83	"[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_32d73488		It is a bit worn, but it still looks decent.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	83	"[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_006d3677		I should be quite comfortable here.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	83	"[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_2f5f4868		When I am ready, I head downstairs to the tea room.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	93	"[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_836c703a	butler	Miss Baxter.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	101	butler "[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_fdc93cff	butler	Almost everyone is here now.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	101	butler "[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_755e1632		He quickly introduces me to those I have not yet met.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	107	"[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_6c38de48	butler	Please make yourself at home.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	111	butler "[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_cf92f09a	butler	Now, if you'll excuse me, I hear the car is back with the last guest.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	111	butler "[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_828a4c6e		He leaves me on my own.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	117	"[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_88e80c96		I glance about the room.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	117	"[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_82353b9a		Nearly everyone is gathered around Sushil Sinha.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	117	"[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_aa5b6d30		He is in the midst of what sounds like yet another tedious story.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	117	"[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_4ae6da06		I am not eager to listen to that again.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	117	"[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_69b37a29		On a chair, Samuel Manning sits alone with a glass in his hand.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	117	"[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_ecb1488d		I can't believe it.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	117	"[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_8e68b582		He fell asleep again.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	117	"[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_f1f6a402		Well, I suppose I have no choice but to join the larger group.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	117	"[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_09e62824		But before I can move, the butler returns.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	117	"[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_2ce34aae	butler	Mr Ted Harring!	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	139	butler "[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_f7f0f755		The butler nearly shouts the name of the new guest.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	143	"[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_d70d1d20		He is a good-looking young man, but he appears unsure.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	143	"[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_a6558964		It is clear he is not in his natural element here.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	143	"[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_5cef5cf4		I smile at him and, after some hesitation, he comes towards me.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	143	"[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_b7ad0f4e	butler	Dinner is served. Please follow me to the dining room.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	161	butler "[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_e18de909		I sit down at the place with my name on it.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	173	"[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_699f5e5b		Then, a lady enters the room.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	173	"[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_0a9f9296		She is wearing expensive clothing.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	173	"[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_c49327ff		Well said.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	183	"[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_a42da467		I join in the applause with the rest of the guests.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	183	"[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_978694fe	host	Please no need to thank me. The food will be served, enjoy your meal.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	189	host "[what]"
psychic_day1_evening_75af03cd		The food arrives right after the speech.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	193	"[what]"
