psychic_day2_evening_attic_default_b67059fc		And I couldn't force it open myself, obviously.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/0_map_choices.rpy	343	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_dd7a2e3a		I observe the hunting party as they make their way into the house.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	27	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_b953da2f		Lady Claythorn steps through the doorway first, her expression one of utter disbelief.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	27	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_871ce9e7		Following close behind are the butler and footman.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	27	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_333fcc05		They carefully carry someone on an improvised stretcher.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	27	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_04a67e3f		I watch Captain Sinha and Ted Harring carry Doctor Baldwin to his room.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	41	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_763fb67d		Now, the attention of everyone turns to Samuel Manning.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	41	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_ca96f8ca		I realise no one has thought about restraining him in any way.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	41	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_b0fd2852		But it seems unnecessary as he is sitting on the stairs,	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	41	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_1dbce1d7		his gaze empty, apparently unaware of what is happening about him.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	41	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_531b5946		We all watch the two men leave down the stairs.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	57	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_21037180		Then an awkward silence fills the room.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	57	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_992a0650		Before heading to my room, there is something I would like to understand.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	65	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_6557c1e7		I approach the butler.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	65	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_ec254783	butler	Yes, Miss Baxter?	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	71	butler "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_0bcdee64	psychic	I don't understand; how could you give a gun to someone so drunk?	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	75	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_536a7d0e	butler	I am so sorry, but he wasn't drunk when we talked this morning.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	79	butler "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_112b6d68	butler	He was acting totally normally.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	79	butler "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_3f166c9a	butler	He probably got drunk during the day.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	79	butler "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_f2a6f069	butler	There was nothing I could have done.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	79	butler "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_2647918a	psychic	Right.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	89	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_e9fc25e2		He did seem very drunk to me at breakfast, though.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	93	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_eca6b7a8		As I step into the dining room, a sombre ambience surrounds me.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	105	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_0274a797		The chairs where Daniel Baldwin and Thomas Moody usually sat are empty.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	105	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_a7b35b89		Samuel Manning is not here either, of course.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	105	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_0eca0c63		I settle into my familiar place, with Ted Harring to my right.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	105	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_6800cda4		Lady Claythorn stands up to speak.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	105	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_6f5e6c9b		As the food is served, Ted Harring turns to me.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	119	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_b40e286c		We eat in almost silence.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	127	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_7a0370c3		After dinner, most people retire to their rooms.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	127	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_b7c2a911		I do not think many will join for a drink afterwards.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	127	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_29f15ac2		So I could also take advantage of the fact that the Manor is almost empty.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	127	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_fa7392ab		Or I could wait in my room for Ted Harring.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	139	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_a6cba65a		Or perhaps it is safer to simply wait in my room.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	145	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_ec012af7		What should I do?	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	149	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_4f84a4d7		There's no need to wander the house further.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	161	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_bdfa36db		I should return to my room.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	161	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_3e694dbc		With nothing more to do, I quickly fall asleep.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	173	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_cancel_61473b1a		There's nothing more I can do right now.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/1_main.rpy	184	"[what]"
