psychic_day2_evening_bedroom_09dcf732		I return to my room to change and collect my thoughts.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	7	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_bedroom_72cb974b		So much has happened today, it is overwhelming.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	7	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_bedroom_ac64676b		I use this brief respite to compose myself.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	7	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_bedroom_b140737e		There is little time before dinner, so I could wait here,	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	7	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_bedroom_d65478f9		or take the opportunity to have a private word with someone.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	7	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_bedroom_9fe72c24		I do not think it would be wise to approach Captain Sinha,	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	7	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_bedroom_1b682c9b		nor Lady Claythorn.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	7	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_bedroom_8b524775		And I should let Rosalind Marsh rest.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	25	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_bedroom_295431c3		However, I do not believe I am taking too much of a risk by talking with Ted Harring.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	25	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_bedroom_bf19e34f		However, I do not believe I am taking too much of a risk by talking with Rosalind Marsh or Ted Harring.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	33	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_blood_fdb04795		I return to my room to rest.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	56	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_blood_f308544e		But very quickly, the gong rings.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	56	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_blood_055b3795		I guess I'd better join the others downstairs.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	66	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_cancel_nap_89a63e24		That's about all I can manage right now.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	130	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_cancel_nap_c3ebd8da		I should rest for a bit.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	130	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_cancel_nap_bbdae6d6		Right on time, the dinner gong rings.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	142	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_cancel_nap_91a3806f		I guess I should join the others downstairs.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	142	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_gone_4eb276c7		I knock gently on the door.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	157	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_gone_df40d4fa		but there is no answer.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	157	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_gone_0690a68b		She is probably resting.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	165	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_gone_1a7b45f7		After all, she said it herself. At night she takes her medicine then falls asleep.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	165	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_gone_78db00d3		But I don't know.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	165	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_gone_05847759		She looked in dreadful shape when I last spoke with her.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	165	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_gone_c9d20044		Perhaps her condition has worsened.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	165	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_gone_0b3d1fb3		Should I make certain she is all right?	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	165	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_gone_enter_f1a4e7d0		I know it's very impolite, but this is for her own good.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	193	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_gone_enter_fd097da7		I try to open the door.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	193	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_gone_enter_6ef7234b		It is unlocked.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	193	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_gone_enter_0750874a		But there is no one in here.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	203	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_gone_enter_51093f93		Where is Miss Marsh?	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	203	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_gone_enter_52330a85		She seemed so sick earlier.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	203	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_gone_enter_24d338c4		I look around the room.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	203	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_gone_enter_03aed663		It is tidy, clean and well-organized.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	203	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_gone_enter_f8310dd9		At first I don't notice anything out of the ordinary, but as I pry deeper I see something weird next to her bedstand.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	203	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_gone_enter_4ff8cdfc		Is that silverware?	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	203	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_gone_enter_72b0bcb0		What is it doing here?	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	203	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_gone_enter_f34fc1c8		Perhaps she was planning to eat in her room and changed her mind at the last minute.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	203	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_gone_enter_483cd7e0		But there is more then one set.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	203	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_gone_enter_04774633		Unless she wanted to entertain a few guests, there is no reason for her to have that many utensils in her room.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	203	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_gone_enter_31b8f7c4		I am not sure what to make of that.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	203	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_gone_do_not_enter_b7d7f756		She is probably just asleep.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	236	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_bedroom_nurse_gone_do_not_enter_1315de0c		There is no reason to wake her up.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2a_bedroom.rpy	236	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_billiard_room_39f05180		Just as I expected, the place is almost empty.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	9	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_billiard_room_347b3805		Besides the butler, I can see only one other person in the room:	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	9	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_billiard_room_1339fbda		Captain Sinha.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	9	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_billiard_room_acddd7a0		Good heavens.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	9	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_billiard_room_2158f8e5		He has spotted me.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	9	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_billiard_room_d2723eac		Now, I cannot avoid talking to him without appearing impolite.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	9	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_billiard_room_8d95dd73		At least the bar is still there.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	9	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_billiard_room_619510f0		I am back in the billiard room.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	38	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_billiard_room_bar_8f8854fc		I'll have a glass of sherry, as it's the only decent drink I can see.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	48	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_billiard_room_bar_107d34cc		Captain Sinha has looked up from his book and is now staring at me.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	54	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_billiard_room_bar_c622da08		I can't very well ignore him now.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	54	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_3961dfcc		I suppose I have no choice but to speak with him, at least for a little while.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	69	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_5376f4c4		Approaching him, I notice his expression is quite grave.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	69	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_7fb0eaaf		He looks at me with a piercing gaze, as if to assess whether I am a threat.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	69	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_eecfb08d		I sit down beside him, acutely aware of the tension between us.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	69	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_131a147b	captain	Miss Baxter.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	79	captain "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_46b9b785	captain	I wouldn't have thought you'd come here.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	79	captain "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_af2ec38c	psychic	I wasn't sure I would to be honest.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	85	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_658965fe	psychic	The atmosphere of this house has become quite sinister.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	85	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_c6ff3b42	psychic	But the idea of waiting alone in my room is not very reassuring either, so here I am.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	85	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_fe53f387	captain	Yes, sorry that there isn't a larger company here.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	93	captain "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_c556abeb	captain	Everyone else seems to have been too scared to come.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	93	captain "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_84099426	psychic	Oh that's quite alright.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	99	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_027caf34	psychic	But I am afraid I shall not be staying long in any case.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	99	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_billiard_room_captain_69522ff2	captain	Miss Baxter, is there anything else?	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	107	captain "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_nurse_captain_47d40b1f	captain	What do you mean, something weird?	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	118	captain "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_nurse_captain_b37969cd	psychic	Well, I am not certain I should tell you, but Miss Marsh is very ill.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	122	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_nurse_captain_d522ebb8	captain	Yes, now that you mention it, I noticed she has spent a good deal of time in her room.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	126	captain "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_nurse_captain_d9747502	captain	I simply assumed she was shy.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	126	captain "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_nurse_captain_25925d2f	psychic	Yes, but that is the point.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	132	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_nurse_captain_a0333d00	psychic	She should be in her room, and she is not.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	132	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_nurse_captain_7ce1e3fa	psychic	I went in to check, and it was empty.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	132	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_nurse_captain_a334f399	captain	Really? Do you often wander into other people's rooms when they are absent?	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	140	captain "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_nurse_captain_fb6b2d1f	psychic	Don't be absurd, of course not.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	144	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_nurse_captain_fc79351d	psychic	It was entirely for medical reasons. I feared for her well-being, you see.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	144	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_nurse_captain_649f4666	captain	If you say so.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	150	captain "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_nurse_captain_643be3da	captain	Still, she could be anywhere. It is not as though she were confined.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	150	captain "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_nurse_captain_b9a718ec	psychic	Quite, but there was something else.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	156	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_nurse_captain_3f070002	psychic	In her room I found a quantity of silverware — the very same we used at dinner.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	156	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_nurse_captain_ce8e01c3	psychic	And far too much to suppose it was simply for her own use.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	156	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_nurse_captain_91e1b66a	captain	What are you implying? That she stole it?	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	164	captain "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_nurse_captain_f3174664	psychic	I do not know, perhaps.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	168	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_nurse_captain_7fb47e55	psychic	Do you not think it rather odd?	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	168	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_nurse_captain_c2975f05	captain	I must concede, it is.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	174	captain "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_nurse_captain_05fa9eed	captain	I have read in the papers about people driven to take what is not theirs.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	174	captain "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_nurse_captain_c5124561	captain	An illness, apparently — kleptomania, they call it.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	174	captain "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_nurse_captain_aefd51b0	captain	I suppose it is possible Miss Marsh is afflicted with it. For it would be folly indeed to risk the reward money by provoking our host.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	174	captain "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_nurse_captain_0579618a	captain	But who can say, without speaking to her first?	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	174	captain "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_nurse_captain_79cc84c2	psychic	Of course, yet I have no idea where she has gone.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	186	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_nurse_captain_7e305706	psychic	She could be anywhere.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	186	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_nurse_captain_a2073d42	captain	True. But if she is prowling about in search of something to steal, there are only so many places she might try.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	192	captain "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_nurse_captain_e93d8afc	psychic	Really? Such as where?	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	196	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_nurse_captain_2a501681	captain	As you know, the silver is most likely kept in the butler's pantry.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	200	captain "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_nurse_captain_36ad53ad	captain	That may be in his own quarters, or perhaps downstairs, in the kitchen or scullery.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	200	captain "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_nurse_captain_8eb46035	psychic	I am not permitted below stairs. Perhaps I should try the butler's room.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	206	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_nurse_captain_a48b3174	captain	You might — but it could be dangerous. I ought to come with you.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	210	captain "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_nurse_captain_cancel_a09e2cf3		It is a tempting offer, yet I do not feel at ease being alone with him in the attic.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	224	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_nurse_captain_cancel_73fa9e1e	psychic	Thank you, but I do not believe it is necessary.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	228	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_nurse_captain_cancel_b4ce01b9	psychic	I must have the wrong idea.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	228	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_nurse_captain_cancel_48136507	psychic	I am sure Miss Marsh has only gone for a walk to help her sleep.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	228	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_nurse_captain_cancel_023f207a	psychic	Nothing more.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	228	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_nurse_captain_cancel_c3be6c71	captain	You are probably right.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	238	captain "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_a951ff80	psychic	Yes, I would like for you to come check with me.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	247	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_96f02cfd	psychic	Would you mind?	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	247	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_33ea940b	captain	Not at all, I don't have much else to do anyway.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	253	captain "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_b1f7e7a3	captain	But I really don't think we will find her there.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	253	captain "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_2b1c8419		We don't waste any time and go straight to the attic.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	261	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_f03667e3	psychic	Here we are. How shall we get in?	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	265	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_9bb847c1	psychic	The door is likely locked.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	265	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_1f97bfc8	captain	No matter. The butler gave me a master key earlier, when I had to secure Samuel Manning.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	271	captain "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_b0935329	captain	I still have it.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	271	captain "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_79b1baee	psychic	How convenient.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	277	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_362e8ed3		A master key? Then he can open nearly every door in the house.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	281	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_72b8343e		And yet the butler entrusted it to the captain without hesitation?	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	281	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_0c1d090a		That is not very sensible.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	281	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_ef0e66f7		Captain's sinha unlocks the door and we both step in.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	291	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_56b89852		As we suspected, Rosalind Marsh is there — holding a silver candelabra.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	297	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_02053d91	nurse	God.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	301	nurse "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_005c3e20	nurse	What are you doing here?	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	301	nurse "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_406f2195	captain	We might put the same question to you.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	307	captain "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_fda3962f	captain	Though I daresay the answer is plain enough.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	307	captain "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_88050db9		The captain points to the candlestick in her hand.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	313	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_f19b1904	nurse	This? I only wished for more light in my room.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	317	nurse "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_ef3b150d	nurse	The butler kindly gave me the key so I could take it.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	317	nurse "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_3145b024	captain	Did he indeed?	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	323	captain "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_79ea8e71	captain	Strange, for I already hold the only spare key in his possession.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	323	captain "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_bbf8642c	captain	Also, why would you lock the door behind you if you have nothing to hide?	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	323	captain "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_b3085a3f	nurse	Did I? It must have be by habit and—	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	331	nurse "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_d4b737d9		Something tumbles from her pocket and smashes on the floor.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	337	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_470d6c13		A champagne glass.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	337	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_8935b5ee	captain	Ah, and you needed a crystal glass as well?	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	343	captain "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_e8c5c692	captain	Planning a little party?	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	343	captain "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_31c75c3a	nurse	I was… I was…	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	349	nurse "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_961e401e	psychic	We know very well what you were about, Miss Marsh.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	353	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_45450877	psychic	I have seen the cutlery in your room.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	353	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_39f21077	psychic	Are even really sick or was it just for show?	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	353	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_a57e8782		Her face alters.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	363	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_fab60881		The flustered look vanishes, replaced by a cold resignation.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	363	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_cb292d2e		She sets the candelabra down.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	363	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_894bcfde	nurse	I see.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	371	nurse "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_fdec4697	nurse	There is no point in pretence any longer.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	371	nurse "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_a02b259d	nurse	You are right. I was helping myself to whatever I could find.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	371	nurse "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_5cca8465	nurse	Trinkets, keepsakes, silver, jewels — I have taken them all before.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	371	nurse "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_fc40307a	nurse	From houses, hospitals, from the old and feeble who never noticed until it was too late.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	371	nurse "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_e943b4c8	nurse	And now from here.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	371	nurse "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_0ff0379b	nurse	It is simply what I do.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	371	nurse "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_adab6c8b	nurse	Surprisingly, it's the first time I've been found out.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	371	nurse "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_0a0ecd79	nurse	And sadly yes, I am really sick, but not quite as severely as I let you believed.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	371	nurse "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_8550c372	nurse	It just provides a great cover for my little excursions.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	371	nurse "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_2b1a8888	nurse	And now you have put me in a very difficult position.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	395	nurse "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_8699c52b		Her voice is strained, almost pleading.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	399	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_ad9a59c4		But the captain is not moved.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	399	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_b206032c		His jaw tightens and he reaches into his coat.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	399	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_2edc3880	captain	I think not. You will come with us downstairs, and we shall settle this properly.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	407	captain "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_1faf6a59		He draws a revolver and levels it at her.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	411	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_40de1337		He acts with confidence, but I can see his hand shaking.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	411	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_9858619e		Miss Marsh recoils, but does not move towards the door.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	411	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_f46bcf91	nurse	You wouldn't dare.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	419	nurse "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_9cb14eff	captain	I said move.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	423	captain "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_707d367f		The captain fires into the ceiling.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	429	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_7d38b132		Plaster rains down upon us.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	429	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_d0c32ff6		Miss Marsh screams — and in the same breath, her hand darts into her pocket.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	429	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_8f0523dc		She has a gun of her own.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	429	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_5c920fb7		The shot catches the captain square in the chest.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	441	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_254a2c0e		He staggers back, a look of utter disbelief upon his face, and crumples to the floor.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	441	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_a534d664		She stands over him, breathing hard, her hands trembling.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	449	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_7cd62f7c		For a moment she looks as though she might be sick.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	449	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_b3a710f3		Then she turns to me, the revolver still in her grip.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	449	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_76a87743	nurse	He fired at me. You saw it. He fired at me.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	457	nurse "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_4af8d645	psychic	I did. But you needn't make things worse. Put the gun down. We can explain what happened.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	461	psychic surprised "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_6a282802		For a fleeting instant, I believe she might listen.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	465	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_c8a4c09b		But then her expression hardens.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	465	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_8ce34a81	nurse	You went through my room. You told the captain. You led him up here.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	471	nurse "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_70f1e5ce	nurse	None of this would have happened if you had simply left well enough alone.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	471	nurse "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_d600b8d8	nurse	But you couldn't, could you? You had to play the clairvoyant.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	471	nurse "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_1f9ebecf	nurse	Now you will tell them everything, I assume.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	471	nurse "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_b9a877d3	nurse	About the silver, the stealing — all of it.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	471	nurse "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_0b91d456	nurse	You will claim that you "saw" it.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	471	nurse "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_02b53d45	nurse	That will give you another "proof" of your power.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	471	nurse "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_8ec9b00e	nurse	Another reason to take advantage of vulnerable people.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	471	nurse "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_c8148a0c	psychic	That is not true. I would not -	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	489	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_750ed4dd	nurse	Well it doesn't matter now.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	493	nurse "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_cad18c0f	nurse	I can't really take the chance.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	493	nurse "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_ce40a39a		Her hand steadies on the gun.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	499	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_fe643908		There is no madness in her eyes — only a dreadful, weary resolve.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	499	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_a1f023ea		The look of someone who has already made her choice and cannot turn back.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	499	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_dfda52b6	nurse	I am sorry, Miss Baxter. Truly I am.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	507	nurse "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_e092c884	nurse	But I cannot go to prison. Not for this.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	507	nurse "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_e8ad2aff		The shot strikes my shoulder and I fall.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	515	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_a8429684		I am grievously wounded — but alive.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	521	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_2efcd8f9		Rosalind Marsh stands over me. Her face is pale, drawn tight with fear.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	521	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_69eef932		She raises the gun once more.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	521	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_1e19552c		A dull click. Empty.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	531	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_74305b08		She lets out a shuddering breath.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	531	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_7bd1d8fd		For a long moment she simply stands there, the useless weapon hanging at her side.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	537	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_3c9cfb47		Then, without a word, she sets it down and picks up the candelabra.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	537	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_72564fa9		Her hands are still shaking.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	537	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_butler_room_6eaeb562	nurse	I wish you hadn't made me do this.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2b_billiard_room.rpy	545	nurse "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_lad_discussion_follow_up_8c5592a8		After a little while, someone knocks at my door.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2c_lad_discussion.rpy	7	"[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_lad_discussion_follow_up_a5aa9009	lad	Not really. About what?	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2c_lad_discussion.rpy	15	lad "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_lad_discussion_follow_up_5f3274d2	psychic	I believe it's getting quite late.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2c_lad_discussion.rpy	25	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_lad_discussion_follow_up_118c75a1	psychic	We ought to get some rest now.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2c_lad_discussion.rpy	25	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day2_evening_lad_discussion_follow_up_d1a82ab3	lad	Of course, I'll see you tomorrow.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 2/3_Evening/2c_lad_discussion.rpy	31	lad "[what]"
psychic_day3_morning_9d9b9f6d		Unsurprisingly, I slept terribly.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	28	"[what]"
psychic_day3_morning_303c7ca3		At least it's the last day. All of this will be over soon.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	28	"[what]"
psychic_day3_morning_95d3b284		Now I need to get my things ready and head to Ted Harring.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	36	"[what]"
psychic_day3_morning_96480bbb		Even though I didn't have a talk with Ted Harring last night, I should still see him.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	42	"[what]"
psychic_day3_morning_412124a6		On my way to Ted's, the emptiness of the Manor hits me.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	49	"[what]"
psychic_day3_morning_c63bb81f		There is not a sound that can be heard.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	49	"[what]"
psychic_day3_morning_d34be711		It gives me a chill.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	49	"[what]"
psychic_day3_morning_798961ee		I stop in front of his door.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	49	"[what]"
psychic_day3_morning_bfba5f04		He is not responding.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	61	"[what]"
psychic_day3_morning_ed9b4db2		I hope he is well.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	61	"[what]"
psychic_day3_morning_ec85bbed	psychic	Mr Harring, are you there?	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	69	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day3_morning_9c998fb0		And we started to look for others in the manor,	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	82	"[what]"
psychic_day3_morning_9c235a67		inspecting every room.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	82	"[what]"
psychic_day3_morning_68a7c450		I let him choose where we were going,	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	82	"[what]"
psychic_day3_morning_1042dd2b		even though his choices didn't always make much sense.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	82	"[what]"
psychic_day3_morning_80014cf0		We searched the Manor extensively, but we didn't find much anything interesting.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	96	"[what]"
psychic_day3_morning_ab8ec6a2		Ted Harring insisted on taking an empty gun from the gun room.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	96	"[what]"
psychic_day3_morning_b22d9779		I am not sure what he intends to do with it.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	96	"[what]"
psychic_day3_morning_19084138		Tired and demoralised, we decided to take a break in the tea room.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	96	"[what]"
psychic_day3_morning_498cc902		We rested there until we heard a familiar voice.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	96	"[what]"
psychic_day3_morning_4ca5f41d		I sat there quietly, pondering what had happened, what I should do next.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	114	"[what]"
psychic_day3_morning_3d4bc1c2		After some time, they came back.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	120	"[what]"
psychic_day3_morning_has_not_visited_lad_74cf0e24	lad	I'm coming!	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	135	lad "[what]"
psychic_day3_morning_has_not_visited_lad_9da43bc9		Finally, I was getting worried.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	139	"[what]"
psychic_day3_morning_has_not_visited_lad_f62c5e41		He opens the door for me and I enter.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	139	"[what]"
psychic_day3_morning_has_not_visited_lad_b7d91352	psychic	Mr Harring, I am sorry to disturb you but something strange is happening.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	149	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day3_morning_has_not_visited_lad_5bc886f2	lad	What do you mean?	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	153	lad "[what]"
psychic_day3_morning_has_not_visited_lad_feceb16a	psychic	I haven't seen any staff members on my way here.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	157	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day3_morning_has_not_visited_lad_52434750	psychic	At this hour, they should be busy with lighting fires, cleaning and setting up breakfast.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	157	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day3_morning_has_not_visited_lad_c94b7d90	psychic	Yet, I neither saw nor heard anyone.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	157	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day3_morning_has_not_visited_lad_f5e8f1ce	psychic	It's as silent as a graveyard in here.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	157	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day3_morning_has_not_visited_lad_40d8711a	lad	Are you sure it's not just because it's so early?	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	167	lad "[what]"
psychic_day3_morning_has_not_visited_lad_402a526d	psychic	I'm certain.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	171	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day3_morning_has_not_visited_lad_569f2baf	psychic	I was up at the same time yesterday, and the house was bustling with activity.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	171	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day3_morning_has_not_visited_lad_d054e3ce	psychic	Something's not right, I assure you.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	171	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day3_morning_has_not_visited_lad_85df4b75	lad	Okay, if you say so.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	179	lad "[what]"
psychic_day3_morning_has_not_visited_lad_1b9b4748		He paused for a second there, he must have realised it's serious.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	183	"[what]"
psychic_day3_morning_has_not_visited_lad_443e8e9a	lad	What do you propose we do then?	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	187	lad "[what]"
psychic_day3_morning_has_not_visited_lad_5f104d7b	psychic	I am not sure, but I think we should start by searching the Manor to try to understand what's happening.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	191	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day3_morning_has_not_visited_lad_9be09d4d	lad	Alright, let's investigate then.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	195	lad "[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_63b7e1c7		We waited in the tea room without exchanging any words for a short time.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	28	"[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_52673076		Finally, Captain Sinha comes back.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	28	"[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_1bd62419		Leave? I can't leave.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	40	"[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_c5e4627a		Yet something doesn't feel right.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	40	"[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_6612254e		I have a terrible premonition about this place.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	40	"[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_5d3a08ff		I can see it... burning.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	40	"[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_53c8b9f6		Gosh, it's like I can smell it too.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	40	"[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_529b090b		What's happening to me? Am I losing my mind?	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	40	"[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_3bfd05c9		I know it makes no sense to go out right now, but everything in my body compels me to leave this place as fast as possible.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	40	"[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_618cd510	lad	Of course, I'll stay.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	67	lad "[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_04c8310e	lad	Only a monster would leave you alone here in this condition.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	67	lad "[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_10964d25	psychic	Thank you Mr Harring!	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	73	psychic normal "[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_f8d7357c	psychic	That means the world to me.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	73	psychic normal "[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_a001c80a	captain	Very well.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	79	captain "[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_eb80151b	captain	I will go right now then. I don't want to lose time.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	79	captain "[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_90d7fb47	captain	Hopefully, I'll be back with help before nightfall.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	79	captain "[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_8e05b74f	psychic	Thank you captain.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	87	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_254faa87	psychic	I hope you'll be safe.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	87	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_681337c0	lad	Yes, thank you.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	93	lad "[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_287e2a10		And then he is on his way.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	97	"[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_escape_714d64ff	psychic	You're right.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_escape.rpy	5	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_escape_572d27cf	psychic	I can't stay one more minute in this cursed place.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_escape.rpy	5	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_escape_16b5c73f	captain	Are you sure?	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_escape.rpy	11	captain "[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_escape_85d1b9fb	captain	It won't be an easy walk.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_escape.rpy	11	captain "[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_escape_c9524329	psychic	I am certain.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_escape.rpy	17	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_escape_9f8ca64d	captain	Very well, let's get ready before we leave then.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_escape.rpy	21	captain "[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_escape_5c553e6e	captain	I suggest we all put on our most comfortable shoes, warm clothing and leave everything else here.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_escape.rpy	21	captain "[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_escape_ac08cad1	captain	No need to be encumbered by our luggage. Hopefully, we will come back soon enough to retrieve it.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_escape.rpy	21	captain "[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_escape_4a657954	captain	Let's get ready and meet in the main hall in 15 minutes.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_escape.rpy	21	captain "[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_escape_188b3bbc	captain	Do you agree?	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_escape.rpy	21	captain "[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_escape_e418ad92	psychic	Of course.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_escape.rpy	33	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_escape_732ae0a3	lad	Sounds good to me.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_escape.rpy	37	lad "[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_escape_5c8483cd		I rush to my room, grab what I need, and hurry down to the hall as fast as possible.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_escape.rpy	47	"[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_escape_f8dec43b		The others are already there.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_escape.rpy	47	"[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_escape_a8b0f1d1		Captain Sinha has a large coat and sturdy boots with him.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_escape.rpy	47	"[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_escape_3bcec7cb		Ted Harring, on the other hand, doesn't seem to have changed his clothes at all.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_escape.rpy	47	"[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_escape_54ce378d	captain	All right, if everyone is ready, let's set out.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_escape.rpy	57	captain "[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_escape_42a95a16		We then proceed to exit the house, leaving its impressive shadow behind us.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_escape.rpy	61	"[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_escape_65d1d4b0		We've been walking for a couple of miles already.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_escape.rpy	69	"[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_escape_521bedc3		I am struggling to keep up but, besides that, everything is going smoothly.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_escape.rpy	69	"[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_escape_00b1579f		Maybe too smoothly.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_escape.rpy	69	"[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_escape_6c7c483e		I stop to take a brief break.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_escape.rpy	69	"[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_escape_58d1e457		As I catch my breath, I look at the forest surrounding us.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_escape.rpy	69	"[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_escape_f64ee9d8		Then...	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_escape.rpy	69	"[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_escape_c49db165	psychic	Captain, could you come and see something?	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_escape.rpy	85	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_escape_a60f3985	captain	Of course, what is it?	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_escape.rpy	89	captain "[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_escape_8df4bf61		He retraces his steps to my level, while Ted Harring continues walking ahead.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_escape.rpy	93	"[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_escape_251b381f	psychic	Can you look over there, behind that huge oak tree?	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_escape.rpy	97	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_escape_2b377656	psychic	I thought I saw something.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_escape.rpy	97	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_escape_c7a4350f	psychic	I might be imagining things, but it looked like a person.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_escape.rpy	97	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_escape_a2845688	captain	I can spot the tree but see no one.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_escape.rpy	105	captain "[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_escape_c88b45f7	psychic	I don't see it anymore, but it was definitely there a second ago.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_escape.rpy	109	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_escape_229d4982	psychic	I'm sure of it.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_escape.rpy	109	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_escape_2007b19e	captain	Alright, I'll go and check quickly.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_escape.rpy	115	captain "[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_escape_6d1b47c2		Without hesitation, he rushes towards the large tree ahead.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_escape.rpy	119	"[what]"
