psychic_day3_afternoon_escape_f5ff33b5		Sushil Sinha has succumbed to his injuries.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_escape.rpy	167	"[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_escape_d2df70b1		There is no one alive at the manor.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_escape.rpy	167	"[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_escape_1c9f57c6		In addition to Samuel Manning, Thomas Moody, and Daniel Baldwin, they've also found Rosalind Marsh's body.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_escape.rpy	167	"[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_escape_6acefdd7		She has been stabbed to death and is lying somewhere in the attic.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_escape.rpy	167	"[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_escape_c7b1b824		However, they have found no trace of Lady Claythorn and her staff.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2b_escape.rpy	167	"[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_stay_fa62c0e8		We both go on to our room, leaving Rosalind Marsh alone in the dining room.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2_stay.rpy	9	"[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_stay_391e2694		I did not waste time going to my room and back, but Rosalind Marsh and Ted Harring are already seated when I come back.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2_stay.rpy	15	"[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_stay_8add07b1		Ted Harring must have been very fast, I suppose he was scared to stay alone for too long.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2_stay.rpy	15	"[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_stay_4f1b3c80		We start eating in silence, each deep in our own thoughts.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2_stay.rpy	15	"[what]"
