psychic_day3_afternoon_convince_nurse_5d233911	nurse	Look what you made me do!	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2_stay.rpy	181	nurse "[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_convince_nurse_66e620ec	psychic	I... just wanted... to...	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2_stay.rpy	187	psychic "[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_convince_nurse_5b3c0f47		I look down at my stomach.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2_stay.rpy	191	"[what]"
psychic_day3_afternoon_convince_nurse_2ae7891d		It's all covered in blood.	game/scripts/psychic/Day 3/2_Afternoon/2_stay.rpy	191	"[what]"
psychic_ending_lord_25518147		You fell in the staircase.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_endings.rpy	10	"[what]"
psychic_ending_lord_bea55201		You are not sure what happened there in the attic, but it got the best of you.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_endings.rpy	10	"[what]"
psychic_ending_burns_78d5f871		The smoke from the fire caused you to lose consciousness.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_endings.rpy	27	"[what]"
psychic_ending_burns_b6c0766e		Needless to say, you didn't survive it.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_endings.rpy	27	"[what]"
psychic_ending_burns_df080157		The whole place burned down.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_endings.rpy	27	"[what]"
psychic_ending_burns_a5621fc0		A tragic ending for Claythorn Manor and everyone still within.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_endings.rpy	27	"[what]"
psychic_ending_shot_942d34d1		You were shot.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_endings.rpy	46	"[what]"
psychic_ending_shot_0acab5b7		That is on you for trusting strangers.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_endings.rpy	46	"[what]"
psychic_ending_shot_ac953e1b		In tough situations, sometimes the best course of action is to fight.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_endings.rpy	46	"[what]"
psychic_ending_shot_b128c513		Keep that in mind for the future.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_endings.rpy	46	"[what]"
psychic_ending_escape_272bcd27		You've made it!	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_endings.rpy	65	"[what]"
psychic_ending_escape_8661558b		And you've managed to save one person with you.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_endings.rpy	65	"[what]"
psychic_ending_escape_c4075684		That's not bad, and you could stop there.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_endings.rpy	65	"[what]"
psychic_ending_escape_9b0a8348		Not everybody needs a happy ending.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_endings.rpy	65	"[what]"
psychic_ending_escape_d1b23609		And this one is as good as any.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_endings.rpy	65	"[what]"
psychic_ending_escape_ddf8b423		So it's up to you to just stop,	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_endings.rpy	65	"[what]"
psychic_ending_escape_75de6faf		Or to keep playing.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_endings.rpy	65	"[what]"
psychic_ending_nurse_thief_e1f0b527		You were bludgeoned to death with a candelabra.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_endings.rpy	91	"[what]"
psychic_ending_nurse_thief_ff24e665		Killed by a desperate woman with too much to lose.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_endings.rpy	91	"[what]"
psychic_ending_nurse_thief_fb8cbb3d		A horrific end.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_endings.rpy	91	"[what]"
psychic_ending_nurse_thief_a33cd9ab		And not something you could have expected from a middle-aged nurse.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_endings.rpy	91	"[what]"
psychic_ending_nurse_thief_ab965a57		Be careful, some people will go to terrible lengths when cornered.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_endings.rpy	91	"[what]"
psychic_generic_weather_friday_f7d07495	psychic	Well, it is not very original to ask about such things when meeting someone new.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	19	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_weather_friday_6f7319e4	psychic	But it is true that this is not your average rain. It looks more like a dangerous storm to me.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	19	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_weather_friday_d0307d15	psychic	And since we are, essentially, in the middle of nowhere, that is reason enough to be a little nervous, I suppose.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	19	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_weather_saturday_ca7b5cfa	psychic	I must say that last night was quite scary.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	31	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_weather_saturday_17b4441c	psychic	It has been a while since I've experienced a storm like that.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	31	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_weather_saturday_41f9470d	psychic	We should consider ourselves lucky if there is no damage to the manor.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	31	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_weather_sunday_3ecb335a	psychic	Really, you want to talk about the weather with everything that is happening around us?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	43	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_weather_sunday_6954b67e	psychic	What is wrong with you?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	43	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_room_10584ba1	psychic	That's a strange question.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	54	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_room_32ae0838	psychic	But if you must know, my room is "Elizabeth the First."	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	54	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_age_lad_6354a533	psychic	I beg your pardon?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	69	psychic angry "[what]"
psychic_generic_age_lad_bd2c28e7	psychic	Are you truly asking me that? Were you raised in a barn?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	69	psychic angry "[what]"
psychic_generic_age_lad_74ed0c62	psychic	Only a person without any social skills would ask such a question of a respectable lady.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	69	psychic angry "[what]"
psychic_generic_age_lad_d1b8c192		I mutter an apology and quickly change the subject.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	77	"[what]"
psychic_generic_age_nurse_b8dff460	psychic	My, my. I would not have expected that question from you, Miss Marsh.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	88	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_age_nurse_5f802f17	psychic	Surely you know some things simply are not asked.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	88	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_age_nurse_fcc33b03		She holds my gaze for a moment, a faint smile playing on her lips.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	94	"[what]"
psychic_generic_age_nurse_db980b26		I have no good answer to that. I clear my throat and move on.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	94	"[what]"
psychic_generic_background_intro_e2bd67d2	psychic	Oh, where to begin? I suppose I'm just an old woman who keeps herself busy.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	107	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_background_intro_d8216996	psychic	I tend to my garden and brew herbal remedies,	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	107	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_background_intro_433f738f	psychic	and I usually keep to myself, save for the séances I frequently organise.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	107	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_background_f9785f46	lad	Séances? You mean like talking to the dead?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	122	lad "[what]"
psychic_generic_background_a9b854fc	psychic	Well, simply put, yes. But there's more to it than that, of course.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	126	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_background_57b29974	lad	I've never been to one of those... séances. How does that work?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	130	lad "[what]"
psychic_generic_background_8bb1d771	psychic	There isn't just one way of doing it.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	134	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_background_4c4637ae	psychic	Personally, I usually ask people to bring items that belonged to their loved ones who have passed.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	134	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_background_eacf03c2	psychic	Through these objects, I am able to form a bond with the soul of the deceased.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	134	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_background_97390fe6	psychic	Then they communicate with me. Sometimes it is but a whisper, scarcely audible.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	134	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_background_8c21a573	psychic	Other times, I can see them clearly, just as I see you now.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	134	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_background_29f1778c	psychic	And on rare occasions, they can take over my body and speak directly to their loved ones through me.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	134	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_background_2117328f	lad	You mean... like being possessed?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	148	lad "[what]"
psychic_generic_background_c0f99407	psychic	Yes, but do not worry, there is nothing unholy in it.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	152	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_background_1756e44b	psychic	It only lasts for a few moments, and I always regain full control immediately after.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	152	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_background_e7cedf18		Still... that doesn't make me feel at ease.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	158	"[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_story_c3b651d8	psychic	I was invited here because of something I did a couple of years ago.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	168	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_story_c0503b07	psychic	You might actually remember the event. It was in all the papers at the time.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	168	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_story_84ad9aca	psychic	You see, with my talent, I am sometimes able to help people who desperately need it.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	168	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_story_7407de03	psychic	One day, a young couple came to see me.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	168	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_story_a59b9667	psychic	Their only son, not even five years old, had been kidnapped.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	168	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_story_e4388ca8	psychic	The police had no clues about what might have happened.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	168	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_story_d9a70334	psychic	Desperate, they sought my help.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	168	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_story_4d772db4	psychic	Right away, I could tell the child was still alive but in great danger.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	168	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_story_ac14b4fb	psychic	I saw him with a specific individual whom I described to the couple.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	168	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_story_456c001c	psychic	They were able to identify her immediately.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	168	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_story_f70984e8	psychic	She was an old family friend who often visited their house.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	168	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_story_de3033c8	psychic	Nobody had suspected her until that point.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	168	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_story_79bb4dce	psychic	But it turned out I was right. The child was indeed with her.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	168	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_story_3852f71d	psychic	She was arrested and the boy was safely returned to his parents.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	168	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_story_d31076f6	psychic	Since they were prestigious members of the nobility, a duke and duchess, the story was prominent in the press.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	168	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_story_bb23e442	psychic	My popularity grew quite a lot after that.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	168	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_52fa9faa	lad	Wait, I don't understand.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	211	lad "[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_5406a9f7	lad	How did you know the child was in danger?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	211	lad "[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_f4d6ff5f	lad	You can also communicate with people who are still alive?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	211	lad "[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_fd5764c6	psychic	In a sense yes.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	219	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_cccc3014	psychic	Like I said, there is more to my gift than simply speaking with the dead.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	219	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_3eea9390	psychic	I can also sense if someone's life is at risk.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	219	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_553719ac	psychic	Some say it is because when someone is close to the other world, we can sense them almost like they are already there.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	219	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_4ede373e	psychic	But for myself, I think it's something else entirely.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	219	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_b659872d	psychic	I believe I can only talk to the dead.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	219	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_40d6ec66	psychic	So when I sense someone who yet lives, it means to me there is a version of them that does not.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	219	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_5120b87b	psychic	I am not sure if you understand what I mean.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	219	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_f625be39	lad	I don't know.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	237	lad "[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_9f6c1502	lad	You mean someone can be dead and alive at the same time?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	237	lad "[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_140bba6f	psychic	Yes. I believe some version of the person died in another realm of existence.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	243	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_de0dd0ee	psychic	Then they came back to help a version of them who is still alive.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	243	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_6249a0c1	psychic	I am sorry. That must sound like nonsense to you.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	243	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_fb4d8237	psychic	Forget I said anything. I get carried away sometimes.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	243	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_5918bfd5	psychic	But tell me. Why were you invited yourself?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	243	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_2ddc5440		So I tell her my story.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	257	"[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_1d9ccab2	psychic	Oh how interesting! I assumed most people were here because of something they did during the war.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	261	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_11115d54	lad	It would have been difficult for me. I was but sixteen when the war ended.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	265	lad "[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_e598ec5c	psychic	Really? I thought you were older.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	269	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_manor_f460badf	psychic	Such a magnificent house, is it not?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	281	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_manor_27a6433f	psychic	Even if the style is not very recent, it still possesses a great deal of charm.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	281	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_manor_f795d6cc	psychic	You don't see a lot of that type of place anymore.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	281	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_manor_6b8ff5bb	psychic	The only problem is I don't see a lot of help for a house this big.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	281	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_manor_fea86b0b	psychic	And I don't think money is a problem.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	281	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_manor_6019054d	psychic	Lady Claythorn couldn't possibly give away so much money if she lacked the means.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	281	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_manor_d9d2356b	psychic	More likely, she couldn't find enough people to come live here.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	281	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_manor_f0787ecd	psychic	It has become very hard to recruit good help since the war.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	281	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_manor_b1326387	psychic	And it must be especially difficult when you are so far away from a city.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	281	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_manor_33284f6c	psychic	Even in London, some of my neighbours struggle to find staff.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	281	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_manor_e85c47fc	psychic	In any case, she should have made more of an effort for this weekend.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	281	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_manor_829f0527	psychic	I hope we won't suffer any inconvenience because of this.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	281	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_manor_f3685e16		All right. I would not have thought of that.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	308	"[what]"
psychic_generic_manor_15d2db49		She seems in her element here.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	308	"[what]"
psychic_generic_manor_38ed071d		Am I the only one in here who has never had a butler waiting on him?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	308	"[what]"
psychic_generic_weather_saturday_nurse_4851bc99	nurse	Indeed. One hopes for a quieter day ahead.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	328	nurse "[what]"
psychic_generic_background_nurse_9f1dd696	nurse	I should like to know a little more about you, if you don't mind.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	337	nurse "[what]"
psychic_generic_background_nurse_ef5ff57f	nurse	Séances. I see.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	343	nurse "[what]"
psychic_generic_background_nurse_e02a8077		I keep my expression neutral.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	347	"[what]"
psychic_generic_background_nurse_c9f09f1f		I have met women like her before.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	347	"[what]"
psychic_generic_background_nurse_7372aed6		Sometimes well-meaning, utterly convinced of things that simply are not there.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	347	"[what]"
psychic_generic_background_nurse_2395a520		But more often they are just frauds.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	347	"[what]"
psychic_generic_background_nurse_35ecf111		They take advantage of the vulnerable, the grieving to make a profit.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	347	"[what]"
psychic_generic_background_nurse_2939a371		Those people disgust me.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	347	"[what]"
psychic_generic_background_nurse_dd18e0f8	psychic	Are you alright, Miss Marsh?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	361	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_background_nurse_deaece02	nurse	Of course, I am merely listening.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	365	nurse "[what]"
psychic_generic_background_nurse_e3acd274		My face must have betrayed my thoughts.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	369	"[what]"
psychic_generic_background_nurse_9a2df2d7		She studies me for a moment before letting it pass.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	369	"[what]"
psychic_generic_background_nurse_11ba74f8		But she doesn't elaborate further on her "powers".	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	369	"[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_nurse_032808c4	nurse	Why were you invited here, Mrs Baxter?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	384	nurse "[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_nurse_12efdf98		I listen carefully and say nothing for a moment.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	390	"[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_nurse_9325b43d		That the woman she named was guilty does not prove she fore-saw it.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	390	"[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_nurse_06ea04cb		A lucky guess, most likely, combined with a good deal of charm.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	390	"[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_nurse_ee9387f6		Still, I will not say so.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	390	"[what]"
psychic_generic_heroic_act_nurse_2afcd495	nurse	That must have been an enormous relief for the family.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_choices.rpy	400	nurse "[what]"
psychic_downstairs_default_86208e83		The basement is where the domestic staff work.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_locations.rpy	5	"[what]"
psychic_downstairs_default_ea1a40dd		I definitely shouldn't go down there, it's not my place.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_locations.rpy	5	"[what]"
psychic_library_intro_2a2994df		Here is an impressive library.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_locations.rpy	19	"[what]"
psychic_library_intro_51595cb5		"A Genealogical and Heraldic Dictionary of the Landed Gentry of Great Britain." is open on a table.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_locations.rpy	19	"[what]"
psychic_library_intro_e7c76fb8		The library is still as impressive.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_locations.rpy	29	"[what]"
psychic_library_default_18204270		But I don't feel like reading now.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_locations.rpy	39	"[what]"
psychic_tea_room_default_512b58c8		There's no one here.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_locations.rpy	50	"[what]"
psychic_tea_room_default_47cad4fe		There's no reason to linger.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_locations.rpy	50	"[what]"
psychic_dining_room_default_bd8c3028		The dining area is currently unoccupied.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_locations.rpy	62	"[what]"
psychic_dining_room_default_a19c6425		I shouldn't stay here.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_locations.rpy	62	"[what]"
psychic_billiard_room_default_2e1603a4		The billiard room is empty right now.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_locations.rpy	75	"[what]"
psychic_billiard_room_default_90736cdf		I should leave.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_locations.rpy	75	"[what]"
psychic_garden_default_d7a0f162		A lovely garden.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_locations.rpy	88	"[what]"
psychic_garden_default_6afe529e		I take a peaceful stroll through it.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_locations.rpy	88	"[what]"
psychic_garden_default_14d95352		Still, I notice nothing out of the ordinary.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_locations.rpy	88	"[what]"
psychic_garden_default_82693e82		There is a small shed at the far end of the garden.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_locations.rpy	88	"[what]"
psychic_garden_default_8f78eba1		Nothing in there but tools, I should think.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_locations.rpy	88	"[what]"
psychic_garden_default_c9346339		Not worth the trouble.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_locations.rpy	88	"[what]"
psychic_entrance_hall_default_0d67787e		A very nice great hall.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_locations.rpy	109	"[what]"
psychic_entrance_hall_default_f7c33dd4		But it is totally empty.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_locations.rpy	109	"[what]"
psychic_portrait_gallery_default_654798d3		There are quite a few impressive portraits here.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_locations.rpy	124	"[what]"
psychic_portrait_gallery_default_e98aa06e		However, no one else is present.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_locations.rpy	124	"[what]"
psychic_portrait_gallery_default_e4bd0521		The paintings remain unchanged.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_locations.rpy	134	"[what]"
psychic_bedroom_default_no_answer_770ada03		I knock on the door, waiting for a response.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_locations.rpy	149	"[what]"
psychic_bedroom_default_no_answer_066163ee		There's silence. No one replies.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_generic_locations.rpy	149	"[what]"
psychic_attic_default_8f8a9e75		I climb the stairs to the attic and arrive in a dimly lit hallway.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	8	"[what]"
psychic_attic_default_e857dc25		There are multiple doors, most of them lie in darkness.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	8	"[what]"
psychic_attic_default_1a31377d		As I move into the hallway, I hear something.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	8	"[what]"
psychic_attic_default_d6a6182e	lord	Hello, is someone there?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	18	lord "[what]"
psychic_attic_default_90b03654	psychic	Hello...	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	22	psychic "[what]"
psychic_attic_default_c909be1e	psychic	My name is Amelia Baxter.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	22	psychic "[what]"
psychic_attic_default_1ba4e597	lord	Nice to meet you, Miss Baxter.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	28	lord "[what]"
psychic_attic_default_6fd9daeb	lord	It's rare to meet someone up here.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	28	lord "[what]"
psychic_attic_default_19e3b975	lord	I am usually by myself.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	28	lord "[what]"
psychic_attic_default_fb9cccaa	psychic	Nice to meet you too.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	36	psychic "[what]"
psychic_attic_default_a54ec30c	psychic	I am sorry to ask,	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	36	psychic "[what]"
psychic_attic_default_325b6462	psychic	but who are you?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	36	psychic "[what]"
psychic_attic_default_779a9a2b	lord	Oh, where are my manners?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	44	lord "[what]"
psychic_attic_default_92fef653	lord	I am the Lord of this Manor, of course.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	44	lord "[what]"
psychic_attic_default_7afba655		Wait, what?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	50	"[what]"
psychic_attic_default_da59560f	psychic	I am sorry, Lady Claythorn didn't mention you.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	54	psychic "[what]"
psychic_attic_default_9ac67442	lord	Lady Claythorn? You probably mean my daughter then.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	58	lord "[what]"
psychic_attic_default_7e833d3d	lord	I suppose she likes having all the attention to herself.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	58	lord "[what]"
psychic_attic_default_42a7a72d	lord	She must be relieved that I spend most of my time alone in my room here.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	58	lord "[what]"
psychic_attic_default_b1665cea	psychic	You live here?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	66	psychic "[what]"
psychic_attic_default_84436190	lord	Yes, it's rather uncommon, but I enjoy how peaceful it is.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	70	lord "[what]"
psychic_attic_default_7e80fb78	lord	Plus, I believe I have the biggest room in the manor.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	70	lord "[what]"
psychic_attic_default_08b1b489		He points to the big door in front of the stairs.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	76	"[what]"
psychic_attic_default_5263ba5c	psychic	Right...	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	80	psychic "[what]"
psychic_attic_default_27715248		I don't know what to say. There is something wrong with all this.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	84	"[what]"
psychic_attic_default_994508f1	lord	So my dear, were you looking for something in particular by coming here?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	88	lord "[what]"
psychic_attic_default_6a77595f	psychic	Well, not really. I was mostly exploring your home.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	92	psychic "[what]"
psychic_attic_default_d5ec4c50	lord	In that case, I would advise you not to linger here.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	96	lord "[what]"
psychic_attic_default_99cd7874	lord	There's not much to see in this old attic.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	96	lord "[what]"
psychic_attic_default_e198a047	lord	You'll find more interesting rooms downstairs.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	96	lord "[what]"
psychic_attic_default_6a3f7036		Alright, he probably wants to stay alone.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	104	"[what]"
psychic_attic_default_4b7d7172	psychic	Of course, I will continue visiting elsewhere.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	108	psychic "[what]"
psychic_attic_default_f0a59396	lord	Thank you, my dear.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	112	lord "[what]"
psychic_attic_default_31ee930a	lord	Enjoy your stay.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	112	lord "[what]"
psychic_attic_default_11b4c184	psychic	Thank you.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	118	psychic "[what]"
psychic_attic_default_140301cd		This was rather peculiar.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	122	"[what]"
psychic_attic_default_9385df02		I don't think I should return here too soon.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	122	"[what]"
psychic_attic_default_8de0f676		I really shouldn't go back there right now.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	136	"[what]"
psychic_attic_return_too_soon_dbf7696d		I climb the stairs to the attic.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	147	"[what]"
psychic_attic_return_too_soon_5f07a903		The room is filled with darkness.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	147	"[what]"
psychic_attic_return_too_soon_34380303		I think I shouldn't venture here.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	147	"[what]"
psychic_attic_return_too_soon_898cf38c		There's no reason for me to disturb Lord Claythorn any further,	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	147	"[what]"
psychic_attic_return_too_soon_1813646a		at least for now.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	147	"[what]"
psychic_attic_return_too_soon_32534e2c		So I turn back.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	147	"[what]"
psychic_attic_return_eea9e734		I've decided to return to the attic.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	169	"[what]"
psychic_attic_return_53c7099b		I have some questions to ask the "Lord" of this place.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	169	"[what]"
psychic_attic_return_ce300685		But am I sure I should?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	169	"[what]"
psychic_attic_return_af0ad211		I've changed my mind, I'd better leave him alone.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	184	"[what]"
psychic_attic_return_73c399c4		God knows what I might stir up here.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	184	"[what]"
psychic_library_look_for_lord_f3d15b39		I take a closer look at the book.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	197	"[what]"
psychic_library_look_for_lord_fd239c7d		It's the 8th edition, printed in 1894. That was quite some time ago.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	197	"[what]"
psychic_library_look_for_lord_64fec823		Perhaps I should look up information about the people living here.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	197	"[what]"
psychic_library_look_for_lord_4178f1cf		I find multiple entries for families with the name Claythorn.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	209	"[what]"
psychic_library_look_for_lord_succeed_2ae58ff2		I turn back to the page with the Claythorn name.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	228	"[what]"
psychic_library_look_for_lord_succeed_693088ee		Now I know which one to look at.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	228	"[what]"
psychic_library_look_for_lord_succeed_39a8bbcc		There's only one place associated with a Nicholas.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	234	"[what]"
psychic_library_look_for_lord_succeed_35c5c7a9		There's additional information about the history of this place.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	242	"[what]"
psychic_library_look_for_lord_succeed_2e6ec1fc		But something seems off.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	242	"[what]"
psychic_library_look_for_lord_succeed_968f1cd6		Born in 1813.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	242	"[what]"
psychic_library_look_for_lord_succeed_cce4283b		Wait, that would make him...	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	242	"[what]"
psychic_library_look_for_lord_succeed_a5788003		111 years old?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	242	"[what]"
psychic_library_look_for_lord_succeed_872309ef		That can't be right.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	242	"[what]"
psychic_library_look_for_lord_succeed_755414d7		If that were true, he'd likely be the oldest man in England.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	242	"[what]"
psychic_library_look_for_lord_succeed_ef8815ee		Possibly even the world.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	242	"[what]"
psychic_library_look_for_lord_succeed_c6f4faab		Yet he didn't appear to be that old.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	242	"[what]"
psychic_library_look_for_lord_succeed_ef03f78a		I suppose this must be an mistake in the book.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	242	"[what]"
psychic_library_look_for_lord_succeed_101f00e6		If they tried to list all the gentry of this country, they were bound to make some errors.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	242	"[what]"
psychic_library_look_for_lord_failed_d50032b4		But I am not sure which one relates to the family living here.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	277	"[what]"
psychic_library_look_for_lord_failed_474b65c5		How could I? I don't even know Lady Claythorn's first name.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	277	"[what]"
psychic_portrait_gallery_look_for_lord_d836a8e3		Now, I realise that there are probably paintings of the Claythorn family here.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	290	"[what]"
psychic_portrait_gallery_look_for_lord_2bb0c908		I can't find Lady Claythorn here, but after a while I spot Lord Claythorn.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	296	"[what]"
psychic_portrait_gallery_look_for_lord_e56afef0		He looks exactly as he does in real life.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	296	"[what]"
psychic_portrait_gallery_look_for_lord_c13ba282		I check the label below the painting.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	296	"[what]"
psychic_portrait_gallery_look_for_lord_84b25dea		"Nicholas III, of Claythorn Manor"	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	296	"[what]"
psychic_portrait_gallery_look_for_lord_3355ce1e		So, Nicholas is his first name.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	296	"[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_6686db65		I know I must confront him.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	317	"[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_7df9d327		But what am I hoping to prove?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	317	"[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_939c35ab		That's a dangerous path I fear I'm taking here.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	317	"[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_14c5173a		He is not in the hallway, so I head to his room.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	317	"[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_8c8a02dc		I don't bother knocking and enter right away.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	317	"[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_36dfb844		It's even more decrepit than the rest of the attic.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	333	"[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_2569715a		Why would anyone decide to live here?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	333	"[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_01d9eef9	psychic	Sir Nicholas, are you there?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	339	psychic "[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_f0be3730	lord	Oh good, you've returned.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	345	lord "[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_ad4b15f5	lord	And you've learned my name as well.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	345	lord "[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_f0db397b	lord	Impressive.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	345	lord "[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_c2424056	psychic	That's not all I've learned, though.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	353	psychic "[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_04f089ae	lord	Really? What else?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	357	lord "[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_7c5ffe81	psychic	That you're supposed to be 111 years old.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	361	psychic "[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_005b1c15	psychic	Is this true?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	361	psychic "[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_6ea3b237	lord	111 years...	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	367	lord "[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_74952fc5	lord	Has it been that long already?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	367	lord "[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_a11006ed	lord	Well, I suppose that's true.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	367	lord "[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_b905d013	psychic	No one can live this long.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	375	psychic "[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_488d00ca	lord	Probably not.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	379	lord "[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_f8732536	psychic	So, are you...	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	383	psychic "[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_f27311da	psychic	Are you...	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	383	psychic "[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_e0f4cbf2	lord	Am I what, my dear?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	389	lord "[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_7488fcef	lord	Dead?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	389	lord "[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_8e3c1572	lord	That's what you think, right?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	395	lord "[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_ab8d0987	lord	Or rather, it's what you're hoping.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	395	lord "[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_ccf0df80	psychic	What do you mean?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	401	psychic surprised "[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_83ccac25	lord	Because either I am a ghost...	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	405	lord "[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_81721182	lord	Or you're just losing your mind.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	405	lord "[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_b51cbe5b		He inches closer to me.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	411	"[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_fdc30a58	lord	So, which will it be?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	415	lord angry "[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_c844ef75	lord	That a liar, someone who preyed on the bereaved to make money,	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	415	lord angry "[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_4b7eeb5f	lord	is actually a real-life medium?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	415	lord angry "[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_7e412d79	lord	That it was in her all along?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	415	lord angry "[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_f9f0c2a1	lord	I understand the appeal to believe that now.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	415	lord angry "[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_29fa8b1c	lord	That would mean that you weren't really deceiving people your entire life.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	415	lord angry "[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_50c1e03a	lord	But that would be too easy, wouldn't it?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	415	lord angry "[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_b47a1f8c	lord	I am afraid there is only one other alternative.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	415	lord angry "[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_e8790b55	lord	You must see it too now.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	415	lord angry "[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_5b9d2182	lord	You understand what's happening here, don't you?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	415	lord angry "[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_cca9c215		He is now almost next to my face.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	437	"[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_f19b02b0		I can't take this.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	437	"[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_a4b48b23		I rush outside his room.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	437	"[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_13a4defa		But he is already there.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	447	"[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_0413eb4b		Standing in front of me.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	447	"[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_96a13cf1	lord	Where are you going?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	453	lord angry "[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_b6e3b285	lord	Do you think you can get rid of me that easily?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	453	lord angry "[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_223fec09	psychic	What do you want from me?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	459	psychic surprised "[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_bb1a15b6	lord	Me? I don't want anything.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	463	lord angry "[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_f9ba7f26	lord	The question is: what do you want?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	463	lord angry "[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_5bbba9f6		I slowly take a step back towards the stairs.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	469	"[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_2053ce00	lord	Do you feel remorse maybe?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	473	lord angry "[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_78fe6d00		I take another step.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	477	"[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_4b0730c9	lord	Some regret over what you've done?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	481	lord angry "[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_067290b1	psychic	Please, leave me alone.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	485	psychic surprised "[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_c7c5adaf		I try to walk back further,	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	489	"[what]"
psychic_confront_lord_f0f766a9		but my foot doesn't find the ground behind me.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_lord_locations.rpy	489	"[what]"
psychic_generic_other_guests_saturday_3dd74d4d	psychic	I haven't had time to form an opinion of everyone yet.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	9	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_other_guests_saturday_e2cb56ab	psychic	I have only had time to speak with Captain Sinha, and with that poor drunkard Samuel Manning.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	9	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_other_guests_saturday_6a088463	psychic	And I could also exchange a few words with our hostess, Lady Claythorn.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	9	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_other_guests_saturday_hunt_4ef976b2	psychic	You know that I already talked with Samuel Manning, Captain Sinha and our host.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	38	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_other_guests_saturday_hunt_2ad5cb85	psychic	Now, I have also talked a little with Miss Marsh.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	42	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_other_guests_friday_daeb35bf	psychic	I've just met them. So I can't say I know a lot yet.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	52	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_other_guests_friday_9531e223	psychic	All I know is that this guy over there ...	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	52	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_other_guests_friday_38e2ec2e		She points at Sushil Sinha.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	58	"[what]"
psychic_generic_other_guests_friday_a90e991e	psychic	... is monopolising the conversation.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	62	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_other_guests_friday_94aa6098	psychic	And he is very noisy too.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	62	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_other_guests_friday_03a459f9	psychic	It's not very tactful if you ask me.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	62	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_drunk_saturday_morning_8b37fe51	psychic	Well, I believe you can tell as well as I that he is a dangerous drunk.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	76	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_drunk_saturday_morning_2a29d6df	psychic	We better stay away from him.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	76	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_drunk_saturday_morning_83565488		A reasonable enough assessment, I suppose.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	84	"[what]"
psychic_generic_drunk_saturday_morning_0e5fbaf1		Though I would have put it differently.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	84	"[what]"
psychic_generic_drunk_saturday_morning_e440404d		In my experience, drunks are simply wounded persons.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	84	"[what]"
psychic_generic_drunk_saturday_morning_ac072aff		There is no reason to vilify them.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	84	"[what]"
psychic_generic_captain_saturday_morning_38fd0162	psychic	He appears to me the very image of a military man.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	100	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_captain_saturday_morning_3c4b89aa	psychic	Except for, you know, his origin.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	100	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_captain_saturday_morning_e38d699d	psychic	I did not think they would accept indigenous people in the British Army.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	100	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_captain_saturday_morning_073b2de4	psychic	But aside from that, he is exactly like other officers I have met.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	100	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_captain_saturday_morning_133bbe7c	psychic	Bold, sure of himself, and never shy of speaking about himself.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	100	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_captain_saturday_morning_ffb8eb56	psychic	I bet he will keep on telling stories about his "Glorious Days" during one war or another.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	100	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_captain_saturday_morning_00d9cdc0	psychic	I find it in poor taste, so I shall try to avoid him in the coming days.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	100	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_captain_saturday_morning_8cce9435	psychic	I suggest you do the same, unless you want to be bored to death.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	100	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_host_saturday_morning_ae2f7036	psychic	I only exchanged a few pleasantries with the lady of the house.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	124	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_host_saturday_morning_a2cb3148	psychic	She seems delightful to me.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	124	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_host_saturday_morning_c109a640	psychic	What pleased me even more was that she addressed me as an equal.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	124	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_host_saturday_morning_ac616b26	psychic	That's very different from most noble people I've met.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	124	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_host_saturday_morning_c1ed4be3		They usually look down on people like you...	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	136	"[what]"
psychic_generic_host_saturday_morning_704be2d2		... and me.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	136	"[what]"
psychic_generic_host_saturday_morning_d6773484		She paused a little too long before adding "and me".	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	136	"[what]"
psychic_generic_host_saturday_morning_6c7f0c79		I don't like that.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	136	"[what]"
psychic_generic_nurse_saturday_hunt_a696ee4e	psychic	From what I've seen, I believe she is a very respectable woman.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	152	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_nurse_saturday_hunt_847e84f1	psychic	She worked most of her life as a nurse.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	152	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_nurse_saturday_hunt_6df83fbe	psychic	So I believe the prize money could help her retire.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	152	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_other_guests_saturday_evening_1d5ff287	psychic	Good question, we'll be stronger if we know who to be wary of.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	164	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_other_guests_saturday_evening_95ce4441	psychic	I've thought about it and Samuel Manning is of course the prime suspect.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	164	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_other_guests_saturday_evening_6572d05f	psychic	But he is locked in his room now, so I wouldn't worry about him too much.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	164	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_other_guests_saturday_evening_25251b17	psychic	The other obvious suspect is Thomas Moody.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	164	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_other_guests_saturday_evening_2b29af66	psychic	The fact that he wears a mask is the perfect way to hide his true identity.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	164	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_other_guests_saturday_evening_c4787da5	psychic	But he can't really hurt us anymore, can he?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	164	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_other_guests_saturday_evening_29b0c484	psychic	So that leaves us three persons to worry about: Sushil Sinha, Lady Claythorn and Rosalind Marsh.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	164	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_captain_saturday_evening_7630a618	psychic	Captain Sinha is the one I am most worried about.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	186	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_captain_saturday_evening_2108dc97	psychic	He is the strongest of us, has military experience.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	186	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_captain_saturday_evening_92eb1356	psychic	And he often took command during dramatic moments, which means he can try to drive us where he wants.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	186	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_captain_saturday_evening_5b769418	psychic	I would be very cautious around him if I were you.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	186	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_host_saturday_evening_ad42ced1	psychic	If money is not the reason behind the murders, then I suppose she would be suspicious.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	201	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_host_saturday_evening_5a51378c	psychic	After all, she is the one who called all of us here.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	201	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_host_saturday_evening_6183f3c9	psychic	But as I said, it would be a lot of work to organise all this, and for what?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	201	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_host_saturday_evening_ae288a13	psychic	To kill a few of her enemies?	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	201	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_host_saturday_evening_1084681e	psychic	That seems a bit far-fetched.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	201	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_host_saturday_evening_f5c2bca9	psychic	Also, she seemed very nice to me.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	201	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_host_saturday_evening_9adf6964	psychic	But of course that doesn't mean much.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	201	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_nurse_saturday_evening_e2a4cbe3	psychic	Miss Marsh definitely doesn't have the type of a killer.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	221	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_nurse_saturday_evening_47e80f71	psychic	But that's not reason enough to think she couldn't be.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	221	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_nurse_saturday_evening_8c191371	psychic	She is very discreet.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	221	psychic "[what]"
psychic_generic_nurse_saturday_evening_9c435dd5	psychic	That could be a way to search the manor while she relies on an accomplice for the more "physical" part of the robbery.	game/scripts/psychic/psychic_other_guests.rpy	221	psychic "[what]"
tutorial_clock_51bd4dc3	tutorial	Wait, don't you hear something ticking?	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	7	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_clock_86a754c4	tutorial	If you haven't noticed it yet, look at the clock in the upper-left corner.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	7	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_clock_5a0ca5eb	tutorial	There, you can see the current time, as well as the day.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	7	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_clock_dabb7d11	tutorial	This helpful tool will move as the story progresses, for example, when you start a new chapter of this adventure.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	7	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_clock_f2ffdee4	tutorial	Also, when you are faced with multiple choices, each action will take a different amount of time.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	7	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_clock_f9cdb12c	tutorial	Since each scene has a limited duration, this means you won't always have the opportunity to explore every option on a list.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	7	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_clock_1a5056e6	tutorial	So make every choice count.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	7	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_clock_cf695f8f	tutorial	Also, there is no need to rush reading, the time spent on an choice is set and not dependent on the speed of your actions.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	7	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_description_hidden_df478a60	tutorial	Congratulations on discovering your first piece of information about a character!	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	36	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_description_hidden_1974e106	tutorial	Learning about characters is crucial in this game. You can find two types of information: essential and trivial.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	36	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_description_hidden_a7a817bd	tutorial	To unlock a new playable character, it is necessary to learn all the essential facts about them.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	36	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_description_hidden_4e749191	tutorial	Once you have acquired this knowledge, you will be able to restart the story from their perspective.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	36	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_description_hidden_a9d34e28	tutorial	While conversing with a character can unlock certain information, some facts can only be revealed at specific moments in the story.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	36	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_description_hidden_6ae5ea2f	tutorial	The "Characters" menu gives you an estimation of how much essential information has been unlocked, as well as a complete description of a character.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	36	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_description_hidden_fcdfabf3	tutorial	At the beginning, the descriptions are riddled with holes. It's up to you to fill those holes to reveal someone's true story.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	36	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_description_hidden_c9bb0971	tutorial	Check out for yourself.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	36	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_map_f7d5cd2e	tutorial	Well done, you just found new information about the Manor.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	66	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_map_8fa297ad	tutorial	As a result, additional details have been added to the Manor map to assist you in navigating the house.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	66	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_map_7bd96e9b	tutorial	You can access this information by navigating to the "Map" menu here.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	66	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_intuition_8cab1c54	tutorial	You just received your first "Intuition"	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	85	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_intuition_32a2c26a	tutorial	An "Intuition" is a powerful tool.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	85	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_intuition_0178edcc	tutorial	Some say that when a death is particularly strong, it leaves a mark that can be felt across different planes of existence.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	85	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_intuition_4232042a	tutorial	Others believe it's the ghost of an alternate timeline returning to warn you.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	85	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_intuition_601ebdba	tutorial	In any case, it means you will now receive a warning at some point during this adventure.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	85	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_intuition_88ad3212	tutorial	This will allow you to change the course of the story in ways that were previously impossible.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	85	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_intuition_1f3ad676	tutorial	Make good use of it.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	85	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_unlock_character_fd86b2c9	tutorial	You've unlocked a new character!	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	110	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_unlock_character_34cba2ba	tutorial	Now, you can begin the narrative through their point of view.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	110	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_unlock_character_10994769	tutorial	Each character possesses a distinct story, persona, and background.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	110	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_unlock_character_11d8e157	tutorial	This individuality may grant you access to specific choices unavailable to others.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	110	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_unlock_character_92d95747	tutorial	Use the characters' full potential to unravel the mystery of this weekend.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	110	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_progress_6523986e	tutorial	Wait, it looks like you've unlocked something.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	130	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_progress_6821cebb	tutorial	It could be that you made a choice, an observation, or found an object.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	130	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_progress_94abe5df	tutorial	Basically, something that can influence the rest of the story.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	130	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_progress_11fdfa5d	tutorial	To help you, you can now consult the "Progress" page.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	130	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_progress_5c9a92a2	tutorial	Let's have a look at it.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	130	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_restart_4afc8a82	tutorial	You now have to restart the story.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	163	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_restart_91cf3992	tutorial	However, there's no need to worry as you can use the skip button located at the bottom right of the screen to skip over any previously encountered dialogues.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	163	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_restart_f209d0e3	tutorial	You can also use the "CTRL" key on your keyboard.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	170	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_restart_f0e355ca		This blinking icon will be visible when it is possible to fast forward.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	176	"[what]"
tutorial_restart_82ba1291	tutorial	Furthermore, you now have access to the "Restart" button in the "Progress" menu.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	182	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_restart_5a26731f	tutorial	Just choose a chapter on that screen, then any checkpoint from the list.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	182	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_restart_93061741	tutorial	It's now possible to restart the story from the selected checkpoint.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	182	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_restart_2c1aaa7a	tutorial	Please be cautious, as these checkpoints save the previous choices you've made.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	182	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_restart_29631c27	tutorial	Therefore, it may be necessary to start from an earlier point to unlock new story paths.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	182	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_already_chosen_245248ca	tutorial	You've selected a choice that was in dark.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	199	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_already_chosen_66359ae8	tutorial	That means you've already made that choice before.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	199	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_already_chosen_6047283b	tutorial	No need to worry — there's nothing wrong with wanting to retrace your steps.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	199	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_already_chosen_daf931cf	tutorial	However, you should know that if there were other choices to be made afterwards, you've already explored them all as well.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	199	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_already_chosen_47058487	tutorial	To explain, let's take a simple example: imagine a question such as "Do you like apples?"	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	199	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_already_chosen_968aaf7f	tutorial	If you answer "no", then the conversation ends there.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	199	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_already_chosen_b2c741b7	tutorial	But if you choose "yes", a new question appears: "Do you prefer red or green apples?"	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	199	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_already_chosen_f0218313	tutorial	In that case, the "no" will turn dark once you've chosen it once.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	199	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_already_chosen_4a3bb279	tutorial	But the "yes" option from the first question won't turn dark until you've also selected both "red apples" and "green apples".	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	199	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_already_chosen_b14e8208	tutorial	I hope that makes things clearer.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	199	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_already_chosen_map_5a1efd79	tutorial	You've selected a place you've already visited — at least during the same period.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	239	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_already_chosen_map_57d54b2f	tutorial	If you didn't notice, the text appeared in a darker tone.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	239	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_already_chosen_map_b86a803a	tutorial	No need to worry — there's nothing wrong with revisiting the same location.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	239	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_already_chosen_map_2257d5d1	tutorial	But on a map, if a place name appears in dark, you're unlikely to find anything new there.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	239	tutorial "[what]"
tutorial_already_chosen_map_39df6c09	tutorial	I hope that helps you save some time.	game/scripts/tutorials.rpy	239	tutorial "[what]"
library_book_content_74d3b5fb	book	Nicholas Claythorn, of Claythorn Manor, 3rd Earl of Kilbraith.	game/scripts/_common/common_generic_all.rpy	3	book "[what]"
library_book_content_02a2c0d2	book	Born on June 22, 1813.	game/scripts/_common/common_generic_all.rpy	3	book "[what]"
library_book_content_58f065c6	book	His parents were Nicholas Claythorn, 2nd Earl of Kilbraith, and Agnes Cicely.	game/scripts/_common/common_generic_all.rpy	3	book "[what]"
library_book_content_a900cd5b	book	With Mary Kirwan, his wife, he fathered one son and one daughter:	game/scripts/_common/common_generic_all.rpy	3	book "[what]"
library_book_content_dbfba1a2	book	1. Elisabeth, his heir, born in 1865.	game/scripts/_common/common_generic_all.rpy	3	book "[what]"
library_book_content_d25e35ed	book	2. Andrew, born in 1867, died in 1869.	game/scripts/_common/common_generic_all.rpy	3	book "[what]"
library_book_content_ff2ddb3e	book	Lineage...	game/scripts/_common/common_generic_all.rpy	3	book "[what]"
drunk_letter_first_part_e9288705	letter	In case you haven't recognized him yet, the doctor invited this weekend is the same one who treated your wife years ago.	game/scripts/_common/common_generic_drunk.rpy	6	letter "[what]"
drunk_letter_first_part_f2e36743	letter	He is the reason she never recovered, due to his inadequate treatment and withholding of medication for his own benefit.	game/scripts/_common/common_generic_drunk.rpy	6	letter "[what]"
drunk_letter_first_part_260bd0c1	letter	Do what you will with this information.	game/scripts/_common/common_generic_drunk.rpy	6	letter "[what]"
drunk_letter_second_part_1da01c5b	letter	The bastard must pay.	game/scripts/_common/common_generic_drunk.rpy	18	letter "[what]"
drunk_letter_second_part_c13e9966	letter	Don't hesitate.	game/scripts/_common/common_generic_drunk.rpy	18	letter "[what]"
drunk_letter_first_part_burned_1133787e	letter	*** treated yo***	game/scripts/_common/common_generic_drunk.rpy	29	letter "[what]"
drunk_letter_first_part_burned_76ad76d5	letter	** recovered ***	game/scripts/_common/common_generic_drunk.rpy	29	letter "[what]"
drunk_letter_first_part_burned_ac5a896c	letter	Do what you ****.	game/scripts/_common/common_generic_drunk.rpy	29	letter "[what]"
drunk_letter_second_part_burned_a06eb2a7	letter	The b*****	game/scripts/_common/common_generic_drunk.rpy	41	letter "[what]"
drunk_letter_second_part_burned_02d9e6b5	letter	***** hesitate.	game/scripts/_common/common_generic_drunk.rpy	41	letter "[what]"
common_day1_afternoon_station_doctor_nurse_c4712115	nurse	Forgive me — Rosalind Marsh. Are you bound for Claythorn Manor?	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	7	nurse "[what]"
common_day1_afternoon_station_doctor_nurse_b34d7a45	footman	Yes, ma'am. This gentleman will come with us.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	11	footman "[what]"
common_day1_afternoon_station_doctor_nurse_b9166434	doctor	How do you do, Miss Marsh. Doctor Daniel Baldwin.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	15	doctor "[what]"
common_day1_afternoon_station_doctor_nurse_0e60edf4		Daniel Baldwin...	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	21	"[what]"
common_day1_afternoon_station_doctor_nurse_2e27d676		The name is familiar, and yet I cannot quite recollect from where I know it.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	21	"[what]"
common_day1_afternoon_station_doctor_nurse_9990e014		No doubt it is nothing. I have met a great many doctors in my time.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	21	"[what]"
common_day1_afternoon_station_doctor_nurse_bb1aa335	nurse	How do you do, doctor. Was your trip pleasant?	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	29	nurse "[what]"
common_day1_afternoon_station_doctor_nurse_4671df0a	doctor	Quite pleasant, as it happens. And yours?	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	33	doctor "[what]"
common_day1_afternoon_station_doctor_nurse_0e400d3e	nurse	Well enough, thank you. And what...	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	37	nurse "[what]"
common_day1_afternoon_station_doctor_nurse_a7ff01d9		She stops suddenly, surprised, a bit scared.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	43	"[what]"
common_day1_afternoon_station_doctor_nurse_776f27cb		Her gaze fixes on something behind me.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	43	"[what]"
common_day1_afternoon_station_doctor_nurse_638b3d75		I turn quickly.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	43	"[what]"
common_day1_afternoon_station_doctor_nurse_72833b9d		I stop.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	53	"[what]"
common_day1_afternoon_station_doctor_nurse_105d973a		Something — someone — catches my eye over the doctor's shoulder.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	53	"[what]"
common_day1_afternoon_station_doctor_nurse_f8320722		A man has appeared farther along the platform.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	53	"[what]"
common_day1_afternoon_station_doctor_nurse_e17d8a46		He is tall and composed, and most of his face is concealed behind a mask.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	53	"[what]"
common_day1_afternoon_station_doctor_nurse_eb4736e0		I have seen worse, working on the wards. Much worse.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	53	"[what]"
common_day1_afternoon_station_doctor_nurse_c9a1b4e7		But I was not expecting it, and the surprise must have shown on my face.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	53	"[what]"
common_day1_afternoon_station_doctor_nurse_44194dcc	broken	Thomas Moody. Lady Claythorn invited me. I don't suppose you are bound for the same place?	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	67	broken "[what]"
common_day1_afternoon_station_doctor_nurse_11f45609		It takes a moment before anyone can respond.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	73	"[what]"
common_day1_afternoon_station_doctor_nurse_1e7c7ef3		We are all shocked by the mask covering most of his face.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	73	"[what]"
common_day1_afternoon_station_doctor_nurse_a2f3cf8f		A "broken face" from the war.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	73	"[what]"
common_day1_afternoon_station_doctor_nurse_2c125c8c		It's not the first one I've seen, but I'm still not used to it.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	73	"[what]"
common_day1_afternoon_station_doctor_nurse_e589c2e9		Apparently, neither are the people next to me.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	73	"[what]"
common_day1_afternoon_station_doctor_nurse_248e9e86		Nobody speaks for a moment.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	87	"[what]"
common_day1_afternoon_station_doctor_nurse_55c5949f		Doctor Baldwin collects himself first.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	87	"[what]"
common_day1_afternoon_station_doctor_nurse_6f6d1efb	doctor	Hello, Mr Moody. You're with the right people.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	93	doctor "[what]"
common_day1_afternoon_station_doctor_nurse_2a04d282	doctor	This young man was about to drive us to Claythorn Manor.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	93	doctor "[what]"
common_day1_afternoon_station_doctor_nurse_a939665a	doctor	I'm Daniel Baldwin, and this is Rosalind Marsh.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	93	doctor "[what]"
common_day1_afternoon_station_doctor_nurse_6dca564c	doctor	Nice to meet you.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	93	doctor "[what]"
common_day1_afternoon_station_doctor_nurse_fe924410		We exchange a few pleasantries, then go to the car and begin our journey to Claythorn Manor.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/1_Afternoon/1_main.rpy	103	"[what]"
common_day1_evening_doctor_nurse_broken_arrival_a5863503	butler	Welcome everyone.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	6	butler "[what]"
common_day1_evening_doctor_nurse_broken_arrival_db2d22d1	butler	You are the first guests to arrive for this week-end event.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	6	butler "[what]"
common_day1_evening_doctor_nurse_broken_arrival_ecc97bde	butler	It's a bit early, so it may take a while before others arrive. In the meantime, let me show you to your rooms.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	6	butler "[what]"
common_day1_evening_doctor_nurse_broken_arrival_d53f57e3	butler	You can rest there a bit, there will be drinks later in the tea room.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	6	butler "[what]"
common_day1_evening_doctor_nurse_broken_arrival_46c434d7	doctor	Perfect, when should we meet later?	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	16	doctor "[what]"
common_day1_evening_doctor_nurse_broken_arrival_019c8d5e	butler	Around four I believe.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	20	butler "[what]"
common_day1_evening_host_welcome_speech_de0df00e	host	Welcome, everyone. My apologies for keeping you waiting.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	29	host "[what]"
common_day1_evening_host_welcome_speech_5c3fbebc	host	Now that we're all gathered, I'd like to express my gratitude once more.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	29	host "[what]"
common_day1_evening_host_welcome_speech_adbd6522	host	As you already know, you are here because of the heroic acts you've committed in the past.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	29	host "[what]"
common_day1_evening_host_welcome_speech_44757dd9	host	I've taken notice of these actions and felt it was my responsibility to extend a formal 'thank you.'	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	29	host "[what]"
common_day1_evening_host_welcome_speech_8feadbb3	host	I realise the invitation letter you received was somewhat vague, so let me clarify its contents now.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	29	host "[what]"
common_day1_evening_host_welcome_speech_aa6c1d46	host	My first gift to you is a stay at my manor.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	29	host "[what]"
common_day1_evening_host_welcome_speech_8068cb25	host	You'll be fully catered to, enjoying the most refined food, expertly prepared by my personal chef.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	29	host "[what]"
common_day1_evening_host_welcome_speech_55cd481c	host	During the three days we'll spend together, we'll also partake in various activities, which I'm sure you'll find enjoyable.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	29	host "[what]"
common_day1_evening_host_welcome_speech_f238bd69	host	My second gift is a sum of one thousand pounds, awarded to each and every one of you.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	29	host "[what]"
common_day1_evening_host_welcome_speech_3403e8a4	host	This is my way of thanking those as selfless as yourselves, who help others without thought of reward.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	29	host "[what]"
common_day1_evening_host_welcome_speech_cf518bfa		Following her speech, our host settles back down in her chair.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	51	"[what]"
common_day1_evening_second_arrival_part_1_da57a5d0	butler	Good afternoon, everyone, and welcome to Claythorn Manor.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	62	butler "[what]"
common_day1_evening_second_arrival_part_1_440927ae	butler	I'm sorry that Lady Claythorn can't greet you herself.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	62	butler "[what]"
common_day1_evening_second_arrival_part_1_491e4fdb	butler	She is still busy preparing for tonight.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	62	butler "[what]"
common_day1_evening_second_arrival_part_1_7c8cda89	butler	In the meantime, you can enjoy some drinks in the tea room.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	62	butler "[what]"
common_day1_evening_second_arrival_part_1_5c494ae1	butler	Or, if you wish to change, I can show you to your room right now.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	62	butler "[what]"
common_day1_evening_second_arrival_part_1_38ba0bca	drunk	I'm good, but I could use a drink.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	74	drunk "[what]"
common_day1_evening_second_arrival_part_1_3b4a58f6	drunk	Which way is the tea room?	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	74	drunk "[what]"
common_day1_evening_second_arrival_part_2_bc620f4e	butler	Very well, sir. You'll find the tea room through the door on your left.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	85	butler "[what]"
common_day1_evening_second_arrival_part_2_6f826478	butler	Other guests who arrived earlier are already settled there.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	85	butler "[what]"
common_day1_evening_second_arrival_part_2_d8f0c7d8	butler	You can join them.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	85	butler "[what]"
common_day1_evening_second_arrival_part_2_02eb75a8	captain	I'll come with you.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	93	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_1_9a716f96	captain	It was in June of 1900, so some of you might remember.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	105	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_1_0650a4f0	captain	In China, a group of rebels, called the "Boxers," had taken up arms against foreign presence in their country.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	105	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_1_e5dae6dd	captain	They were a group of mostly peasants, poorly armed.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	105	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_1_9dd0168a	captain	We called them "Boxers" because of their use of martial arts in their fights.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	105	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_170184b7	captain	They managed to surround the Europeans and Japanese in the "International Legations" quarter, in China's capital, Beijing.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	121	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_0b28519f	captain	There, the besieged did their best to resist the Chinese assaults, but it was obvious to everyone that they wouldn't last very long.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	121	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_ef8fcf3d	captain	In order to break the siege and rescue their compatriots, the largest foreign nations formed expeditions to help lift the siege of Beijing.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	131	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_52cdaee7	captain	I was part of the most important one, and the only successful one: The "Gaselee Expedition," named after Alfred Gaselee, the British expedition leader.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	131	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_f0bcf997	captain	It was a mish-mash of troops from eight different countries.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	131	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_b9de1dcc	captain	Japan, The British Empire, The United States, France, Russia, German Empire, Italy, and Austria-Hungary.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	131	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_7c2952d8	captain	As an Indian officer, I was obviously part of the British army.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	131	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_f7281bc6	captain	We first landed at Tientsin, then we marched from there to reach Beijing.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	131	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_e38ecee7	captain	Our goal was to rescue the civilians besieged there, as well as people from previous expeditions.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	131	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_c2327bce	captain	The journey was a total nightmare.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	131	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_bb74768a	captain	We endured a march of almost a hundred miles, where we were under constant attacks from Chinese troops.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	131	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_42d4202a	captain	If that wasn't bad enough, some poorly led and confused soldiers, notably from the French army, often ended up shooting at their allies.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	131	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_6bf4886b	captain	But the worst part was the scorching heat.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	131	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_23d78a82	captain	Even my fellow Indian soldiers were not immune to it, and many died of sunstroke.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	131	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_de6bfec9	captain	By the time we reached Peking, our expedition had lost hundred of men.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	131	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_59eaacf1	captain	By that time, the soldiers were angry, tired, and restless.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	131	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_d15a794c	captain	They had started to commit such acts that I can't even repeat here.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	131	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_0c3a4613	captain	I was expecting the exactions of the Japanese and the Russians, who were known for their ruthlessness.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	131	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_14c68b5d	captain	But in the end, our proud "civilized" European nations fared no better.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	131	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_07a0619d	captain	The final assault of the besieged was also an example of a lack of discipline among the soldiers and their commanders.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	131	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_d607b62c	captain	Each country was supposed to attack a different gate of the city.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	131	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_cad7bebb	captain	But the Russians were not happy with their assigned choice of gate.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	131	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_eb069c4b	captain	So they woke up early and assaulted the closest gate to the Legation Quarters, where the Americans were supposed to be.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	131	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_636b8ed4	captain	They wanted to be the first army to reach the defenders, and so claim the glory of having liberated the city by themselves.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	131	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_d199efb5	captain	Bloody fools.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	131	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_f89b8ce9	captain	Luckily, in the end, we managed to conquer Beijing without too much trouble.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	131	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_bb0ddf19	captain	We even entered the Imperial City and rooted out the Empress.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	131	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_5eb13541	captain	It was an undeniable victory, but the price paid was high.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	131	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_a2a292f2	captain	Afterwards, we stayed and occupied the city.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	187	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_4b2a3ee9	captain	To compensate themselves, the soldiers went on a looting frenzy.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	187	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_536a0e16	captain	Sadly, people in the British army also took part in it.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	187	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_d2d71aad	captain	But not in the same outrageous manner as other nations.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	187	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_e674be8f	captain	At least, looting on the part of British troops was carried out in the most orderly fashion.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	187	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_58a4b661	captain	We held loot auctions every day except Sunday in front of the main gate to the British Legation.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	187	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_324145f6	captain	It was the best way to compensate for the loss of our compatriots who had suffered the siege for three months.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	187	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_0b4bb4de	captain	There was no way around it, I'm afraid.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	187	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_82d9f2d8	captain	Well, in any case, that was my first campaign as a captain.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	187	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_a56aa09c	captain	And I do not regret it.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	187	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_56efa941	captain	I stayed a few more months in China to ensure the peaceful transition.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	187	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_a075994c	captain	In the end, my commanders were really pleased with me.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	187	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_2bf83cd5	captain	So, I was sent to London to lead a training regiment nearby.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	187	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_e382283d	captain	That was very rare for someone of Indian descent.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	187	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_captain_billiard_room_speech_part_2_f016d63b	captain	In any case, that's why I live in England today.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	187	captain "[what]"
captain_psychic_should_talk_to_captain_first_1253b2a1	captain	I don't want to make a scene, but I am the one on your left.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	229	captain "[what]"
captain_psychic_should_talk_to_captain_first_5aca1512	captain	You should have engaged in conversation with me first.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	229	captain "[what]"
captain_psychic_should_talk_to_captain_first_39a35c47	psychic	Oh, how dreadful of me. I do apologise.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	235	psychic "[what]"
common_day1_evening_tea_room_captain_arrives_6e360681	captain	Hello there, I am Captain Sushil Sinha.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	247	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_tea_room_captain_arrives_f8fed4bc		As he sees the new guests coming in, Thomas Moody joins me back to greet them.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	253	"[what]"
common_day1_evening_tea_room_captain_arrives_49263603	broken	Nice to meet you, Captain. I am Thomas Moody.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	257	broken "[what]"
common_day1_evening_tea_room_captain_arrives_2da85eca	doctor	Doctor Daniel Baldwin.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	261	doctor "[what]"
common_day1_evening_tea_room_captain_arrives_cfb75e29	doctor	How do you do.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	261	doctor "[what]"
common_day1_evening_tea_room_captain_arrives_e3b3325e	captain	Nice to meet you both.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	267	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_tea_room_captain_arrives_bdef91e7		I notice at once that Mr Moody is wearing a mask.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	272	"[what]"
common_day1_evening_tea_room_captain_arrives_4c27b47d		I have seen many of those. The poor man must have suffered terribly during the war.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	272	"[what]"
common_day1_evening_tea_room_captain_arrives_444c06ae		I must be careful not to stare.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	272	"[what]"
common_day1_evening_tea_room_captain_arrives_0e6a7c5b	broken	And who is the gentleman over there?	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	282	broken "[what]"
common_day1_evening_tea_room_captain_arrives_7936e3e7	captain	That would be Samuel Manning.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	286	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_tea_room_captain_arrives_9f995264	captain	I am afraid he had a bit too much to drink.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	286	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_tea_room_captain_arrives_9f07ad63	captain	But don't worry about him.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	286	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_tea_room_captain_arrives_4e720148		We watch as Manning fills a water glass to the brim with sherry.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	295	"[what]"
common_day1_evening_tea_room_captain_arrives_bf7953fb		He drinks it in one go, then sits down on the sofa and falls asleep almost immediately.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	295	"[what]"
common_day1_evening_tea_room_captain_arrives_b60ca65f		We all glance at him from afar as he fills a water glass to the brim with sherry.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	302	"[what]"
common_day1_evening_tea_room_captain_arrives_a3ea6984		He then proceeds to chug it in one sip.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	302	"[what]"
common_day1_evening_tea_room_captain_arrives_d5e443ad		After that, he sits down on the sofa next to him and immediately falls asleep.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	302	"[what]"
common_day1_evening_tea_room_captain_arrives_6470733b	captain	Well, that should keep him still for a while.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	310	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_tea_room_captain_arrives_b066aebb	doctor	Indeed, it's impressive that...	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	316	doctor "[what]"
common_day1_evening_tea_room_captain_arrives_b7c8f4b0	captain	It reminds me of a fellow I knew back in the Army.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	320	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_tea_room_captain_arrives_a02548a0		The words left my mouth before I have weighed them.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	326	"[what]"
common_day1_evening_tea_room_captain_arrives_695dc9f8		Only once I am halfway through do I notice that I have spoken straight over the doctor.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	326	"[what]"
common_day1_evening_tea_room_captain_arrives_6135503a		An old habit, picked up a lot time ago, when I noticed that if I don't impose myself, no one will pay attention to me.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	326	"[what]"
common_day1_evening_tea_room_captain_arrives_e9e134ff		Rude, perhaps. Yet stopping now would be worse than carrying on.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	326	"[what]"
common_day1_evening_tea_room_captain_arrives_52ce8dec	captain	He was my superior, but I swear I never saw him sober.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	336	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_tea_room_captain_arrives_da786ab5	captain	Even in the mornings, he was always still drunk from the day before.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	336	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_nurse_joins_captain_40b63b61	captain	Oh, hello Miss ... ?	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	351	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_nurse_joins_captain_117572eb	nurse	Miss Marsh.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	355	nurse "[what]"
common_day1_evening_nurse_joins_captain_572866aa	captain	How do you do, Miss Marsh. Captain Sushil Sinha.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	359	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_nurse_joins_captain_579d1df1	captain	I was telling those gentlemen a story about a certain conflict I was involved in.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	359	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_nurse_joins_captain_8dc321f9	captain	But I can change the subject if you prefer.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	359	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_nurse_joins_captain_9d10695a	nurse	No, please, go on. I am quite familiar with wartime stories, having served as a nurse through more than one.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	367	nurse "[what]"
common_day1_evening_nurse_joins_captain_7c16770e	captain	Really? You were a wartime nurse. How interesting.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	371	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_nurse_joins_captain_2869c428	captain	Well, where was I?	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	371	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_nurse_joins_captain_249b7101	broken	I believe you were talking about the Anglo-Zanzibar War.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	377	broken "[what]"
common_day1_evening_nurse_joins_captain_296bb40e	captain	Right.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	381	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_nurse_joins_captain_dbaabd83	captain	That's where I got my first battle scar.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	381	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_nurse_joins_captain_3ae8ffd6	captain	It's on my back so I won't show it to you, but it was rather dangerous fighting.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	381	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_nurse_joins_captain_5b0358bd	captain	Not like the Great War of course, and not that I can understand your pain.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	381	captain "[what]"
common_day1_evening_nurse_joins_captain_48e7d12a	captain	But still, a battle wound is a battle wound.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	381	captain "[what]"
common_day1_drinks_lad_psychic_encounter_3b6b7b08	lad	Nice to meet you, Miss Baxter. I am Ted Harring.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	401	lad "[what]"
common_day1_drinks_lad_psychic_encounter_ad344ca2	psychic	How do you do, Mr Harring.	game/scripts/_common/Day 1/2_Evening/1_main.rpy	405	psychic "[what]"
common_day2_morning_host_death_788fab01		Suddenly, Lady Claythorn and the butler are back in the room.	game/scripts/_common/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	6	"[what]"
common_day2_morning_host_death_f0318b3b	captain	Lady Claythorn, what is happening?	game/scripts/_common/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	10	captain "[what]"
common_day2_morning_host_death_8b160ed9		The lady is visibly distressed.	game/scripts/_common/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	14	"[what]"
common_day2_morning_host_death_a5bd97f0	host	I'm sorry to announce such horrible news, everyone.	game/scripts/_common/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	18	host "[what]"
common_day2_morning_host_death_98cbccba	host	It appears that Mr Moody passed away in his sleep last night.	game/scripts/_common/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	18	host "[what]"
common_day2_morning_host_death_8684730e		The room instantly falls silent.	game/scripts/_common/Day 2/1_Morning/1_main.rpy	26	"[what]"
